title: * master mix *
directions: Stir baking powder, salt, cream of tartar, dry
milk solids and sugar into unsifted flour, then sift all together.
Cut shortening into mixture until it looks like corn meal.
Place in sealed container and store.
This is great to have in the camper and keeps well.

title: banana bread
directions: Add sugar to mashed bananas.
Then add oleo, flour, soda and vanilla; mix well.
Bake in 2 small greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Test for doneness.

title: sour cream fudge cake(heritage cake)
directions: Stir dry ingredients twice and place in mixing bowl.
Blend melted butter into beaten eggs.
Add sour cream and vanilla, beat until smooth.
Pour liquid ingredients into dry ingredients. Using only 60 strokes, blend together thoroughly.
Do not over beat.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: fried apples
directions: Peel apples and quarter.
Put in frying pan with the other ingredients.
Cover with lid and cook until tender, occasionally turning with a fork.
Take lid off and let water dry out on low heat.
At last, you may sprinkle cinnamon over apples if you like spices.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus. Place asparagus in greased baking dish. Add layer of eggs, layer of grated cheese and layer of soup. Sprinkle with cracker crumbs. Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: beef kidney pie
directions: Prepare pie crusts and refrigerate until ready to use.
Cut round steak into 2 x 1-inch strips.
Roll in 1/4 cup flour; shake off excess.
Brown in cooking oil and butter, turning with tongs until well done on all sides, about 25 minutes.
Brown only enough meat each time to cover bottom of skillet.

title: oatmeal rolls
directions: Grease 3 loaf pans.
Put frozen dinner rolls in pans.
Sprinkle 1 pkg. butterscotch pudding (not instant) over the top, plus 1 cup brown sugar and 1/4 c. melted butter.
Cover with a paper towel or cloth.
Do this in the evening and let sit out on counter until morning.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge(microwave)
directions: Lightly butter 8 x 8-inch cake pan, set aside to receive mixture.
Blend sugar and cocoa in large mixing bowl, place butter and milk in bowl (don't stir).
Put microwave on full power, cook mixture for 2 minutes.
Remove and stir well, adding vanilla and nuts.
Pour mixture into cake pan and chill in refrigerator until set.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream together well the sugar, egg yolks and butter; add vanilla.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Add flour mixture alternately with the sour cream, beating after each addition.
Beat egg whites separately until stiff and fold gently into batter.
Pour in a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 300° for 2 hours or until cake tests done.

title: easy chocolate icing
directions: Cream butter.
Add cocoa and sugar alternately with milk (may need to add more if too thick).
Blend in vanilla.
Makes 2 cups. Very easy and tasty.

title: mexican crescent pie
directions: Brown hamburger; add salt and pepper.
Add taco seasoning mix and 1 cup hot water.
Let simmer for 5 minutes.
Separate crescent rolls into 8 triangles.
Place triangles in ungreased
9 x 13-inch pan or 2 pie tins.
Press triangle edges together to form a crust. Spoon meat mixture evenly over the rolls.
Arrange tomato slices, overlapping to cover meat.
Sprinkle on chillies and pepper. Sprinkle 1 cup of cheese over.
In a small bowl, mix sour cream and mayonnaise, onions and olives.
Spread over filling and top with remaining cheese.
Bake until crust is brown and cheese is melted.
Let cool 5 minutes.

title: herman pancakes
directions: Mix Herman and all other ingredients together.
Pour onto hot griddle or frying pan.
Make pancakes smaller than usual and cook more slowly.

title: creole cole slaw
directions: Bring last 6 ingredients to a boil.
Layer vegetables in a large bowl.
Sprinkle sugar over vegetables.
Pour the boiled ingredients over vegetables.
Cover bowl and chill at least 3 hours before serving.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and pudding.
Add
boiling water.
Cool till it gets the thickness of cream.
Add Cool Whip.
Add oranges and fruit cocktail.

title: apricot on the half-shell
directions: Cut apricots in half, then remove the pits and stems.
In a large bowl, combine orange juice, cinnamon, almond extract and maple
syrup.
Add apricots and toss until they're well coated. Then let them marinate for 30 minutes.
Preheat broiler.
Remove apricots from the bowl, reserving marinade.
Fill each apricot half with about 1/2 tablespoon of cheese and set on a baking sheet; broil until light brown.

title: apple dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add sugars, vanilla and peanuts.
Beat until smooth.
Serve as a dip for sliced apples.

title: korean shortribs
directions: Combine all ingredients for marinade.
Cover and chill 4 to 5 hours before grilling.
Baste during cooking.

title: old settlers' baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef, bacon and onion.
Add sugars, catsup, mustard and molasses to the beef mixture, then add beans.
Put in a casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Split cake into 3 layers.
Spread jam between layers and reassemble layers.
Cut into 2-inch cubes.
Arrange cubes in 2-quart serving bowl.
Sprinkle with orange juice.
Wash strawberries.
Save 8 to 12 for garnish.
Slice remaining and spoon over cake.
Pour chilled Custard Sauce over berries. Refrigerate covered for 1 hour.
Whip cream to soft peak stage. Add sugar and vanilla.
Whip until stiff.
Spread whipped cream over custard.
Garnish with whole strawberries.
Chill.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzels, add 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan, which has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake for 8 minutes at 400°.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and salt; stir well.
Add vanilla and milk; stir well.
Cook 15 minutes.
Do not stir after it begins to boil. Cook until mixture boils down.
Remove from burner.
Add butter and stir.
Add peanut butter.
Stir well.
Pour into prepared plate.

title: shrimp dip
directions: *Scrape a cut onion with back of spoon for 1 tablespoon juice.

title: beryl's cheap chocolate cake(cake)
directions: In a large bowl, beat the eggs.
Add sugar and vanilla. Stir. Then add Crisco oil.
Stir oil in well.
Add buttermilk. Mix well. Measure remaining dry ingredients into sifter.
Sift into mixture and blend well.
Last add 1 cup boiling water.
Mix well until smooth.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13 greased and floured or waxed paper lined pan for 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix with the 2/3 cup water.
Beat well and bake at 350° for one hour. Makes 2 loaves.

title: silly dough
directions: You will need a mixing bowl and a big spoon.

title: marinated ranchero steak
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Leave plenty of room for stirring.
Refrigerate for a minimum of four hours.

title: aunt delano's fudge
directions: Boil milk, sugar, salt and butter for 5 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Add Hershey bars and chocolate chips.
Turn over and under but do not stir.
When all is melted, add marshmallow cream, then nuts.
Fold but don't stir.
Pour into a greased pan.
Let cool, then cut into squares.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: pu cha's oriental egg rolls
directions: At least one day before, saute half the garlic (2 cloves) with all the vegetables in 3 tablespoons vegetable oil until almost tender.
Season to taste with 2 tablespoons of soy sauce, a dash of Accent, ginger, salt and black pepper.
Remove from pan.
Brown the ground beef with the remaining 2 tablespoons of garlic and 2 tablespoons of soy sauce.
Season to taste with salt and black pepper.
Add the vegetable mixture to this.
Add 1 1/2 tablespoons dry mustard and enough cornstarch to thicken slightly.
Refrigerate the mixture overnight or cool well.
Place 1/2 cup of mixture in center of egg roll wrapper.
Fold and roll to enclose filling. Seal by dampening edge of wrapper with water.
Deep fry until light brown.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix dressing, oil, garlic, salt and dill in large bowl.
Add crackers; mix in gently to coat.
Stir gently every 15 minutes for a couple of hours.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: ground beef pie
directions: Cut shortening into flour; add salt.
Sprinkle water onto flour mixture; mix until mixture forms a ball and cleans sides of bowl.
Roll out dough into oblong shape; place in an 8-inch pie tin.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli and onion fine; mix all ingredients, except cashews and bacon. Marinate. When ready to serve, add cashews and crumbled bacon for crunchy texture.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked, unforked, pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until clean blade test.

title: shrimp casino
directions: Place shrimp flat, cut side up, on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle bread crumbs, oregano and parsley.
Moisten with butter and oil. Broil until shrimp are firm (4 to 5 minutes).
Top with bacon and lemon juice.
Broil 1 minute.
Serve hot.
Yields 4 servings.

title: strawberry yogurt pie
directions: Mix the yogurt and Cool Whip together.
Place in the graham cracker crust.
Slice the strawberries and place on top.
Chill for 2 -3 hours.
Serve.

title: mock enchiladas
directions: Brown meat in hot fat.
Add onion; cook until golden.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add beans or chili.
Place layer of Fritos in greased, 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Alternate layers of chili mixture, Fritos and cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: sauerkraut cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add rest.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes in Bundt pan.
Frost, if desired, with favorite frosting.

title: jellied cranberry sauce
directions: Cook for about 5 minutes after berries burst open.

title: oven fried chicken drumsticks
directions: Place 3 or 4 chicken legs at a time in a plastic bag and shake with flour mixture.
Place chicken in a single layer in an ungreased baking pan.
Drizzle the melted shortening over chicken. Bake in a preheated oven at 425° for 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Combine in baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cut in squares and serve with a can of cream of chicken soup and 1/4 cup milk, mixed.

title: egg custard
directions: Makes its own crust.
Can add coconut to mixture for pie.

title: banana salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite size pieces, place in the bowl you plan to serve the salad.
Top with desired amount of bananas and ladle a couple of scoops of dressing to top.
Sprinkle the chopped peanuts over the top.
Let sit about 30 minutes in the refrigerator before you serve.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Microwave, uncovered, on High 3 to 5 minutes or until thickened, stirring every minute until begins to thicken, then every 30 seconds.
Cook 30 seconds more.
Serve warm.

title: party meat balls
directions: Mix ground chuck, eggs, salt and pepper.
Shape into miniature balls.
Place party balls on a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove cover and bake 30 minutes longer. Transfer to chafing dish and pour sauce over.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Mix with sauce. Mix cheeses with egg. Layer sauce, noodles, sauce, noodles and cheese; sauce, noodles and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: angel food strawberry fluff
directions: Let egg whites stand at room temperature 30 minutes.
Draw a 10-inch circle on plain brown paper or parchment paper; place on baking sheet.

title: potluck beef barbecue
directions: Place roast, water, vinegar, salt and pepper in a slow cooking pot.
Cover and cook at medium for 8 to 10 hours or until meat is very tender.
Remove roast, discard cooking liquid.
Shred roast by pulling meat apart with two forks.
Return meat to cooking pot. Add remaining ingredients and stir to combine.
Cover and increase heat to medium high.
Cook 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to low for serving.
Makes 16 servings.

title: peach jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, sugar and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil until Jell-O and sugar are dissolved.
Remove from heat; add pineapple and peaches.

title: red velvet cake frosting
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and vanilla.
Add powdered sugar and beat until fluffy.

title: no peek casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle generously with grated Cheddar cheese or Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: truly different cupcakes
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in heavy pan.
Add nuts and stir to coat.
Remove from heat.
Combine remaining ingredients in a bowl. Mix only enough to blend; do not beat!
Add chocolate mixture and again mix without beating.
Pour into muffin cups.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 20 to 24 cupcakes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Melt butter, add onion and cook until limp.
Add beef and stir until meat is no longer red.
Pour in tomatoes, consomme and water.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat about 45 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Wash, stem and drain strawberries.
Place berries in the bottom of baked pie shell.
Slowly cook the sugar, cornstarch, water, salt and food coloring until glossy.
Pour hot mixture over the strawberries and place in refrigerator until cold.
Just before serving, cover with whipped cream.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain the corn.
Melt the oleo in casserole dish. Add the flour and stir.
Add drained corn and whipping cream. Cook at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: fish a la burgendland
directions: Cut fish in pieces.
Salt and sprinkle with lemon juice and then let stand for 10 minutes.
Then dip in milk, then in flour. Saute both sides in butter until golden brown.
Remove to shallow casserole.
Blend anchovies into fish butter.
Pour over fish. Pour sour cream over and bake 5 minutes in preheated moderate oven (375°).
Lightly saut peppers in butter.
Arrange over fish.

title: pineapple dump cake(quick and easy)
directions: Mix together by hand.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 9x12 pan. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
In small bowl, mix mushroom soup, cheese and mayonnaise.
Place broccoli in casserole dish.
Add soup, cheese and mayonnaise mixture.
Sprinkle Ritz crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Put eggs in pan, boil gently for 15 minutes.
Run under cold running water to let them cool down.
Peel the shells, cut eggs in half.
Remove yolks and mash until fine.
Add a pinch of salt and pepper, vinegar and mustard.
Mix all together until well blended. Refill egg halves and sprinkle with paprika.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: granny's pineapple pudding
directions: Arrange
vanilla
wafers in bottom and sides of 10-inch square casserole.	Add a layer of pineapple.
Alternate layers until the dish is 3/4 full.
Mix pudding according to package directions. Pour
over	pineapple
and	wafers.
Chill	until ready to serve.

title: irish stew
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; pour over beef in shallow pan. Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours.
Drain meat, reserving marinade.
Remove and discard bay leaves.
Heat oil in Dutch oven over medium heat.
Brown beef in oil.
Add broth and marinade; bring to boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours. Add carrots, onions and potatoes.
Cover and cook 30 minutes. Yield:
2 1/2 quarts.

title: edna's cranberry mold
directions: Grind (or finely chop) fruit and nuts.
Add sugar; set aside until sugar is dissolved.
Add cream and marshmallows.
Put in loaf pan.
Freeze.
Slice to serve.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Wash and slice apples.
Mix well with sugar.
Add oil and eggs.
Sift and add flour, cinnamon, salt and soda.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Put into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: beef-egg sandwich
directions: Cook and stir meat, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Blend eggs and water; pour over meat mixture.
Cook on low heat just until eggs are set. Lift cooked portions with spatula; turn to cook eggs evenly. Serve in buns.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 1-quart baking dish.
Combine apples, sugar and cinnamon.
Pour into dish.
Mix remaining ingredients until blended and drop by teaspoonfuls onto fruit. Bake for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 10 minutes longer or until fruit is tender.
Serve warm with cream or brown sugar sauce; peaches, cherries or strawberries.

title: santa fe soup
directions: Brown meat with onion, drain well.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for about 30 mins., great for crockpot.
Garnish with shredded cheese, sour cream and tortilla chips.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Spray the bottom of a 4-quart saucepan with nonstick cooking spray.
Put onions, peppers and garlic in the pan; saute for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, tomatoes and green chilies, tomato sauce, chili powder and cumin.
Bring to a boil.
Add corn and kidney beans.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve over a baked potato or brown rice.
Yields 10 cups.
Serves 10.

title: homemade bubbles
directions: Mix until sugar dissolves in 1 3/4 quarts of water.
Shake well.

title: pool room slaw
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together and boil for 20 minutes. Pack in jars and seal.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in pan.
Put on medium heat until starts to boil. Stir to avoid sticking.
Add vanilla, salt, oats and peanut butter.
Stir and spoon on foil until cool. Serve.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar together well.
Add chocolate.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating for 5 full minutes after each addition. Blend in vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill for 6 to 8 hours or overnight.
Serve topped with whipped cream.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: mock indian pudding
directions: Mix together beaten egg, milk, molasses, sugar, melted butter and salt.
Add cornflakes.
Cook slowly in double boiler without stirring or set in pan of warm water and bake 1 hour at 375°. Serve with cream or ice cream.

title: pecan pie
directions: Add Karo to eggs first.
Add other ingredients.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk and margarine over medium heat until a small amount forms soft ball when dropped into cold water.
Add miniature marshmallows and heat until melted.
Add graham cracker crumbs and chopped pecans.
Mix.
Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper.

title: crock-pot country style steak
directions: Brown cube steaks in a skillet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Place in crock-pot. Mix together soup mix and soup. Pour over cube steaks and cook on low for 3 to 4 hours.

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and Italian seasoning.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Top with half the cheese, then pizza sauce.
Add toppings you desire (green peppers, mushrooms, onion, olives, etc.).
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with breadsticks or crackers.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix egg and vinegar with enough water to fill 1 cup measure. Mix flour and shortening, cutting the two together until mixture is size of small peas.
Pour in liquid mixture and mix well.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine
all
ingredients.
Mix
well and pour into two 9-inch pie
pans
or one long baking dish. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Makes its own crust.

title: zucchini patties(use as hors d' oeuvres or side dish)
directions: Drain zucchini and squeeze out excess moisture.
Place zucchini in a large bowl.
Stir in flour.
Add buttermilk or milk, eggs, parsley, mint, garlic, onion and salt and pepper.
Mix well.

title: garden vegetable pie
directions: Blend milk, flour, eggs, salt and pepper.
Stir in rest of ingredients and pour into 9 or 10-inch casserole dish.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in a 400° oven.
Makes 4 servings.

title: poor boy casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Mix with sliced potatoes, green beans, cream of mushroom soup and salt and pepper to taste.
Put in baking dish and top with shredded cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until cheese melts.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Combine cheese and butter in a saucepan over low heat; stir until cheese is melted.
Remove from heat; stir in sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes, mixing gently.
Pour into a buttered 2-quart casserole; dot with 2 tablespoons batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
When cake is done and still hot, poke holes in it and pour condensed milk and caramel over the top of cake.
Let cool, put cool whip over top of cake and crumble candy over the top of cool whip.

title: mom's blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg.
Add milk.
Add dry ingredients. Fold in blueberries.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Sprinkle a bit of sugar on top of each.
Makes 12 muffins.
Serve hot with lots of butter!

title: cooked salad dressing
directions: Add vinegar to egg and beat.
Stir in rest of ingredients. Cook in double boiler or over water; stir constantly until it thickens.

title: caramel filled brownies
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk in double boiler. Keep warm.
Mix cake mix, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and margarine. Put 1/2 of cake mix mixture in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread evenly.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°.
Cool 2 minutes.
Spread with caramel mixture.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Add 1/2 cup walnuts to the rest of chocolate mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls onto caramel.
Sprinkle with remaining walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: machinka
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and milk; stir until thickens.
Add eggs to white sauce; stir well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve on bread or toast.

title: old recipe for grape juice
directions: Put into half gallon jars. Fill jar with boiling water and seal. This may also be made in gallon jars, just double grapes, sugar and water.

title: ham loaf
directions: Grind together ham, pork and veal.
Combine meat, bread crumbs, pepper, eggs and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Form into loaf and place into baking pan.
Mix sugar, mustard and vinegar; baste over meat. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: In a large skillet, over medium heat, stir-fry vegetables in 2 tablespoons oil for 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
In a small bowl, combine cornstarch, soy sauce and sherry.
Blend together thoroughly, slowly adding beef stock and water.
Add mixture to cooked vegetables, adding constantly to coat well.
Cook over low heat for 2 to 3 minutes, adding additional water or stock if a thinner sauce is desired.
Serve over Minute rice.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Toss lettuce with celery and oranges.
Place slivered almonds and 1/2 cup of sugar in a frying pan.
Fry until golden brown, stirring constantly.
Place on waxed paper and crumble when cool. Heat salad oil, vinegar and 6 tablespoons of sugar for 2 minutes. Cool.
Add almond extract.
Add dressing to greens and toss.
Place on plates and garnish with crumbled almonds.
Serves 8.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple and orange.
Add enough water to make 2 cups of liquid.
Heat liquid to boiling point.
Pour over both jellos. Stir until
dissolved.
Add cranberries and stir until the jellied part has dissolved.
Add oranges and pineapples.
Mix well.
Pour into 8x12-inch
dish and chill for several hours.

title: grandma's poultry dressing
directions: In a skillet, brown the sausage.
Drain and discard drippings. In a large mixing bowl, combine sausage and remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Place in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields 6 cups. Makes enough to stuff a medium size turkey.

title: tollerine
directions: Saute meat for few minutes.
Add first 9 ingredients and simmer.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Boil noodles and drain.
Mix with meat sauce.
Add chopped olives.
Put in baking dish.
Cover with cheese and parsley and bake at 325° to 350° (medium oven) for 1 hour.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat your oven to 350°.
Mix 1 cup sugar and cinnamon. Grease a tube pan well.
Cut biscuits into 4 parts and roll in (white) sugar and cinnamon mix.
Stack evenly into tube pan.
Melt margarine in a small saucepan and stir brown sugar into margarine. Pour this mixture over biscuits and sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: beef-cabbage soup
directions: Wash and drain fresh berries.
Puree until smooth (add a little water to frozen berries, if needed).
Add sugar and lemon juice and mix.

title: chicken fingers
directions: Beat egg and milk together.
Batter chicken in egg mixture and then in flour.
For a thicker crust, batter two times.
Put into hot grease and brown on both sides or until done.

title: cheese corn chowder
directions: Heat all ingredients.
Serve in small bread bowls.

title: aunt reta's datenut bread
directions: Sprinkle baking soda over dates. Pour boiling water over dates, add margarine. Let cool. Mix together all other ingredients. Add to date mixture. mix well. Turn into well greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45-50 min. Test with toothpick before removing from oven. Serve with butter or whipped cream cheese.

title: pickled beets (sweet)
directions: Heat syrup until boiling.
Pour over beets to within 1/2 inch of top of jar.
Put 1 teaspoon ??? per quart (1/2 teaspoon for pints).
Process 30 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: basic waffle recipe
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender.
Cover and mix only until flour is moistened.
Pour into waffle iron which has been coated with vegetable spray.

title: cloverleaf rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water with 1/3 teaspoon of sugar.
Combine warm milk, oleo, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Beat eggs, stir in warm milk mixture and then dissolved yeast mixture.
Gradually beat in flour until too stiff for beaters.
Then stir rest of four in by hand.
Turn into greased bowl. Cover and let rise until double in size.
Make into any kind of roll.
Place in a greased pan.
Let double in size.
Butter top and bake in 400° oven 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and butter top and serve.

title: oatmeal cereal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening with sugars until blended.
Add eggs; beat very well.
Add flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir in oatmeal, raisins and chocolate chips.
Add Shredded Wheat biscuits. Drop by teaspoon on greased sheet.
Bake in oven at 350° for 15 minutes, or until lightly brown.

title: peanut brittle(shared by larry sherman)
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in a saucepan.
Heat to hard crack; add peanuts and stir until mixture turns a straw color (do not overcook).
Add butter and baking soda; stir as it rises. Pour on a buttered cookie sheet to cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream
eggs, sugar, and oil.
Add dry ingredients.
Add zucchini, raisins and nuts.
Put in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bookbinders snapper soup(turtle soup)
directions: Have butcher break knuckles in 2-inch pieces.
Place in a roasting pan and add chicken fat or butter, onions, celery, carrots, thyme, marjoram, cloves, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Bake at 400° until brown (about 30 minutes).
Remove from oven and add flour, mixing well.
Reduce oven heat to 350° and cook 30 minutes longer.
Scrape mixture into a large soup kettle.
Add broth and tomatoes.
Cook at a simmer for 3 1/2 hours, covered.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt together and add to first mixture.
Spread in small cake pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over top.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Double for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: bake a scripture cake
directions: Light oven; get out utensils and ingredients.
Remove blocks and toy autos from table.
Grease pan and crack nuts.
Measure 2 cups flour.
Remove Johnny's hands from flour, wash flour off of him and re-measure flour.
Put flour, baking powder and salt in sifter.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Melt butter, cheese and the soup on the stove.
Mix onion and carrots together.
Toss together.
Put the cubes on the top and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook onions until tender and drain. Stir in tomato sauce, eggs, cheese, oatmeal, salt, pepper and thyme.
Add ground beef and pork, mixing well.
Shape into a loaf in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cinnamon sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
Pour over apple pie or ice cream.

title: taco soup
directions: Mix together and cook until hot.
If you are on Weight Watchers this is 2 1/2 points per 1 cup serving.

title: tropical waldorf salad
directions: Combine fruits.
Blend together mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon juice and ginger.
Pour over fruit and toss.
Serve on crisp salad greens.
Sprinkle with coconut if you desire.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except the chocolate chips. Dust the chips with flour and stir into batter. Bake in a Bundt pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Frost with chocolate frosting and top with nuts (optional).

title: beef tips
directions: Mix all ingredients, except beef.
When thoroughly mixed, add beef.
Put in covered casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for about 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: cranberry congealed salad
directions: Combine jello and boiling water, stir until dissolved. Cool. Add other ingredients. Pour into 9 by 13 inch dish and chill.

title: strawberry ripple freeze
directions: Combine crumbs, butter and sugar and mix well.
Press mixture over bottom and sides of a 1-quart refrigerator tray; chill.
Stir ice cream just to soften.
With spoon, quickly zigzag concentrate through ice cream until marbled.
Turn into crust and freeze until firm.
Cut in bars or wedges.

title: tuna salad
directions: Blend well; serve with crackers.

title: spanish rice
directions: While
cooking
rice, saute onions and pepper in oil in skillet.
Then add onions, peppers and tomatoes to rice.
Salt and pepper
to
taste.
Add
tablespoons
of margarine and continue to cook until rice is tender.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, flour, syrup, butter, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in 425° oven for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 45 minutes.

title: chicken with pita
directions: Saute chicken with all of the ingredients in pan with a little oil (until sauce it thick).
(Sauce to your taste.) Serve in the pita bread pocket with a choice of peas, sauteed onions, avocado and sour cream.

title: yum-yums
directions: Melt all ingredients, except marshmallows.
After a few minutes, add marshmallows.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate.
Keep in refrigerator until serving and put remainder back in refrigerator.
(Cut in squares before serving.)

title: creamy peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese at high speed until fluffy. Add Cool Whip, peanut butter, sugar and milk. Beat well. Spoon into crust. Chill at least 5 hours.

title: venison swiss steak
directions: Steak should be about 1 1/2-inches thick.
Dredge with flour and season with salt and pepper.
Brown in fat on both sides.
Add the other ingredients.
Cover tightly and cook at 350° in oven or on low on top of range until tender (about 1 1/4 hours).
Remove meat to a platter and make gravy from pan drippings.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in lightly greased pan. Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and honey.
Add strawberries, bananas, marshmallows and nuts to cream cheese mixture.
Freeze. Serve frozen.

title: italian slaw
directions: Bring sugar, oil, vinegar, celery, mustard and salt to a boil. Let cool before pouring over cabbage.
Marinate in a covered dish.

title: 4 layer cake
directions: First Layer:
Mix thoroughly and put in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan the nuts and melted stick of butter.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 15 minutes.

title: marinated fruit cup
directions: Chop the fruit.
Marinate in fruit punch or grape juice.
Serve cold.

title: cherry delight
directions: Crust:
Mix well the graham cracker crumbs and butter.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: brazilian sweet bread
directions: Stir the yeast into the warm water.
Set the mixture aside for about 10 minutes.
Mix the flour and salt into a large bowl; make a well in the center and pour in the yeast mixture, sugar, eggs, milk, butter and lemon peel.
Mix to a smooth dough; then lay the dough on a floured board and knead the dough until smooth and elastic (about 10 minutes).
If you need more flour, add slowly until dough does not stick to the hands.

Return dough to the bowl and cover; let rise for 1 hour, until it has doubled in volume. Punch down the dough and braid it or just knead it into a ball. Mold the ball the same length as the bread pan.
Cover the pan and set the dough aside in warm place until it rises above the rim (about 1 hour).
Bake for 35 minutes in a preheated oven (350°). Let cool down on wire rack.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together.
Store in covered container.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.
Use 1 to 2 teaspoons in cup boiling water.

title: seafood primavera
directions: Stir milk, Neufchatel cheese, scallions and seasonings in saucepan over low heat until smooth.
Stir in fish and Parmesan cheese.
Prepare fettucine according to package directions, adding broccoli, carrots and red pepper at the last 5 to 6 minutes of cooking time.
Drain.
Toss pasta and vegetables with sauce and fish.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Save out 1 cup of the dry cake mix.

title: beef barbecue for a crowd
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Pour off grease.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour.
Makes enough for 50 buns or more.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Blend in oleo and egg, stirring to make thick batter.
Spread pie filling into oiled pan.
Drop batter from spoon to cover filling.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until topping is brown.
I take part of the batter and pat it on bottom of pie pan.
I also use fresh apples.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork and noodles
directions: Boil pork in salt water (using enough water to cook noodles). When pork is done remove from pot and add noodles.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.

title: apple crisp
directions: Spread apples in 8-inch square pan. Sprinkle with water, cinnamon and salt. Work together until crumbly, using pastry blender, sugar, flour and butter. Spread crumb mixture over apples. Bake, uncovered, about 30 minutes. Serve warm with rich milk. Makes 6 servings.

title: stuffed hot dogs
directions: Split hot dogs down the middle halfway.
Mix ketchup, mustard and onion together.
Stuff hot dogs with mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Makes a great party or snack dish.

title: mint brownies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in jelly roll pan.
While brownies bake, melt glaze in pan (double boiler).
Cool brownies.

title: champagne punch
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve over ice.
Makes 100 (4 ounce) cups.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Put 1/2 cup water into skillet.
Add ring sausage.
Cook until water evaporates and sausage is browned (pierce slightly to remove grease).
Put potatoes into casserole.
Cover with 1/2 of tomato soup.
Lay sausage on top.
Pour remaining soup on top.
Cover; bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender. Serve with salad; makes a nice easy meal.
Serves 4.

title: japanese pecan fruit pie
directions: Cream eggs, butter and sugar.
Add vinegar and remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 50 minutes at 325°.

title: pound cake
directions: Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes in 350° oven.
This recipe is very old and good.

title: swiss broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325.
Grease 10 inch baking dish.
In 2 quart saucepan, over high heat bring 1 inch water to boil.
Add broccoli and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Drain and set aside.

title: herbed steak and onions
directions: For marinade, combine tomato juice, oil, basil, oregano, pepper and garlic.
Set aside.
Trim fat from steak and cut steak into four equal portions.
Place meat in a plastic bag set in a deep bowl.
Pour marinade over steak.
Seal bag; turn to coat steak well.
Marinate overnight in the refrigerator.
Then, drain steak, reserving marinade.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Place 2 tablespoons hamburger, 1 teaspoon tomato, olive and green pepper in Tostado. Roll up and place in 13 x 9 pan. Cover with Ragu. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Add grated cheese after 28 minutes. Melt cheese. Serve.

title: ever-ready biscuits
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening. Add milk. Add yeast dissolved in water. Mix in enough flour to make consistency of pancake mix. Let stand 1 hour. Add soda, baking powder, salt and enough flour to make a regular biscuit dough. Knead until smooth. Put into a large sized bowl and cover. Refrigerate. This dough will last for 10 days. Just take desired amount of dough and roll out on floured board. Cut biscuits. Place in greased pan and brush with melted butter. Bake at 400° until slightly brown. Makes 75 to 80 biscuits.

title: watergate salad
directions: Blend marshmallows, nuts, cool-whip; add pineapple and pudding. Chill before serving.

title: easy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, water and oil. Add chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy as "can" be rice
directions: Mix.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and let stand 10 minutes.
Stir and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana blonds
directions: Cream together margarine, brown sugar, egg and vanilla extract. Add baking powder and salt.
Mix well, then add mashed bananas and 3/4 cup coconut.
Blend in flour.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix remainder of coconut with 1 tablespoon of butter and sugar (melted) and spoon evenly over the top.
Bake in oven at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Roll out pastry to 1/4-inch thick.
Place in bottom of pie (deep dish) plate or round casserole.

title: kim's pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs with sugar.
Add oil, water and pumpkin.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Then add dates, nuts and raisins.
Blend together well.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Prepare lasagna noodles as package directs; drain.
In blender or food processor, process tomatoes until smooth.
In large saucepan, combine tomatoes, carrots, onion and seasonings; simmer 20 minutes.
Spread about 3/4 cup of the tomato mixture in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Layer one third each of lasagna, remaining tomato sauce, spinach, zucchini, mushrooms, Ricotta cheese, parsley, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layering twice.
Cover; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven; let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 8 servings.

title: veggie pizza
directions: The fruit of the land;

title: 6 week muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add mixture of eggs, milk and oil.
Mix well.
Store in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks while in use.
To bake, fill greased muffin tins 1/2 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
These may be cooked and then frozen.

title: tropic dressing
directions: Note:
Adjust vinegar and mayonnaise to taste.

title: angel gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and molasses; beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with hot water, beating until smooth.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan in moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by tablespoons on wax paper.
Cool.
Remove and put in refrigerator.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine milk and egg yolks at low speed of mixer.
Slowly add the juice, mixing until well blended.
Pour into prebaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° with or without meringue for 8 minutes. Chill.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: Cook ground beef with garlic powder and onions. Add in kidney beans when meat is almost cooked all the way. Drain and set aside. Mix lettuce, tomatoes, avocados, cheese, chips and ground beef in a large bowl. Add dressing (add to preference; we prefer a light coat of dressing in the salad which would be just a little over half the bottle). Serve immediately.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage; crumble.
Set aside to drain on paper towel. Shred cheese.
Combine all ingredients, except sausage.
Mix sausage in last.
Put in casserole dish.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pepper steak
directions: Heat wok or large iron skillet (chicken fryer); add oil and garlic. When garlic turns brown, remove. Add beef, cut in small thin pieces, and fry a few minutes. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Add beef bouillon mixture and continue to cook a few seconds or until meat is tender. (May be made in advance to this point.) Add mixture of cornstarch, soy sauce and water. Cook until sauce thickens, stirring slowly. Add green peppers, sliced lengthwise, and ginger. Heat thoroughly and serve over rice.

title: shrimp fritters
directions: Peel and devein shrimp and pat with dry towel.
Dice shrimp into 1/2-inch pieces.
Mix together the egg, flour, milk, salt and pepper.
Mix it until it's the consistency of pancake batter. Fold in diced shrimp.
Drop batter by large spoon into 1/2-inch hot oil and fry just like a pancake.
Drain on paper towel and serve hot.

title: crazy cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt, baking soda and cocoa together into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make 3 wells in dry ingredients.
Mix oil, vinegar and vanilla together; pour into the 3 wells.
Pour water over all.
Mix with fork until smooth.
Bounce pan lightly for air bubbles to rise.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter, sugar and cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add salt and vanilla; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flour.

title: easy chicken noodles
directions: Heat chicken soup.
Mix together soup and cooked noodles.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a saucepan; stir well.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.

title: trawler famous crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add more French dressing or horseradish if needed.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 6 1/2 dozen.

title: steamed fish mushrooms
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
Use 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper.
Arrange lemon slices atop fish.
Sprinkle with mushrooms. Drizzle sake over all.
Over high heat, bring water for steaming to boiling.
Place pie plate on steamer rack over boiling water.
Cover steamer and steam 12 to 15 minutes until fish flakes easily.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Cream butter
and sugar.
Add eggs 1 at a time and beat well. Stir
in
flour
gradually and add nuts and flavorings. Bake in greased shallow pan at 375°.

title: mixed greens
directions: Cook salt pork or turkey 30 minutes in 6 to 7 cups water. Trim any bruised spots on greens.
Wash in several changes of cold running water to remove all traces of dirt and sand.
Cut up and combine the greens in a Dutch oven or large pot, with remaining ingredients, including salt pork or turkey, and water.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook until done or tender, about 1 hour.

title: souped-up broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Place in an 8-inch baking dish.
Stir soup and cheese together; add milk, egg and mayonnaise.
Mix until blended.
Pour over broccoli.
Combine bread crumbs and melted butter.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sherry's chocolate caramel squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°; grease bottom only of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Measure 2 tablespoons of chocolate syrup reserve.
Mix brownie mix, remaining syrup, water and egg with spoon just until mix is moistened.
Spread in pan.
Bake 27 to 30 minutes (do not overbake), appearance or touch does not mean brownies are done.

title: cuban cheese log
directions: Grate cheese and mix all ingredients except chili powder. Knead together until smooth.
Roll in wax paper to form a log. Then sprinkle chili powder on paper and roll log in chili powder until coated.
Refrigerate and serve with crackers.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Mix sugar and syrup and let boil.
Beat in peanut butter. Stir over crushed corn flakes.
Press into buttered cookie sheet. Cut into squares.
Store in covered container.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Season both sides with tenderizer and salts.
Add smoke and Worcestershire.
Cover and marinate (turn once) 24 hours. Be sure to
use a glass or stainless steel pan.
Cook covered for 8
hours at 225°.
Let cool; slice, then reheat.
Use your favorite barbecue sauce to serve.

title: baked vidalia onions
directions: Place whole onions in dish.
Place 1 bouillon cube in each onion.
Cover and bake at 400° until tender.

title: filberts crescents
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well.
Add and mix in, one at a time, corn syrup, prune puree and the egg.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, salt and spices; mix into the wet ingredients. Chill dough for an hour or more. That done, shape the batter into balls the size of a walnut.
Dip them, firmly, into the chopped walnuts and put them onto a lightly greased cookie sheet, walnut size up!
Flatten each cookie, slightly, with the bottom of a glass.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on a rack.

title: lasagne
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Cook noodles, drain and rinse.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish in alternate layers of noodles, Mozzarella cheese, cottage cheese, and sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: debbies dip
directions: Boil soup then add gelatin add the rest.
Let chill for 3 hours.
Serve with ritz crackers.

title: shrimp-crab gumbo
directions: Heat the margarine in a large skillet.
Add the onion and okra.
Cook mixture until onion is soft.
Add tomatoes and spices to the skillet.
Mix well. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in shrimp and crab meat and cook 10 minutes.
Serve over rice or cornbread.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Cook onion, celery and bell pepper; drain.
Combine soup, eggs, mayonnaise and cheese; mix well.
Add broccoli and vegetables.
Pour into well buttered casserole and bake in 350° oven until set.
Remove from oven.
Cover with chips and bake until light brown.

title: smoked salmon spread
directions: Blend well and chill.
Serve with snack crackers.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix the dry ingredients.
Add other ingredients, except butter. Cook slowly until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add butter.
Stir and pour into pie shell.
Beat reserved egg whites until foamy; add 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar and beat until soft peaks form.
Add 4 tablespoons sugar and beat until stiff. Pour on top of pie.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.
Serves 6. Enjoy!

title: pepper steak
directions: Combine flour and seasonings.
Pound into meat with a meat hammer.
Brown meat in shortening; pour off fat.
Add soup and ketchup.
Cover and cook over low heat for 1 hour.
Add green pepper and cook for 20 minutes, or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place margarine in a deep ovenproof bowl or casserole and place in a 450° oven to melt while assembling the other ingredients.
Mix together the flour, sugar, milk and vanilla. Stir until smooth with a wire whisk.
Remove the bowl from the oven and pour flour mixture over the melted margarine.
Don't stir!
Pour can of peaches over the top of this.
Again, don't stir!
Return to the oven and cook at 450° for 10 minutes.
Turn oven down to 375° and cook until crust comes to the top and is golden brown.

title: seven layer dip
directions: In large casserole dish spread refried beans evenly in bottom. Smash avocados and mix in lemon juice.
Layer on top of beans. Mix taco seasoning in sour cream and layer on avocados.
Layer grated cheese on sour cream.
Next layer black olives, then diced tomatoes.
Chill before serving.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: marshmallow cream fudge
directions: Mix sugar, oleo and milk in large pan.
Place over low heat; stir constantly.
Bring to a boil; continue to stir and boil for 11 minutes (after it starts a full boil).
Remove from heat; add chocolate chips and stir until melted.
Add marshmallow cream.

title: mrs. read's sourdough pancakes
directions: Beat the egg white in bowl until stiff; set aside.
In medium size bowl, put egg yolk.
Add soda, salt, sugar, oil and milk; beat well.
Add 2 cups of Sourdough Starter.
As quickly as possible rapidly blend together.
Take care not to break the bubbles now or later, as they are the leavening.
Never beat or re-stir batter once it is complete.
As soon as yolk mixture and Starter are blended, pour over egg whites, folding carefully to avoid breaking bubbles.
Bake on hot greased grill.

title: salty cracker pie
directions: Beat
egg
whites
in
mixer
until
stiff.
Add
sugar gradually, then beat in baking powder and vanilla.	Last, fold in nuts and cracker crumbs.
Pour into well-greased 9-inch pie plate and
bake
It makes own top and bottom crust. Top with whipped cream.

title: lemon squares
directions: Melt margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add 2 cups flour and 1/2 cup powdered sugar; mix.
Pat down flat in pan. Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mushroom meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given and pack into loaf pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve hot or cold.

title: pizza spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti, drain and rinse.
While hot, add egg and milk. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add spaghetti.
Brown hamburger and drain the grease.
Add the chili powder, salt, pepper, garlic salt, mushrooms and sauce.
Pour over spaghetti.
Top with cheese and pepperoni. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Take off foil the last 15 minutes.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, salt, soda and flour and add nuts.
Chill in refrigerator.
Make in rolls and wrap in foil; slice and cook on ungreased sheet at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: wheat germ peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat together butter, peanut butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, wheat germ, oats, soda and salt.
Gradually mix into peanut butter mixture.
Shape level tablespoons of dough into balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheets and flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° 8-10 minutes.
Makes about 4 doz.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chickens; remove from bones and cube.
Reserve stock. Saute onion, garlic and sliced mushrooms in oil.

title: portuguese soup
directions: Brown meat in large soup pot.
Remove meat.
Add oil to soup pot and saute onion and garlic.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer about 45 minutes.
Adjust seasonings to taste.

title: never fail pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco until fluffy. Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each one. Mix flours together and add alternately with milk. Add flavoring and mix well. Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot tuna burgers
directions: Mix lightly all ingredients (except hamburger rolls).
When all ingredients are moistened, fill rolls with mixture.
Wrap each in foil and heat in 250° oven for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: prune butter
directions: Place in food processor; process at high speed.
It will make a smooth paste.
This mixture is too thick for blender.
Use immediately or store in fridge up to 3 weeks in airtight container.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well.
Fold in peas.
Chill and serve with crackers of choice.
Refrigerate.

title: michael's favorite biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in greased muffin pans. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yield: 1 dozen.

title: quick tomato mac 'n beef
directions: In a skillet over medium heat, cook beef and onion until meat is no longer pink; drain. Season with salt and pepper. Add tomatoes and water; bring to a boil. Stir in macaroni. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes or until macaroni is tender. Stir in cheese. Garnish with onions and sour cream,
if desired. Makes 4 servings.

title: mamaw pancakes
directions: Beat eggs at high speed, then lower speed.
Add milk, butter, sugar, vanilla and flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mixture should be consistency of thick cream.
Heat skillet and butter lightly. Pour batter on skillet as to size you want.
When bubbles form on top, turn quickly and brown other side.
Serve with jelly or syrup.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel, slice and cook potatoes.
Mix cornstarch, salt, pepper, milk and cheese.
Cook until thick.
Put potatoes in baking dish. Pour sauce over potatoes and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat peanut butter, shortening and sugars until fluffy.
Add eggs and mix well.
Mix soda with flour and add to mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and put in 13 x 9-inch casserole dish or pan.
Melt butter; pour 1/2 over top of casserole.
Mix remaining melted butter with croutons and spread on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco pie(a weight watchers recipe)
directions: Mix ground turkey, seasoning mix and water.
Layer on tomatoes, onions, green pepper and grated cheese; set aside.
Mix flour, milk and egg whites well, like batter.
Pour over pie mixture.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and set aside.
Mix flour, sugar, oil, eggs, baking powder, salt and juice in large bowl until smooth (thick dough).
Can add a little more orange juice if you like. Grease and flour a tube pan.
Layer dough, then apples until all are gone.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Good warm or cold.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Drain pineapple; throw juice away.
Cut pineapple into small, tiny pieces.
Combine first six ingredients in a medium bowl.
Mix well.
Cover salad and chill.
Serve salad on a bed of lettuce leaves.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Top with 1 cup crushed corn flakes, mixed with 1/8 cup melted butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: orange cream salad
directions: In bowl, add 2 cups boiling water to jello; stir until dissolved.
While still hot, put in cheese.
Beat until cheese is thoroughly mixed.
Add frozen orange juice and 3/4 cup cold water. Add fruit cocktail (drained).
Pour into mold and chill.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine oats and buttermilk in a large bowl.
Let stand one hour.
Add egg, sugar and oil, stirring well.
Combine remaining ingredients, except raisins, in a medium bowl.
Add to oats mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Stir in raisins.
Spoon into greased muffin pans, filing 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for about 18 minutes.
Yield: 18 muffins.

title: taffy candy
directions: Combine
and
cook sugar, vinegar, soda and water until it forms hard ball when dropped in cold water.
When done, add butter.
Pour
in
buttered platter to cool.
Pull until white and brittle.
Do not stir the mixture at any time.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Now dump the pineapple in the pan and spread evenly.
Dump the cherry pie filling over the pineapple and then dump the cake mix evenly over all.
Cut oleo into thin slices and completely cover the mix.
Sprinkle the nuts on last. Bake 45 minutes to one hour in a 350° oven.

title: oatmeal carmelitas
directions: Bottom Layer:
Combine the first 5 ingredients; add melted margarine and stir with a fork.
Press mixture into a 10 x 15 x 1-inch jelly roll pan (cookie sheet).
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cool whip salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook over a medium flame, stirring real often, until mixture is thickened.
Alternate layers of bananas and vanilla wafers with mixture.
Top with meringue made with 3 egg whites and 2 tablespoons sugar, whipped until stiff. Bake at 375° until brown.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour and oleo together; add chopped nuts.
Press in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix together confectioners sugar and cream cheese.
Fold in 1 cup Cool Whip and put on cooled crust.
Mix together pudding and milk.
Put on top of cream cheese mixture.
Put the rest of the Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with nuts and refrigerate.

title: black-eyed pea skillet
directions: In skillet over medium heat, brown beef, onions, peppers, then drain.
Drain can peas and add to beef mixture.
Add can tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cook 30 minutes.

title: perfect giblet gravy
directions: After turkey is removed from the roasting pan, pour drippings into a bowl, leaving most of the brown particles in the pan.
Let fat rise to top of drippings.
With a metal spoon, skim off 1/4 cup of the fat and pour it into a large saucepot.
Skim off the remaining fat and discard.
Pour 3 cups of the broth and the skimmed pan drippings into the roasting pan; place over moderate heat and stir to incorporate brown particles from bottom.
Measure liquid and, if necessary, add enough giblet broth or water to make 4 cups liquid.
Heat the turkey fat in the saucepot over moderate low heat; gradually stir in flour.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon.
Gradually stir in the 4 cups liquid.
Stir over moderate heat until thickened and smooth.
Add salt and pepper, if needed.
Add diced giblets and neck meat and simmer 5 minutes more.

title: hot dog tidbits
directions: Cook on top of stove the jelly and mustard in saucepan.
Add hot dog pieces and cook thoroughly.
Serve warm with toothpicks. Keep warm in crock-pot.

title: punch special
directions: Place sherbet in punch bowl.
Pour ginger ale over top.
Serve at once.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in 1 stick oleo.
Add this to cooked rice with Cheez Whiz.
Stir until Cheez Whiz is melted. Add cream-style corn and salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes, until thick.

title: easy shepherds pie
directions: Mix all except potatoes.
Spoon in mounds around top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecued beef supreme
directions: Pound flour into steak.
Brown in shortening in a heavy skillet or saucepan, along with onions, celery and garlic.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Cover; cook in a 350° oven or on top of range for about 1 1/2 hours, or until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon tart
directions: Whisk together flour, cornmeal, sugar and eggs.
In another bowl, mix margarine, milk, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Add lemon mixture to flour mixture.
Pour into 9-inch crust or 8 pastry shells.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top with dollop of whipped topping.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar until light and fluffy; add eggs and vanilla and beat thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 5 minutes at 425°.
Turn heat down to 325°.
Bake until middle of pie is firm, about 35 to 40 minutes.
May use 1 cup chopped nuts on top of mixture before cooking.

title: orange calendula drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse calendula blossoms.
Pull off petals and set aside.
Cream butter, sugar and orange rind until fluffy.
Add orange juice concentrate and vanilla.
Stir in eggs until blended.

Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Blend calendula petals and dry ingredients into creamed mixture. Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheets. Press almond half into each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large skillet, melt butter.
Saute squash until tender.
In a mixing bowl, beat egg slightly.
Stir in Swiss cheese, milk, salt, mustard and pepper.
Place squash in 1-quart baking dish.
Pour egg mixture over and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana madeleines
directions: Peel bananas and cut in half lengthwise.
Warm jam and brush onto bananas.
Roll in coconut.
Serve with whipped cream. This is good.

title: peanut butter and jelly bars
directions: Stir flour, sugar and baking powder together in bowl.
Cut in butter and peanut butter until crumbly.
Stir in eggs.
Press half the mixture into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread jelly over top. Crumble remaining dough over jelly.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until light brown.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Yield: 2 dozen.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: In a double boiler, melt butter.
Add lemon juice.
Add beaten eggs, stirring constantly.
Add salt and paprika.
Delicious poured over salmon loaf.

title: microwave baked beans
directions: Cook bacon and save drippings to cook onions 3 minutes on High.
Mix all ingredients except bacon.
Cook on High for 10 minutes.
Stir.
Cook on Medium for 40 minutes.
Stir after 15 minutes.
Add bacon or liquid smoke and cook 5 minutes.
Cook with a lid until you want it thicker.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Add egg that has been mixed with water, then vinegar.
Roll into 3 pie crusts.

title: hamby cookies
directions: Cook sugar, cream, butter and cocoa for 1 minute after it boils. Pour cocoa mixture over oatmeal and peanut butter. Beat well. Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: easy chili supper
directions: In large pot, brown meat. Add chopped vegetables. Saute vegetables until tender. Drain. Add tomatoes, water, tomato sauce, chili powder, salt and pepper. Bring to boil. Stir in uncooked macaroni. Reduce heat and simmer until macaroni is done, stirring occasionally.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix with mixer, then add 1 cup pecans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 1 pie.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice and cook carrots until tender-crisp.
Drain.
Add onion and bell pepper to carrots.
Heat remaining ingredients together until hot.
Pour over all vegetables.
Cool.
Store covered in refrigerator.
Wonderful as a vegetable or serve on crisp lettuce as a salad.
May be served as an appetizer with carrots cut into 1-inch rounds.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and soup together, using electric mixer.
Do not use blender.
When blended, mix in other ingredients (except shrimp).
When smooth, fold in can of shrimp (drained).
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve with potato chips.

title: charlies' corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken delight
directions: Cut up beef and place in casserole dish.
Pepper chicken and wrap 1 slice bacon around each serving.
Place on beef.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Cover and cook at 275° for 3 hours.

title: ziti with meat sauce
directions: Heat sauce so it is warm.
Prepare pasta according to directions on box.
In frying pan, add garlic (diced) and onion in a tablespoon of oil. Saute until transparent.
Add hamburg and cook until browned. Drain pasta and place in baking dish.
Mix in Ricotta and half of the Mozzarella cheese.
Mix and add half of the sauce.
Mix hamburg into remaining sauce and pour over ziti. Top with remaining Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: black cherry jello
directions: Fold all together when Jell-O is of syrup thickness.
Chill.

title: strawberry sour cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add fruits and juices.
Pour half of mixture into 10 x 15 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Does rather quickly.
Smooth sour cream over gelatin.
If desired, sprinkle nuts over sour cream.
(I put the nuts right in the jello.)
Cover remaining jello mixture.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares. Serve on lettuce bed with dash of sour cream and fresh strawberries (optional).
Serves 10 to 12.

title: veggie-plus salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients and chill until used.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat egg whites.
Beat egg yolks with milk.
Stir in butter, corn and onion.
Fold in flour mixture; fold in beaten whites.
Pour oil into deep skillet.
Heat and spoon fry mixture until brown.
Serve with honey or syrup.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer.
Pour into pie crust. Bake 35 to 40 minutes on 350°.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk together to soft ball stage.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Beat together until creamy; pour onto buttered dish.
Cut in squares when set.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake per package directions.
Pour 1/2 of the cake batter in bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: jarlsburg cheese dip
directions: Grate the Jarlsburg cheese in a medium size bowl.
Chop the red onion up and mix it together with cheese.
Add pepper.
Bind mixture together with mayonnaise.
Serve with Melba toast, sesame crackers or any other cracker preferred.

title: blueberry upside-down cake(fat free)
directions: Spray 9-inch round layer cake pan with cooking spray.
Add brown sugar, corn syrup and lemon juice; stir to combine.
Place pan in 350° oven for 3 minutes.
Remove.
Add blueberries.
Prepare white cake batter.
Carefully spoon batter over blueberries, smoothing top.
Bake 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Do not overbake.
Immediately run spatula around edge of pan and invert cake onto serving plate.
Serves 12.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Mix preserves, dressing and soup mix together in a large bowl. Coat chicken.
Rest overnight in refrigerator.
Bake on cookie sheet in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: salmon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook potatoes and onion together until tender; add butter and mixing until smooth.
Combine picked over and flaked salmon with potato mixture.
Add milk and seasonings. Line pie plate with crust and spoon in filling.
Add top crust and crimp edges.
Brush top crust with milk and sprinkle with paprika. Bake for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 minutes longer.

title: oysterettes
directions: Combine oil and seasonings; beat with whisk.
Stir in oysterettes and coat well.
Let stand overnight.

title: carleton molasses cookies
directions: Cream lard.
Add sugar.
Add applesauce with soda.
Add flour, etc., and mix.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and salt.
Add eggs, butter, milk and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Pour into pastry shell and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Yield:
One 9-inch pie.

title: date bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch square baking pan; set aside.
Combine nuts, flour and dates in small bowl; set aside. Beat eggs with electric mixer in large mixing bowl until thick and lemon-colored.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Add vanilla; blend well. Add date mixture; blend well.
Pour into prepared pan and spread evenly.
Bake 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into bars while hot.
Cool in pan or on wire rack.
Roll in or sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: barbecued beans
directions: In a one-quart casserole dish combine pork and beans, onion (I use dried chopped onions), barbecue sauce, brown sugar and mustard.
Cook on High (microwave) uncovered for 6 to 8 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes uncovered. (While cooking, I cover with sheet of wax paper.)

title: oatmeal peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the shortening. Add sugar, eggs and peanut butter.
Add dry ingredients.
It's very stiff dough.
Mold in balls.
Mash with fork.
Bake at 350°.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Stir sugar into melted chocolate mixture.
Mix in eggs and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes until toothpick inserted into brownies comes out with fudgy crumbs.
Do not overbake.
Cut into squares.
Makes 24 brownies.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Form cookies on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Will freeze.

title: cookies while you sleep
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 2 cookie sheets with foil.
Beat egg whites until stiff and foamy.
Add a pinch of salt, then gradually add sugar, almond flavor and vanilla.
Mix good.
Fold in chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
Drop by 2/3 teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Put in oven and turn oven off immediately.
Do not open for 4 hours.

title: dorothy's salad
directions: Put Cool Whip in a large bowl and sprinkle with dry Jell-O. Add cottage cheese, and then well drained pineapple.
Mix well. Chill 24 hours.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Heat the sweetened berries with the jello until the jello dissolves. Do not add water. Set aside to cool.
Beat together the milk and pudding. Stir in the sour cream and then fold in the Cool Whip.
Layer wafers, Cool Whip mixture and strawberry mixture. Repeat.
Top with Cool Whip. Chill well before serving.

title: surprise stuffed bread
directions: Brown meat and onion with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Drain.
Cut 2 inches off end of loaf; hollow out bread.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown your beef in skillet.
Line casserole bowl with chips.
Mix beans, mushroom soup, taco sauce, milk and beef in large bowl.
Pour over chips in casserole bowl. Top with layer of cheese, then layer of chips, then another layer of cheese.

title: miracle rolls
directions: Mix yeast into 1/2 cup of warm water.
Set aside.
Warm buttermilk and mix altogether.
Roll out and make rolls.
Use biscuit cutter and fold over; put butter between.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Can keep dough in refrigerator up to 3 weeks or cut out and freeze.

title: chocolate-covered cherry cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla and beat.
Gradually add dry ingredients, beating until blended.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press in center with thumb to make indentation.
Drain cherries saving liquid.
Place cherry in indentation.
Prepare frosting.

title: broccoli cheese chicken
directions: Dice chicken and brown in butter.
Pour broccoli cheese soup over chicken.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour over cooked white rice.

title: almond cheese ball
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese.
Mix with softened cream cheese, diced pimento, 3/4 cup almonds (sliced), lemon juice, salt, Worcestershire sauce, grated onion and cayenne.
Shape into a ball.
Coat
with 1/4 cup almonds.
Serve chilled.

title: crisp bran cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, cream butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Stir in flour, baking soda and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts and bran flakes until blended.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet 2 inches part.
Bake for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Finely chop tomatoes, onion, garlic, peppers, cilantro and oregano.
Mix all ingredients together and cover.
Refrigerate in glass or plastic container for up to five days.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: strawberry fruit salad
directions: Add sliced bananas to peach pie filling.
Drain pineapple chunks and add with strawberries.
Mix and chill.
Serve as a salad or topping for cake or ice cream.
You can delete strawberries and pineapple and use mandarin oranges (drained) and maraschino cherries instead.
Pineapple chunks can be put in this also, if desired.

title: overnight veggie salad
directions: Heat dressing until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over veggies. Cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Good keeper.

title: reece's peanut butter
directions: Cut cupcake papers down to 1 inch and place in a cupcake tin. Melt chocolate bar and melt with 1/2 cup peanut butter.
Melt the remaining peanut butter in a glass measuring cup with a small amount of water to liquify.
Place a tablespoon of chocolate in the papers and let set 20 minutes; then add a tablespoon peanut butter and then another tablespoon chocolate.
Let the whole thing set another 20 minutes.

title: "red hot" punch
directions: In percolator, put filter in and put red hots, cinnamon and cloves in basket.
Perk apple juice and serve.
Good!

title: broccoli-grape salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar and let set overnight in fridge.
Next day: Mix broccoli, celery and grapes (amounts as desired) with dressing.
Just before serving, add bacon and slivered almonds.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix water, cornstarch and sugar; bring to boil on top of stove. Boil hard and stir until mixture is thick. Stir in both Jell-Os. Let cool. Peel and slice 12 to 15 ripe peaches. Mix with Jell-O mixture and pour into baked crust.
Keep in refrigerator. Makes 3 large pies.

title: st. anthony's ricotta cheese puffs
directions: Mix Ricotta, eggs, granulated sugar and baking powder.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Then add flour and salt and beat until smooth.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in oblong baking dish.
Salt to taste.
Mix all ingredients together to make a sauce.
Pour sauce over chops. Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: roulades de jambon(asparagus ham rolls)
directions: Boil asparagus with lemon slices. Drain. Grate boiled eggs. Mix first 7 ingredients. Spread mixture on ham slices. Tightly roll 2 asparagus with tips, opposite each other, in ham slice. Slice in half. Arrange on lettuce and garnish. Chill well.

title: beef and vegetable stir-fry
directions: Partially freeze beef; very thinly slice across the grain into bite size strips.
Cook broccoli and carrots, covered in boiling salted water, for 2 minutes; drain.
Mix cornstarch and sugar. Stir in soy sauce and sherry; set aside.

title: fudge
directions: Cook milk with sugar (enough milk to moisten sugar).
when boiling, add vanilla.
Cook until, when you drop a drop in a cold glass of water, it makes a small soft ball.
Add peanut butter and marshmallow.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Top with 1/2 cup melted margarine and 2 cups corn flakes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tomato soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine in pot.
Blend together with onion the next 8 ingredients.
Add tomato juice, celery and fresh tomatoes; boil 1 minute.
Add milk and heat on low for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: For Crust:
Combine crumbs and butter.	Press on bottom and completely up sides of 10-inch spring-form pan.
Refrigerate 30 minutes (or chill in freezer).

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except nuts and mix with electric mixer.
Mix nuts last into batter.
Divide dough into quantities for three small pans or 2 large ones.
I use 4 (1 pound) coffee cans.
Grease pans before putting in dough.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Bread freezes well.

title: big red cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan. After cake has cooled, punch holes with fork.
Heat 1 cup Big Red, add jello to dissolve. Pour over the cake and then pour 2 cups Big Red over the cake.
Put in refrigerator to cool.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Mix in flour, soda and salt.
Add mashed bananas; mix in well.
Mix in chopped nuts.
Put in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake in moderate oven 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 2 medium loaves.

title: edna's curried peanut slaw
directions: Thoroughly blend sugar, curry, vinegar, 1/2 teaspoon salt, cream, oil, mayonnaise and 1/8 teaspoon pepper for dressing. Combine cabbage, peanuts and onion.
Toss with dressing.
Season to taste with salt and lemon pepper if desired.

title: barbecue slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well by hand.

title: spicy dip for vegetables(servings: 4)
directions: Place raisins in small bowl and cover with hot tap water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, in blender container, combine cottage cheese, vinegar, onion, chili powder, curry, salt and pepper.
Add drained, soaked raisins.
Cover and blend at high speed until smooth and creamy.
If necessary, add 1 tablespoon water in which raisins were soaked (or plain water) to make good dipping consistency.

title: party pinwheels
directions: Soften cream cheese, adding other ingredients.
Spread on tortillas in a thin layer.
Roll as tightly as possible into logs. Wrap in plastic wrap and chill at least 2 hours, overnight is best.
Slice into little pinwheels and serve.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a greased baking dish.

title: raisin sauce for ham
directions: Simmer raisins in water until soft.
Add sugar. Cook for approximately 15 minutes more. Stir in lemon juice; remove from heat. Cool slightly; pour over ham. Recipe may be doubled or tripled.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients and chill.

title: anytime quiche
directions: In a pie plate, place an unbaked pie crust.
Add ham and broccoli; arrange into bottom of crust.
Sprinkle with cheese. Whisk eggs with milk or half and half and pour over mixture.
Bake 40 minutes at 350° or until top becomes light brown.
Eat anytime.

title: snowball salad
directions: Mix well and freeze overnight.
Thaw very little before serving.

title: yeast hot cakes
directions: Mix the warm water and yeast.
Let stand while mixing other ingredients.
Mix dry ingredients, then mix with milk, eggs and yeast mixture.
Let stand overnight.
Fry on ungreased griddle.

title: green chili stew
directions: Brown meat in Crisco.
Add water.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add all other ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.
Add more salt, oregano and ground cumin to taste.

title: tutti-frutti shake
directions: Place 1 bag of Act II microwave popcorn in microwave.
Cook on High for 3 minutes and 45 seconds.
Remove.
Be careful, "it's hot."
Pour into a large bowl.
Serve with your favorite ice cold drink and turn on your favorite T.V. show and relax in your favorite recliner.
Enjoy.

title: zingy cocktail hot dogs
directions: Combine ingredients; simmer for 2 hours and serve.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Add milk and coconut.
