Combine eggs, sugar and nuts and stir into chocolate mixture; mix well. Pour into pie crust.
Bake in 400° oven about 30 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: ground beef and eggplant bake
directions: Preheat oven to slow (300°).
Cook the peeled eggplant slices in boiling salted water until tender, about five minutes.

title: tuna egg salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve on lettuce leaf with tomato wedges or serve as sandwich filling.
Yield:
4 servings. Carbohydrate 0 g, protein 14 g, fat 6 g, calories 110.
One serving = 2 meat low-fat exchange; 1 sandwich = 2 meat low-fat exchange, 2 bread starch exchange.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend cream of mushroom soup with milk and dash of pepper. In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, arrange in alternate layers: potatoes, onion and soup sauce.
Cover; bake 1 hour at 375°. Uncover; bake 15 minutes more.

title: new year's day pork and cabbage
directions: Trim off fat and cut roast into cubes.
Fry fat and drain on paper towel.
Pour off most of the oil. Brown cubed pork, which has been coated with dry seasonings.
Sprinkle any leftover seasoning on chopped onions. When pork is well browned, remove and place in a large stockpot. Add cabbage which has been cubed. Saute onions in grease that pork was browned in.
Stir constantly. When done, add to cabbage and pork.
Cover and cook until cabbage is tender. Add fried fat to your black-eyed peas.
Great while watching the bowl games.

title: thym's dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together with electric mixer.
Chill. (Better when made a day ahead.)

title: green chili chicken enchiladas(serves 6)
directions: Thaw turkey, wash and pat dry.
Remove giblets.
Rub salt in neck cavity and inside cavity.
Place turkey in large brown paper grocery bag and clip shut with clip clothes pins.
Place in roasting pan.
Bake at 325° for approximately 20 to 25 minutes per pound.
Check for doneness approximately 1/2 hour before time should be up.
The turkey usually cooks faster then when just in a pan.
I usually cook my turkey breast side down.
The turkey is not quite as pretty when done, but the breast meat is a lot moister.

title: sausage balls
directions: Bake 1-inch balls at 375° for 15 minutes on ungreased pan until golden brown.
Cool and enjoy.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: mexican stuffed peppers
directions: Cover bell peppers with water and boil about 5 minutes.
Drain and set aside.

title: cheese soup
directions: Chop all vegetables fine, boil in water until tender.
In 5 or 6-quart pan mix broth, milk, and cornstarch.
Stir with wire whisk.
Bring to a boil.
Add butter, mustard, red pepper, and cheese.
Stir until smooth.
Drain vegetables, and add to mixture. Heat until bubbling.
Season as you like.
Some use Mexican Velveeta, or add crushed red peppers.

title: eclair cake
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Turn off heat and add margarine.
When margarine has melted, remove from burner and add flour, using a wire whip to mix.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Eclair will puff up and then settle.
Mix pudding with 3 1/2 cups milk.
Beat 1 to 2 minutes and pour over shell when cooled.
Spread with Cool Whip and drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Refrigerate.

title: bess' chicken and spaghetti
directions: Heat fat.
Add onion, garlic and soup.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add flour and stir well. Add stock and cook over low heat until thick. Add chicken, tomatoes and cheese.
Pour spaghetti in buttered pans.
Pour on chicken and mix gently.
Bake 25 minutes in
a 375° oven.

title: cinnamon squares
directions: Stir the flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder and salt together. Add milk, 2 tablespoons butter, vanilla and raisins.
Pour into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Drizzle 1/2 cup butter over squares.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cut zucchini in cubes; cook it with mushrooms until tender. Add egg.
Stir in tomato juice and rest of seasonings.
Put in greased casserole.
Top with the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ham appetillas
directions: Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, green onions, olives and Tony Chachere to taste.
Spread on tortillas evenly.
Arrange 3 to 4 slices of ham over each tortilla.
Roll up tightly and wrap each individually in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Cut tortillas into 1/2-inch slices.
Yields 8 1/2 dozen.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix.
Put in pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream butter. Add sugar; cream 10 minutes.
Add one egg at a time and beat.
Add flour, milk and flavor; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: five spice casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet; drain.
Add tomatoes, soup and spices.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Stir in rice. Pour into casserole dish (9 x 13-inch works well).
Bake at 350° until hot.
Top with cheese and return to oven until cheese melts and browns a little.

title: died-and went-to-heaven chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly oil a 12-cup Bundt pan or coat it with nonstick cooking spray.
Dust the pan with flour, shaking out the excess.
In a large mixing bowl, whisk together flour, granulated sugar, cocoa powder, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add buttermilk, brown sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla.
Beat with an electric mixer on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Whisk in hot coffee until completely incorporated.
The batter will be quite thin.
Pour batter into the prepared pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until a cake tester inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool the cake in the pan on a rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and let cool completely.
Serves 16.
Nutritional analysis per serving:
222 calories, 3 grams protein, 4 grams fat, 43 grams carbohydrate, 274 mg. sodium, 27 mg. cholesterol.

title: taco chicken wings
directions: Combine flour and taco seasoning mix in paper or plastic bag. Add 2 to 3 chicken pieces; shake to coat.
Melt butter in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
Place chicken in pan, turning once to butter surfaces, then roll in corn chips and return to baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes about 32 pieces.

title: ground meat dressing
directions: Brown meat, gizzards, heart and liver.
Add seasonings and vegetables.
Cook until onions are soft.
Mix Sunrise dressing according to directions on package.
Add oysters and pecans; cook 2 or 3 minutes.
Cool before stuffing turkey.
Serves 20.

title: coconut balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Gradually add rest of ingredients.
Roll into very small balls (thumb nail size) and place on cookie sheet.
Leave space between.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar.
Bake 20 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.
Do not refrigerate.
Oven temperature: 325°.
Can do ahead.
Prep. time 15 minutes.

title: hot cheese and crab dip
directions: Cut cheeses in small pieces; combine in a saucepan with milk. Stir over low heat until cheese melts.
Stir in wine and crab; heat through.
Serve in a chafing dish.

title: creamy frosting
directions: Beat butter and Crisco until creamy.
Beat in evaporated milk until light and fluffy.

title: stickies(poor man's cookies)
directions: Make biscuit dough; roll out thin and put butter and sugar all over.
Add a little cinnamon, if you prefer.
Roll back up like a jellyroll and slice into 1-inch pieces.
Put in skillet and fry slow until brown.
Serve hot.
Real good.

title: kit kat bars
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, milk, graham crackers and brown sugar in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Place layer of Waverly crackers in bottom of 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan. Pour 1/2 mixture over crackers.
Place another layer of crackers and then rest of graham cracker mix.

title: teriyaki finger steaks
directions: Trim fat from steak and slice lengthwise into 1/2 inch strips; place in a large glass bowl.
Combine all remaining ingredients; pour over meat and toss gently.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2-3 hours or overnight.
Drain and discard marinade.
Loosely thread meat strips onto skewers.
Grill over medium-hot coals, turning often, for 7-10 minutes or until meat reaches desired doneness.
Remove from skewers and serve.	These are great with a salad & baked potato, but my kids make a meal out of them by themselves because they are so good and tender.

title: one step fruit cobbler
directions: Melt oleo, flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour into a baking dish.

title: tex mix
directions: Spread bean dip.
Mash avocados; mix with lemon juice and mayo.
Mix sour cream and taco mix.
Add tomatoes, cheese, olives and onions.
Layer the steps.
Enjoy!

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles 15 minutes, then drain. Fry ground beef, garlic, onion, and seasoning. Add tomato paste and water and simmer for 5 minutes. Beat eggs and add ricotta cheese. Use 9 x 13 pan.

title: texas millionaires
directions: In a 2-quart glass cup or mixing bowl, put unwrapped caramels, butter and water.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir and return to oven until melted.
Add pecans.
Mix well and drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets to cool.

title: chocolate dip
directions: Bring syrup and cream to boil. Take off heat and add semisweet chocolate. Beat until
chocolate has melted and is creamy. This makes an excellent fruit dip.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel apples and chop in small pieces.
Pour oil into mixing bowl.
Add sugar and eggs.
Beat with mixer.
Put dry ingredients together and add gradually to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla, nuts and apples.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix in a little of the ingredients at a time to make a stiff dough, about the consistency of pizza dough. Roll out side of dough balls in flour and knead. Roll out dough to be thin. Cut in strips. Drop in simmering broth. Thicken broth with a little flour.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar together.
Add eggs, beating in one at a time.
Add dry ingredients, sifted together.
Add prunes, cut up in pieces.
Add nuts; fold in.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: creamed carrots
directions: Boil carrots in water and salt until tender.
Mix cornstarch with milk; stir until it's mixed well.
Reduce heat to low.
Add cornstarch mixture to carrots, stirring as you pour.
When carrots begin to thicken, turn off heat and add margarine.

title: fried pies
directions: Make a dough and roll real thin. Cut out with a saucer and put a large tablespoon of cooked apples. Put water around the edge and seal it with flour; fry in hot oil until good and brown.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix sugar, coffee and water in large pot. Cool it.
Add vodka and vanilla bean. Put in dark jug or bottle. Let sit for 30 days in dark place. Makes 1 gallon.

title: macaroni and beef skillet(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Lightly brown beef in oil in skillet.
Add onion and green pepper and cook until soft.
Add tomato sauce, water, salt, pepper, Worcestershire and macaroni.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes.

title: macaroni and chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole; cover and refrigerate 5 hours or overnight. Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°
for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain grease and put into crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook approximately 1 hour or until heated through.

title: blackberry dumplings
directions: Combine berries, sugar and water in a 3 quart saucepan.
Bring to boil without stirring; add dough.
After a few minutes, reduce heat to simmer.
Cook, covered, for 15 minutes.
Serve plain with butter, milk, Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: chicken with lime butter
directions: Sprinkle chicken on both sides with salt and pepper.
Brown in hot oil about 4 minutes.
Cook 10 minutes (fork-tender).
Drain oil.
Remove chicken.
Add lime and cook on low until bubbling. Add oleo and stir until opaque and thick.
Stir in chives and dill.
Serve with rice.

title: creamed mushrooms
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Add onions and mushrooms. Cover; cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mushrooms are tender and juices released, about 6 minutes.
Blend in flour, salt and cayenne.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Makes 3 cups.

title: pot roasted veal shoulder
directions: You start with baked potatoes, scoop out the shells, mash the cooked potato with a blend of butter, seasonings and tuna.
This is a nutritious and economical main dish.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; take off bone and cut in small pieces.
Crush 1 package crackers and mix with 1 cup melted butter.
Press in bottom of casserole dish. Mix chicken soup, mushroom soup, corn, chicken and sour cream.
Mix well and pour over crushed crackers in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Crush another pack of crackers and mix with 1 cup butter and sprinkle on top.
Place back in oven and brown on broil.

title: sally's mold
directions: Add hot water to Jell-O.
Drain peaches and pineapple using juice to measure 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Use cold water to complete amount.
Let mixture stand until fully cooled.
Add sour cream and beat with eggbeater.
Add fruit. Pour into mold and put in refrigerator to set.
Garnish with chicory and sliced crabapples.

title: broccoli and cheese strata
directions: Spread one side of each slice of bread with butter.
Using doughnut cutter, cut bread slices into rings.
Set aside rings. Use scrap to line bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle 2 1/2 cups of cheese on top of bread.
Add broccoli, then chicken. Arrange rings, buttered side up, on top.
Combine next 5 ingredients in bowl.
Mix well.
Pour over top of chicken in baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, in 325° oven 50 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake 5 minutes more or until cheese melts.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into a ball.
Take ball and roll into parsley flakes.
Chill.

title: barbecue venison
directions: Put your roast in crock-pot with your chopped onion; add your water.
Add a dash of salt and pepper.
Allow to cook on low until done.
After fully cooked, place your roast in a large bowl to cool.
After it's cooled, pull you meat apart into shreds.
Put it back into crock-pot.
Add a bottle of barbecue sauce and let simmer.
Serve on buns or alone.

title: brocco-slaw
directions: Mix in a large mixing bowl brocco-slaw, cheese and bacon bits; set aside.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger and drain fat. Add cooked macaroni, corn, tomatoes and soup.
Mix well.
Transfer to shallow baking dish. Top with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: no-knead yeast rolls
directions: Pour water in large mixing bowl.
Add yeast.
Let stand a few minutes.
Stir
to	dissolve.
Add	half
the flour, the sugar, salt, shortening
and egg.	Beat until smooth, 1 1/2 to 2 minutes. Add rest
of the flour.
Scrape the sides of bowl. Cover and let rise
in
warm place until double in bulk (about 30 minutes). Grease
muffin pans and spoon in batter, filling half full.
Let rise
until double.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Cool.
Debone chicken and cut up into bite size pieces.
Mix soup and broth together.
Bring to a boil, stirring until well mixed.
Melt margarine and mix stuffing into melted margarine.
Layer one layer of stuffing, layer of chicken and half of soup mixture in casserole dish.
Repeat steps. Use remaining stuffing to put on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: blond brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter or margarine in heavy saucepan.
Add sugar.
Stir in eggs, flour and baking powder.
Add vanilla and walnuts.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 minutes.

title: rainbow dip
directions: Mix
sour
cream, mayonnaise, horseradish and seasoning all together.
On
a large round serving dish, spread mixture to cover
plate.
Start
making
a row with tomatoes to cover mixture, about 1 inch wide.
Continue with rest of diced items until the dip is completely covered with rows of items.
Place crackers
around the dish so they outline it.
Very attractive and tasty dish.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Mix eggs and salsa; stir in cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar until it looks like whipped cream.
Add eggs, one at a time, then add sifted cake flour.
Add canned milk, if the mix is thick.
Mix in cake mixer for 5 to 6 minutes, then add flavoring.
Bake at 350°.

title: green chili-rice casserole
directions: Mix rice, sour cream, milk and butter.
Remove seed and beans from chilies.
Layer the rice mixture, cheese and chilies alternately in a casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven until mixture bubbles, approximately 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: double chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt in a small bowl. Melt 1 cup morsels in a small, heavy-duty saucepan over low heat; stir until smooth. Beat granulated sugar, 1/3 cup peanut butter, butter and vanilla extract in large mixer bowl until creamy. Beat in melted chocolate. Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Gradually beat in cocoa mixture. Stir in remaining morsels. Cover; refrigerate just until firm.

title: roast potato wedges
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Cut lengthwise into 6 wedges.
Place in bowl. Cover with cold water.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Drain.
Pat potato wedges dry with paper towels.
Toss wedges with oil.
Place skin side down on baking sheet coated with vegetable cooking spray. Sprinkle with garlic salt, dill weed and pepper.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until wedges are tender and brown.

title: dorothy kinder's spaghetti salad
directions: Chop peppers and onions together.
Cook spaghetti according to directions.
Drain and rinse and drain again.
Add to the onions and peppers.
Add the salad seasoning.
Pour the salad dressing over and toss well.
Refrigerate, preferably overnight.
Stir well before serving.
Will keep a long time in the refrigerator, if it lasts that long.

title: sausage mostaccioli bake
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain.
In skillet, cook sausage, onion, green pepper and garlic until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, water, oregano and pepper into mixture in skillet.
Stir in cooked pasta.
Spoon half of the mostaccioli mix into a 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with half the cheese.
Top with remaining mostaccioli mix.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake about 5 minutes more or until the cheese melts.
Makes 8 servings.

title: 7 layer surprise
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with melted butter.
Spread in bottom of pan.
Mix 4x sugar and 1 stick butter.
Add beaten egg whites. Spread on crumb mixture.
Add layer of bananas and layer of pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip and layer of chopped nuts.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil and cook first 6 ingredients until chicken is white and mushrooms are tender.
Add vegetables; cook until tender.
Serve over rice.

title: stuffed acorn squash for the holidays
directions: Cut squash in half and remove seeds.
Place cut sides down in a shallow baking dish.
Add water to about 1 inch depth.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn cut side up and sprinkle with salt. Combine remaining ingredients and spoon into squash halves.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until squash is tender.
Serves 4.

title: aunt dot's german apple cake
directions: Sift together first 7 ingredients.
Add next 2 ingredients. Mix well and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: sauerkraut cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and sauerkraut.
Set aside.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and cocoa.
To the creamed mixture, add milk, water and dry ingredients.
Bake in a sheet pan at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Use any caramel or chocolate frosting. Sprinkle coconut over the top.

title: peach or apricot salad
directions: Bring liquid from fruit to boil and mix into Jello.
Beat cream cheese and cottage cheese into mixture.
Beat in fruit.
Let set until fairly firm; mix in Cool Whip.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Peel and slice the potatoes.
Coat the potato slices with flour, salt and pepper.
Place in a lightly oiled 2-quart baking dish.
Pour the milk over the top; cover and bake for 30 to 40 minutes, until the potatoes are tender.
Yield: 2 servings.
One serving:
91 calories, 3 g protein, 18g carbohydrates, 2g fat, 86 mg sodium.
One serving:
1 starch/bread.

title: old fashion chocolate fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, add milk.
Cook on medium heat until thick enough to form ball in cup of cold water when dropped. Add vanilla and butter; beat with mixer a few minutes then add pecans.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch butter dish.

title: sour cream rhubarb squares
directions: Crumble sugar, nuts, melted oleo and cinnamon.
Set aside for topping.
Cream brown sugar, shortening and egg.
Add flour, soda and salt alternately with sour cream.
Stir in rhubarb.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle on topping.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.
Good with whipped topping.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar.
Add vanilla, eggs and milk. Beat on medium speed of mixer.
Combine with dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Stir in zucchini and nuts.
Spoon batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with reserved chocolate chips. Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 35 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched.

title: date-nut balls
directions: Melt butter and sugar in saucepan.
Stir in dates and cook 5 to 10 minutes (when dates look like they melt).
Stir in pecans and Rice Krispies.
Allow to cool slightly.
Roll into balls and then roll into powdered sugar.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift together cocoa, flour, salt and baking powder.
Pour into the creamed mixture.
Beat 2 minutes on high speed.
Bake in tube pan 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.

title: hot caramel over apples
directions: Unwrap individual caramels and place in microwave bowl with cream cheese.
Melt in microwave for approximately 1 1/2 to 2 minutes at a time and stir afterwards.
Repeat melting process until creamy.
Then pour over cold apple wedges.
Let caramel cool a little bit and indulge.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Place chicken in a single layer in a shallow baking dish.
Top each breast with a slice of cheese.
Mix soup with water and pour over chicken and cheese.
Toss stuffing mix and butter until stuffing mix has been coated.
Sprinkle over chicken.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook meat; stir in onion, tomatoes, spinach, salt and pepper. Combine the 2 soups, sour cream, milk and garlic powder in bowl. Mix well.
Dip tortillas in melted butter or I prefer to spread them lightly with soft margarine and arrange on bottom and around sides of a large, shallow pan or casserole.
Spoon on meat mixture, taking care not to disarrange the tortillas.
Scatter chopped chilies on top, then all but half of the cheese, next the remaining tortillas, spread with margarine and finally the sauce. Smooth sauce on top.
Cover with Saran Wrap or foil and refrigerate overnight.
Before cooking, sprinkle with rest of cheese and bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes or until bubbling hot.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: corned beef cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and form into a ball.
Cover with chopped walnuts; chill.
Serve with Triscuit crackers.

title: toffee
directions: Combine butter and sugar in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat. Stir constantly until brown (tan), about 10 minutes.
Spread nuts on cookie sheet.
Spread mixture over nuts.
Place chocolate bar on top while hot.
When melted, spread evenly.
Refrigerate until set (overnight).
Break into pieces.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook potatoes, onions, carrots, and celery for 2 hours.
Mix flour to make thick with milk.
Add to potatoes and other ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Stir often.
Add clams last and simmer a short while before eating.
Sprinkle with chives if desired.

title: magic cookie bars(serves 12)
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in preheated oven (350°). Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on top of melted butter, evenly. Scatter chopped nuts evenly over crumbs.
Scatter chocolate morsels or butterscotch chips over nuts.
Sprinkle coconut evenly over morsels.
Next, pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over coconut.
Bake at 350° (moderate oven) for 25 minutes or until lightly browned on top.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Cut into bars. Makes about 2 dozen 1 1/2 x 3-inch bars.
Chocolate used is semi-sweet.

title: oreo delight
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch pan or a little larger.
Spread 1 tube of Oreo crumbs in pan.
Cover with softened vanilla ice cream.
Then pour caramel and fudge sauce over the ice cream and then spread Cool Whip over all.
Spread the second tube of Oreo crumbs on top and freeze.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together with spoon and put in greased cake pans.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pop-a-pizza
directions: Put muffins on plates.
Spread with 1 or 2 tablespoons of pizza sauce over muffins.
Put on cut up meats.
Sprinkle cheese over everything.
Microwave each plate on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Decorate with remaining ingredients.
Get cup of something to drink and open your mouth and put in pizza; chew. Makes 4 servings.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Simmer hamburg and onion over low-medium heat until browned. Add the mango (green pepper), salt, pepper, chili sauce, chili powder and tomato puree.
Rinse tomato puree can with 1/2 can of water; add to mixture.

title: green rice
directions: Saute onion and celery in melted oleo.
Then add broccoli and water chestnuts.
Mix soup, cheese whiz and rice together and then add to other ingredients.
Mix well. Put into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: apple raisin snack cake
directions: Blend in salad dressing, cake mix and eggs at low speed with mixer until moistened.
Blend in butter and rum extract; beat for 3 minutes.
Add apples and raisins.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes in a 350° preheated oven.

title: french fries dip
directions: Mix all together with fork.
Good with French fries, chicken fingers and hamburgers.

title: thick dough lemon pie
directions: Roll out and use for crusts and strips for the top.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare apples and place in an 8 x 8-inch pan or equivalent.
To 1/4 cup of the water, add salt and cinnamon.
Stir.
Pour over the apples.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease an 8 x 10-inch pan with butter. Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Pour the cherry pie filling into the pan.
Spread the drained pineapple over the pie filling. Sprinkle dry cake mix over pineapple.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Mix pineapple juice and butter together and pour evenly over the top. Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Great served with ice cream or by itself.

title: easy one-step lasagne
directions: Combine water with spaghetti sauce in a bowl.
Cover the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with 1 1/2 cups of the sauce.

title: pound cake filled with fresh raspberries
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Cream together margarine and sugar with an electric mixer until light.
Mix in lemon zest.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix until light and fluffy.
Mix in vanilla. Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients to the batter alternately with sour cream.
Mix just to combine.
Spread half of the batter in pan.
Cover with raspberries; top with remaining batter, smoothing out top.
Bake until toothpick comes out clean, approximately 1 hour.
Cool.
Dust top with powdered sugar.

title: steak and potato casserole
directions: Cut meat into 8 serving pieces, trimming fat and bone.
On wooden board or waxed paper, using meat mallet or edge of saucer, pound mixture of flour, salt and pepper into meat.
In large, heavy skillet over medium heat, in hot oil, brown meat well on both sides.
Arrange meat in 3-quart casserole; place carrots and potato slices on top.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix and cover with 3 1/2 cups water.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven, covered, two hours or until meat is fork-tender.
Skim off any excess fat.
If you like, thicken gravy with 2 tablespoons flour mixed with cold water and stirred into casserole; return oven for a few minutes.
Sprinkle parsley on top.
Yields 8 servings.

title: perfect corn pudding
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Mix the sugar, cornstarch, salt, dry mustard and onion and add to the corn mixture.
Stir in the milk and butter or margarine.
Pour all into a greased 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, stirring once during baking.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, refrigerate, serve chilled.
For presentation, you can boil another egg, slice and place on top.

title: lauren's chocolate filled cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except Kisses.
Take 2 tablespoons of mixture and wrap around 1 Hershey's Kiss.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cool on wire rack. Frost and decorate as you like.

title: sweet pickled beans
directions: Boil fresh snipped beans in salt water until tender for 30 minutes; drain.
Add vinegar and sugar (keep repeating to cover beans).
Heat thoroughly and can and seal in glass jars.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Boil carrots in salted water until tender.
Drain and cool. Alternate layers of carrots, onion rings and pepper rings in a dish.
Combine remaining ingredients adding a little more salt. Beat until well blended.
Pour over vegetables.
Will keep in refrigerator at least a week.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Cream butter with sugars in a large bowl.
Add egg and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and baking soda in a small bowl; stir into creamed mixture with oats, chips, raisins and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls 2 inches apart onto cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove to wire racks to cool.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs until foamy.
Stir flour, salt and baking powder, then mix together.
Roll 1/2-inch thick. Cut in shapes.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: red rice jambalaya
directions: Coat a Dutch oven with cooking spray.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add chicken, meat side down.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Turn chicken and add ham.
Cover and cook 15 minutes. Remove chicken from Dutch oven and let cool.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well and bake in moderate oven about 6 to 8 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat sugar and oil.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift flour, cinnamon, salt and soda together and add to egg mixture.
Mix well.
Fold in carrots and nuts.
Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 300°.

title: pancit
directions: Fry chicken, carrots, onion, cabbage and garlic in oil until the vegetables are tender, but crisp.
Season with pepper and soy sauce to taste.
Add the shrimp and heat until ready to serve. Toss the chicken, vegetables and spaghetti together.
Serve with lemon wedges and soy sauce.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, milk, vanilla and salt.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in uncovered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can be easily doubled.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all together and bake at 450° for 45 minutes.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Cream together butter, Eagle Brand milk, powdered sugar and pecans. Chill until firm.
Form into balls about size of pecan. Chill again.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in a double boiler. Dip balls into chocolate and let set until firm. Store in airtight container.

title: hearty fruit soup
directions: Drain fruits and reserve 1 1/2 cups of juices.
Cut fruit in chunks.
Combine all ingredients (except fruit) and bring to boil in the reserved juice, then simmer for 10 minutes.
Add fruits. Serve hot or cold.

title: beef burgundy
directions: In ovenproof Dutch oven, brown beef on stovetop in 1/4 cup oil.
After browning on all sides, add wine, water, broth, thyme and garlic. Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 2 hours, stirring occasionally. Add onions and carrots.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove meat and vegetables.

title: pink pineapple salad
directions: Heat pineapple in water until hot; add jello and stir until dissolved. Combine cream cheese and Cool Whip and fold into jello mixture. Add nuts. Let set.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in large boiler. Bring to a rolling boil and boil 3 minutes. Remove from heat; add peanut butter and oatmeal. Mix well. Add coconut and nuts if wanted. Spoon on wax paper to cool. Makes a lot of cookies.

title: fettucine rene
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water till tender.
Rinse and drain thoroughly.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions; cool.
In a large bowl, crumble 1/2 cake.
Top with 1/2 of strawberries, 1/2 nuts and 1/2 Cool Whip in layers.
Continue from beginning until all ingredients are gone.
Garnish with a few whole strawberries.

title: breakfast tofu "omelet"(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Place first 8 ingredients in blender bowl and blend for 3 minutes.
Pour into bowl.
Mix in flour, pepper and onion.
Spray baking sheet with Pam and drop mixture by 1/4 cup measure onto baking sheet.
Bake at 400° about 10 to 15 minutes, turn once halfway through baking time.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: Layer as follows in 2-quart greased casserole:

title: double batch christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla in large mixing bowl; beat well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Spoon onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes approximately.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and granulated sugar.
Blend in one egg at a time.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt to chocolate mixture.
Chill overnight.

title: rice krispy treat
directions: Melt
margarine in 3 quart saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows; stir until melted and well blended.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal until well coated; press into greased 13 x 9-inch
baking
pan.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: spanakopeta
directions: You will need a cooking tray.

title: sticky oven-fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place frozen chicken in a single layer in a shallow baking dish for 20 minutes.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Spoon over chicken pieces.
Continue baking for 15 to 20 minutes more.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add soup, Cheez Whiz and broccoli. Cook until bubbly.
Add cooked rice and simmer until broccoli is tender.

title: best rum cake ever
directions: Before ya start, sample the rum to check for quality.
Good, isn't it?
Now go ahead.
Select a large mixing bowl, measuring cup, etc.
Check the rum again.
It must be just right.
To be sure rum is of the highest quality, pour one level cup of rum into a glass and drink it as fast as you can.
Repeat.
With electric mixer, beat 1cup of butter in a large fluffy bowl.
Add 1 seaspoon of thougar and beat again.
Meanwile, make sure the rum is of the finest quality.
Try another cup.
Open second quart if necessary. Add large leggs, 2 cups fried druit and beat till high.
If druit get stuck in beaters, just pry it loose with a drewscriver.
Sample the rum again, checking for tonscisticity.
Next, sift 3 cups of pepper or salt (it really doesen't matter).
Sample the rum again. sift 1/2 pint lemon juice, fold in chopped butter and strined muts. Add 1 babblespoon of brown thugar, or what- ever color you can find.
Wix mel.
Grease oven and turn cake pan to 350.
Pour the whole mess into the cover, and ake.
Check the rum again and bo to ged.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil sugar and water; cool.
Whip bananas with mixer or blender.
Add all ingredients except ginger ale to water.
Add ginger ale when serving.
Mixture (except ginger ale) may be frozen.
Makes approximately 1 1/2 to 2 gallons.

title: frosting
directions: In large bowl, beat first 3 ingredients on low speed.
Add enough coffee to moisten.
Spread between layers.
Blend unsalted roasted peanuts into frosting to use on top layer.
Makes enough for 3 layers.
Great on devil's food cake.

title: buckwheat cakes
directions: Dissolve yeast and molasses in lukewarm water.
Scald milk. Add salt and cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast.
Add buckwheat flour and white flour gradually.
Beat until smooth.
Cover and let rise in a warm place.
Cook as pancakes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until done, but firm.
Drain and cool.
Layer carrots, onion and green pepper in large container.
Heat all the remaining ingredients until mixed well, then cool.

title: fruit smoothie
directions: If using frozen fruit, partially thaw the fruit until it separates. Combine all of the ingredients together in a blender or food processor. (Note: If using a food processor, crush the ice before adding to the processor.) Process until smooth and frothy. Serve immediately.

title: never fail cheese ball
directions: Cut cheese in cubes and allow to soften.
Knead together and add other ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread pecans on waxed paper.
Make mixture into a ball and roll over pecans until ball is completely covered.
Wrap in foil and chill at least 2 hours. Serve with crackers, vegetables, etc.

title: mexican stew
directions: Brown meat in large pot with chopped garlic and onion. Cook a couple of hours until meat is tender. You can add salt and pepper at this time. Then add other ingredients and cook until potatoes are done. Serve over corn bread.

title: richman taco dip
directions: Mix beans, relish, taco seasoning and sour cream in a serving bowl.
Top with shredded cheese, shredded lettuce and tomato chunks, if desired.
Serve with chips.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In a large bowl, sift together the flour, spices, soda and salt.
In another large bowl, mix the sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Mix together with dry ingredients.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Makes 3 large loaves.

title: fresh apple dessert
directions: Mix cake mix, butter, brown sugar and cinnamon until crumbly. Reserve 2/3 cup of the mixture.
Press remaining mixture in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Arrange apple slices on mixture in pan.
Beat sour cream and eggs until blended.
Spread over apples.
Sprinkle reserved mixture on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° until topping is brown.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate cherry cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Makes 2 dozen.
Cook 7 to 10 minutes.
Mix flour, cocoa, salt, powder and soda in small bowl.
In separate bowl, beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla and beat well; gradually add dry mixture and mix well (set aside).
In pan over low heat, melt together juice from the maraschino cherries, chocolate chips and the Borden's milk, then remove from heat after mixture thickens.
Make 1/2-inch balls out of cookie mixture; place on cookie sheets.
Press thumb in the middle of each cookie and put 1 cherry in center, then pour 1/1/2 teaspoons of chocolate mixture over cherry and cook for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter; add cocoa and mix.
Add sugar and mix.
Add flour, vanilla and then mix eggs thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken dallas
directions: In a large shallow baking pan, melt butter over medium heat. Add onion, celery, green pepper and garlic; stir to blend well. Arrange chicken parts on top of vegetables.
Combine brown sugar, sherry and orange juice, Worcestershire, mustard, salt, catsup and vinegar.
Mix well and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 350°
oven, uncovered, for about 1 1/2 hours. Remove chicken and add flour to remaining ingredients and stir over medium heat to thicken.
Pour over chicken and enjoy.

title: brown cow colada
directions: Blend and pour into a tall glass.
Makes 1 serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix cheese, soup, rice, onion, and butter together real well. Fold in the broccoli. Pour into loaf pan and spread crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle some dressing mix and cheese on top.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: liver knieps
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, pepper, onions, beaten egg and grated liver.
Add enough beef stock to make a stiff dough.

title: tammy's meatballs
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and form into meatballs, using rounded teaspoon.
Brown lightly in 1 tablespoon vegetable oil. Cover and cook on low heat for 5 minutes.
Drain fat.
Mix together chili sauce and jelly.
Pour over meatballs.
Heat, stirring until jelly is melted.
Simmer 10 to 12 minutes until sauce thickens; baste occasionally.
Great for parties.
Keep warm by using crock-pot.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan layer lettuce, tomato, onion and peas. Spread mayonnaise over top.
Sprinkle sugar over mayonnaise.
Top with cheese and bacon bits.
Refrigerate for at least 6 to 8 hours.
Serve.

title: fish loaf
directions: Beat milk and eggs together and pour over crumbs.
When soft, mix with meat and work together well.
Add spices, onion and Worcestershire sauce.

title: hot bacon potato salad
directions: Fry bacon crisp; pour off all fat but 1/4 cup.
Add onion; cook until lightly browned, stirring occasionally.
Stir in salt, sugar, flour, mustard, celery seed and vinegar.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add potatoes and celery; mix lightly.
Heat gently.
Add eggs, tomatoes,
spinach leaves and crumbled bacon.
Let stand over low heat until warmed through. Serves 4 to 6.
Don't forget 1/4 cup vinegar.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Toss together the potatoes, cheese, salad dressing, onions and salt and pepper. Turn into buttered dish. Top with bacon or Bac*Os and stuffed olives. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: raspberry coconut cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix as directed for 2 round cake layers, adding 2/3 cup of the coconut to batter.
Mix jam and 1 cup of the coconut in small bowl.
Spread between cake layers.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except noodles. Add noodles last. Put in a 9 x 13 greased pan. Let stand 1 hour before baking.

title: chocolate-peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar and margarine until smooth and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Next, melt chocolate in double boiler and then pour over peanut butter mixture.
Cool at least 1 hour.
Cut into squares.

title: chewy bars
directions: Melt margarine; remove from heat.
Fold in sugar and vanilla. Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour one cup at a time.
Add nuts. Spray 11 x 17-inch jelly roll pan with Pam.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Check at 25 minutes.
If it cooks too long, it gets too hard.
Should be chewy.

title: celery salad
directions: Bring pineapple and Jell-O to boil in 1 cup water. Cream the cream cheese. When pineapple and Jell-O cool, pour into cream cheese and mix. Fold in Cool Whip and nuts. Let set in refrigerator until set.

title: beef stew
directions: Sprinkle meat on all sides with seasoned salt. Heat oil and 2 tablespoons butter or margarine in a large skillet. Add meat and brown well on all sides. Add garlic, onion and celery to fat in skillet; cook about 3 minutes. Blend in the flour, then stir in next 8 ingredients. Cover and bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 2 1/2 hours. Remove fat.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: For crust, stir together flour and the 3 tbsp. brown sugar in a bowl. Cut in the 1/2 cup butter. Pat mixture into an ungreased 11x7x1-1/2 inch baking pan. Bake at 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: 1 minute peanut butter cookies
directions: Boil sugar and syrup for one minute.
Add peanut butter and stir until it melts.
Add Special K cereal and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: monkey bread
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and cinnamon to butter.
Dip biscuits in butter mixture and layer in greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: venison roast
directions: Place roast in a roaster pan with all ingredients, adding flour and wine last.
Mix thoroughly.
Cook at 350° until done.

title: rotel cheese dip
directions: Cook sausage until crumbly and brown; drain.
Melt cheese in crock-pot.
Add tomatoes and sausage, stirring well.
Lower heat. Serve with chips.

title: snickerdoodle cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter and eggs until creamy.
Add flour, baking powder, milk and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes until well mixed.

title: malted milk balls butter cookies
directions: To crush the malted milk balls, place in a plastic bag and beat with the rolling pin.

title: hamburger pancakes
directions: Combine meat, onion, salt and baking powder.
Stir in egg yolks.
Fold in egg whites.
Drop like pancakes onto hot griddle. Turn once.
Serve alone or with tomato sauce.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix well.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Break cauliflower into small pieces.
Combine ingredients, toss lightly and chill well, at least 5 hours.
Serves 8.

title: jambalaya
directions: Note:
May substitute ham or sausage for the shrimp.

title: apple pineapple slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Drain juice from sweet potatoes and mash.
Add all ingredients.
Pour in souffle dish.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and save 2 cups of broth.
Skin and debone.
Place in bottom of large casserole dish.
Combine 1 cup of broth and soups.
Pour over chicken.
In a separate bowl, mix melted butter, 1 cup broth and stuffing mix.
Spoon into pan.
Cook about 30 minutes at 400°.

title: fruit dressing
directions: Beat all ingredients together until fluffy; refrigerate. Serve over fruit or use as a fruit dip.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Sift together sugar, flour and corn meal.
Add eggs.
Beat until thick and ivory color.
Add lemon juice and butter.
Beat enough to mix.
Add milk and beat until it mixes.
Pour into an unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: wayne's famous rice pilaf
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in margarine.
Pour all ingredients together in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Spray dish with Pam first. Place in 350° oven, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: heartland loaves
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; cool to 105° to 115°.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; let stand 5 minutes. Stir yeast mixture and oil into cornmeal mixture.
Add wheat and rye flours, stirring well.
Gradually add enough all-purpose flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic (about 8 minutes).
Place in a well-greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, 1 hour, or until doubled in bulk.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Soften yeast in large bowl.
Add salt and sugar.
Mix in flour and knead to make soft dough.
Cut into small pieces and roll into "pencils" & twist into pretzels.
Place on cookie sheet. Brush on egg and sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix together and press into a cookie sheet.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 6 hours.
Cut into squares.
Roll in flour and fry each square in skillet until browned.
Place browned meat in roaster.
Mix soup and water (soup cans) until blended; pour over meat in roaster.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: dirty rice
directions: Cook rice and set aside.
Brown hamburger, onion, bell pepper and celery in large pot until done.
Drain excess grease.
Add cooked rice and mix thoroughly.
Let stand about 30 minutes for flavors to blend.
Serve with salad or vegetables.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti about 10 minutes.
Drain and rinse.
Brown meat, and add salt, pepper, mustard and one egg.
Cook a few minutes longer until meat tends to hold together.
Form into a ball and place in center of greased 2 quart dish.
Combine soup, peas, egg and spaghetti.
Mix well.
Arrange in circle around meat.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn out.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients and add to scalded milk.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with egg white meringue and brown in 350° oven for 12 minutes or until browned evenly.

title: individual pizzas
directions: Split, toast and butter the muffins.
Saute thinly diced onions with the ground chuck, then add the seasonings.
Spoon the mixture onto the muffins.
Cover generously with Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° to the desired degree of doneness.
These can be frozen and heated in their frozen state.
Serves 16.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift in dry ingredients; add oatmeal, corn flakes, pecans, raisins, coconut and candied cherries.
Work with hands until ingredients are well mixed.
Form into small balls about the size of walnut. Press slightly.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Looks more colorful if fruit is left in large chunks.
Makes 100 medium sized cookies.

title: oriental style green beans
directions: String and snap beans into 1-inch lengths; wash.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Retain drippings.
Cover beans with water.
Add salt and onion powder with 4 tablespoons of bacon grease.
Simmer 1 or 1 1/2 hours.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Reserve 1/2 cup chow mein noodles.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into ungreased pan or casserole dish.
Sprinkle reserved chow mein noodles over top.
Bake 30 minutes (uncovered) in a 350° oven. Yields 8 to 12 servings.

title: sour mustard pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers. Sterilize jars.
Pack cucumbers in jars and pour the
brine
over
them.
Let
set.
Sealing
is
not necessary.	Any brine left over may be kept in jars until more cukes are gathered.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour a 9 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Beat the butter in bowl with an electric mixer until soft. Gradually add sugar; continue beating at high speed until very light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each. When thoroughly blended, add flour, 1 cup at a time; beat at low speed until blended.
Stir in milk, vanilla extract and lemon extract.
Transfer batter to loaf pan; bake until golden brown, about 1 1/2 hours.
Cool; remove from pan.

title: grasshopper cheesecake bars
directions: Place cream cheese in a small mixer bowl; let stand at room temperature about 30 minutes or until softened. Stir together flour, 1/3 cup sugar and cocoa. Cut in butter until mixture resembles fine crumbs. Set aside 1 cup of the mixture for topping. Press remaining mixture onto the bottom of an ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: golden cream soup
directions: Combine potatoes, water, celery, carrots, onion, parsley, salt, pepper and chicken bouillon cube.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Gradually add milk to flour, stirring until well blended. Gradually add flour mixture to hot vegetables, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Makes 4 1/4 cup servings.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix marshmallows with drained pineapple and let set at room temperature 3 to 4 hours.
Combine flour, sugar, pineapple liquid, egg and vinegar and saucepan.
Cook on low until thick.
Cool. Fold in whipped topping and apples.
Combine marshmallow mixture with apple mixture in large bowl.
Top with peanuts.
Yields 10 servings.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate until set.

title: date balls
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, salt and dates.
Cook on low heat until melted
and
brown in color.
Remove from heat and cool slightly. Add Rice Krispies and pecans.
Mix well.
Wet hands in
water, roll into balls.
Roll in coconut and place on wax paper.

title: fast fixin fruit and cake
directions: Completely coat 13x9 pan with oil, add cake mix, eggs, water, stir with fork until mixed.
Add pie filling and stir.
Bake at 350° for 34-45 minutes.

title: brown sugar pies(makes 2 pies)
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks well.
Add sugar.
Beat well.
Add cream, salt and vanilla, then add melted butter.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Fold egg whites in last.
Pour into two unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then turn oven to 350° for about 30 minutes or until done (until pie is firm).

title: taku smokeries famous pat
directions: Remove skin
and finely shred the smoked salmon.
Add softened cream cheese in small chunks.
Process all ingredients in food processor until blended well.
Enjoy with crackers, bagels or bread.
This was served on Auk Nu and Allen Marine Tours in Juneau,
Alaska.

title: "cheese things"
directions: Blend cheese and butter with seasonings until smooth and slowly work in the flour until it's all smooth.
Form into a roll 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Wrap in wax paper and chill overnight or longer.
At serving time, slice rolls 1/2-inch thick and set on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 6 minutes at 400° and serve direct from the oven.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix all together.
Serve with your favorite fruits or spread on gingersnaps.

title: chicken pie
directions: Combine soup, milk, pepper, cooked vegetables and cooked chicken together.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Cut uncooked biscuits in quarters.
Top chicken mixture with biscuits.
Bake again until biscuits are golden (about 15 minutes).

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, brown sugar, egg yolk and vanilla. Gradually add flour and salt to mixture.
Chill dough a little. Roll in 1-inch balls.
Dip in slightly beaten egg white and roll in finely chopped nuts or coconut.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven. Press thumb gently on center of each cookie.
Return to oven and bake 8 minutes more.
When cool, fill center with tinted powdered sugar icing.
Bake at 375°.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Skin, core and slice the 5 apples.
Then in a semi-large plastic bag, mix the apples and the cinnamon by shaking the bag vigorously until the apples are thoroughly covered in cinnamon.
Mix the first six ingredients, then add oil, eggs and orange juice (batter should be thick).
Next, layer the batter like this:
batter on bottom, apples, batter, apples, etc., until all the apples are used up. Finish up with the batter on top.
When the cake rises, put a little walnuts and sugar on top.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes. Enjoy!

title: halupsies
directions: Combine cooked rice, hamburger, onion, salt and pepper.
Place cabbage in very hot water to loosen leaves.
Fill leaves with rice-hamburger mixture.
Fold shut.
Place in roaster, folded side down.
Cover with desired tomato mixture.
Bake in a 325° oven about 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: chicken wings
directions: In a bowl mix all ingredients except chicken wings thoroughly. Cut off tip of chicken wings; cut wings in two parts.
Add to sauce the chicken wings and marinate overnight.
On a foil-covered cookie sheet, place wings and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: "thibs" chicken and dumplings
directions: Brown seasoned, cut up hen in 1/2 cup cooking oil or fat from hen.
Add little water at a time until meat is tender, about 2 hours.
Add more water to make gravy.
After the meat is tender, take meat out of pot.
Add onion to pot with dumplings and cook in gravy.
Add a little water while cooking dumplings.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Mix the flour with the sugar in a saucepan with juice drained from pineapple, the beaten egg and the butter.
Cook until thick. Cool about 15 minutes.
Stir into mixture of remaining ingredients.
Serve at room temperature or chilled.

title: lemon curd
directions: Mix together sugar and cornstarch.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook over hot water in double boiler until thickened.

title: chocolate syrup for ice cream topping or chocolate milk
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and salt in a pan.
Add hot water gradually to make a paste.
Mix thoroughly.
Add remaining hot water.
Place on stove, stirring constantly until mixture boils; boil 3 minutes. Remove from heat and add vanilla.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Place cookie dough briefly in the freezer to firmly chill it. Slice into 1/8-inch slices.
Line a 14-inch pizza pan with slices overlapping slightly.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes. Cool crust.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, vanilla, butter and sugar until dough is stiff (or your arm is).
Shape into balls (small, approximately 1 teaspoon).
Put on wax paper and refrigerate about 20 minutes. Melt chips in pan.
Dip into chocolate using toothpick and put back on wax paper.
Refrigerate until chocolate is set.
Can be frozen.
Keep in tight container.

title: nashville house apple butter
directions: Mix the ingredients in a large pan.
Bake for 8 to 9 hours. Stir every 30 minutes.
Makes 18 pints.

title: country mushroom soup
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, melt butter; stir in flour until smooth. Gradually stir in broth until smooth. Add salt, pepper and bay leaves. Simmer uncovered for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: holy cow cake
directions: Make cake as directed and bake.
As soon as you take out of oven, poke holes all over it.
Pour the Eagle Brand milk over it. Let it cool completely.
You can even let it set overnight.
Add the caramel topping over the cake.
Put the Cool Whip over it. Crush up the candy bars and sprinkle over the top of the cake. Keep refrigerated.

title: one-egg cake
directions: Heat oven to 350° (moderate).
Grease and flour two layer pans, 8 x 1 1/2-inches or a square pan, 8 x 8 x 1 3/4-inches. Measure flour by dip-level-pour method or by sifting.
Blend flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add shortening, 2/3 of milk and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed on mixer or 300 vigorous strokes by hand.
Scrape sides and bottom of bowl constantly.
Add rest of milk and egg.
Beat 2 more minutes, scraping bowl frequently.
Pour into pan(s).
Bake layers about 30 minutes, square 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with your favorite icing.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a casserole dish.
Add the blackberries. Mix the flour, sugar, milk and lemon juice in a bowl and pour over berries.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until brown.
Serve with cream or ice cream.

title: almond cookies
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
In a large bowl beat butter, sugar, egg and almond extract with a wooden spoon or electric mixer until pale and fluffy.
Stir in flour mixture to make a smooth dough.
Refrigerate 1 hour or longer (cover if overnight).
Heat oven to 350°.
Form dough into balls, using a rounded tablespoonful for each, and place 2 inches apart on greased baking sheets.
Paint cookies with egg yolk mixture and press an almond into the center of each.
Bake 15 minutes, or until edges are tinged with brown.
Remove from oven and transfer cookies to a wire rack to cool.
Makes about 24 cookies.
Cost:

title: seven layer salad
directions: Place a layer of each ingredient in the order given.
Put in a large bowl.
Place tight fitting lid over bowl and let sit as is in refrigerator overnight.
Do not mix salad until ready to serve.

title: nanny's dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Pack in quart jars.
Fill with water until cucumbers are covered.
Cap and tighten jars.
Hot water bath for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water; add frozen berries and lemon juice.
Stir until berries thaw.
Chill until almost set.
Blend cheese, powdered sugar, vanilla and salt.
Fold in a small amount of whipped cream, then fold in remainder.
Spread on bottom of pastry shell.
Cover with red mixture.
Chill until set.

title: quick ice cream dessert
directions: Spread half of the Cool Whip onto the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange ice cream sandwiches evenly on top of the Cool Whip, then spread the remaining Cool Whip on top of the ice cream sandwiches and freeze.
Before serving, shave the candy bar and sprinkle the shavings on top of the dessert.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes 1/4-inch thick.
Place on large platter and sprinkle well with lemon pepper.
Let stand 45 minutes at room temperature.
Drain off juice.
Roll tomatoes in flour and corn meal mixture.
Fry in iron skillet with about 1/4-inch grease at medium high heat until golden brown.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Put melted butter in bottom
of iron skillet.
Sprinkle brown sugar onto butter and then
lay
pineapple
slices
onto brown sugar.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Set aside.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain.
Put in a large pan and add beans, tomatoes, garlic powder, salt, pepper, chopped onion and chopped pepper.
Heat to boil, then simmer.

title: waffle and pancake batter
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Mix up egg, milk and oil, then add to dry ingredients.
Stir well and use for waffle iron or griddle.

title: my favorite snack:  chocolate mountain
directions: Take the apples and with a knife make two or more marks going down.
Take the cinnamon and dip it in the marks.
Then do the same thing with the chocolate.
Enjoy!

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together jello, Cool Whip and cottage cheese. Drain juices from pineapple and oranges. Add fruit to jello mixture. Store in refrigerator.

title: broccoli balls
directions: Mix ingredients
together.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and store in refrigerator.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: baked apple butter
directions: Peel and cook apples in a large pan slowly.
Cook until apples are real soft, mash like apple sauce.
Mix the above to apples in a roaster pan.
Bake in 300° oven (uncovered) until desired thickness.
Stir about every 30 minutes while in oven. Can in pint jars while very hot.

title: ice cream cone cupcakes
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Fill cones a little over 1/2 full. Place on a cookie sheet.
Place in a preheated oven (as directed on box).
Bake for 15 minutes or until top is firm to touch (not hard).
Cool and frost.
Add decorations as desired.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix ingredients one at a time.
Beat well after each ingredient.
Do not preheat oven.
Bake at 375° for approximately 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes large cake.

title: fish marinade sauce
directions: Mix all together.
Pour over fillets, cover for 2 hours.
Put under broiler until done.

title: lemon surprise!
directions: Combine flour, butter and chopped nuts; mix together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: cream cheese and taco sauce
directions: Place cream cheese block on serving platter and pour sauce over.
Place chips around sides and dip off cream cheese with chips.

title: asparagus pasta alfredo style
directions: In large saucepan cook fettuccine according to directions and drain.
Wash asparagus; scrape off scales.
Break off woody bases and discard.
Slice spears into 1-inch pieces.
Cook asparagus in small amount of boiling water, 3 to 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Remove from heat and drain.
Return pasta to large saucepan.
Add butter.
Toss gently until butter is melted, coating pasta.
Add cream and toss.
Add Parmesan, dash of pepper and asparagus.
Toss lightly.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fresh fruit tart
directions: Blend flour, 1/4 cup sugar, salt and 1/2 cup butter.
Stir in oats.
Pat in 10-inch tart pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: easy rocky road
directions: Microwave butter in 8-inch pan.
Set aside.
Place chips, margarine and shortening in large microwavable bowl.
Microwave at Medium (50%) for 5 to 7 minutes or until chips are softened and mixture is melted and smooth when stirred.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Blend well.
Spread evenly in prepared pan.
Cover; chill until firm.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for approximately 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix together the green beans and soup. Add 1/2 can onions and mix in.
Put in oven for 30 minutes at 375°.
Remove, put rest of onions on top, then serve.

title: hao nao brown kao
directions: Shape beef into large patty and brown on both sides in large skillet. Break patty into small chunks. Add onions and celery; saute about 5 minutes.

title: old fashioned baked beans
directions: Put can of beans in a baking dish. Mix all of your ingredients together and bake in preheated oven 40 minutes at 350°.

title: shish kabob
directions: Combine equal parts of liquid ingredients with dry ingredients and meat cubes.
Marinate in refrigerator for 1 or 2 days.
Skewer with slices of onion and bell pepper; grill over an open hot fire. Serve with Cajun rice and rolls for a complete meal.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix well. Drop by spoonful in oil in electric frypan at 400°. When brown, turn over and brown the other side.
Serve with ham or pork chops.

title: 24-hour salad
directions: Beat the eggs; add sugar and pineapple juice.
Cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
When cool, add whipping cream.
Prepare pineapple, cherries, oranges and marshmallows. Add to previously cooked dressing mixture.
Slice maraschino cherries on top.
Cool in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: coney island sauce
directions: Brown hamburg and drain. Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 3 to 4 hours.
Keep adding small amount of water.
Put in small cartons and freeze. Really good on the hot dogs!

title: dill bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Stir in 1 tablespoon sugar and dill. Let stand until bubbly for 15 minutes. Add the rest of the sugar, milk, butter and salt. Stir in flour to make a sticky dough. Place in well-greased 9 x 5-inch bread pan and cover with well-greased foil.
Let rise 35 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°. Bake for 35 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and put in baking pan.
Lay chicken on top.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour on top of chicken.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese (1/2 cup plus).
Top with 1/2 cup bread crumbs and melted butter.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: rich chocolate fudge
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, combine sugar, butter and evaporated milk.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, to a full rolling boil, 10 to 14 minutes.
Reduce heat to medium; boil, stirring constantly, until candy thermometer reaches 228° or small amount dropped into ice water forms a 2-inch soft thread.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in chocolate chips and chocolate until melted.
Stir in marshmallow cream until well blended.
Add vanilla and nuts; mix well.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool completely at room temperature.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: horseradish sauce(pepperrot saus)
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Chill until ready to serve.
Good with fish.

title: pecan souffle
directions: Heat milk.
Add beef-like flavoring.
Pour over cracker crumbs and egg.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked seafood salad
directions: Saut vegetables; add shrimp, crab meat and mayo and mix all together. Put in greased casserole. Top with buttered breadcrumbs and bake 40 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt margarine.
Add onions.
Cook until tender.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 5 minutes.
Keep in refrigerator.
Warm before using.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: parmesan mozzarella lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna; brown meat.
Combine cottage cheese, egg and Parmesan cheese.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: chocolate bars
directions: Melt chocolate chips, sweetened condensed milk and margarine on top of double boiler (or over low heat).
Combine peanuts and marshmallows.
Fold in chocolate mixture.
Spread in waxed paper lined 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Remove from pan.
Peel off wax paper.
Cut into squares.

title: 6 week muffins
directions: Blend flour, sugar, soda and salt together.
Add 15 ounce box of Kellogg's Raisin Bran, buttermilk, margarine and eggs.
Blend until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not stir again.

title: eggs deluxe
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise, and carefully remove yolks. Mash yolks and add mayonnaise; mix well. Stir in deviled ham and green pepper. Stuff whites with mixture; sprinkle with cheese and paprika. Yield: 6 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grate zucchini. Beat eggs until light. Add sugar, oil and vanilla and blend. Stir in zucchini. Sift flour and other dry ingredients together except nuts. Blend with creamed mixture. Fold in nuts. Bake in 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice potatoes, add onions and butter, cover with water.
Cook until potatoes are tender.	Add remaining ingredients and let simmer just until cheese is melted.
(Makes 8 cups.)

title: easy fudge
directions: Bring sugar and milk to boil.
Boil 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add other ingredients.
Pour into buttered dish.
Store in air tight container.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Grate cabbage and carrots. Dice celery, green pepper and onion; mix all together.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Add vanilla.
Stir in zucchini. Sift flour, salt, cinnamon, soda and baking powder.
Stir into first mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Add pineapple.
Pour into two well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sandwich filling
directions: Put all ingredients through food chopper.
Moisten with 1 cup salad dressing or mayonnaise.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: vanilla or fruit ice cream
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Add boiling water; set aside to cool.
Using mixer, beat eggs thoroughly.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla; continue beating.
Add cream and 1 to 2 cups of milk; beat.
Add cooled gelatin; stir well.
Pour mixture into freezer can.
Add enough milk to fill freezer can to fill line.
Freeze as directed for freezer.
Let ripen to improve flavor.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Combine mix, eggs, oil and cream cheese and fold in blueberries and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Do not preheat oven.

title: vanilla ice cream(yields 1 gallon)
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy; add sugar slowly, beating until mixture thickens.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Don't add milk yet.
Pour mixture into ice cream freezer and add the 7 to 8 cups of milk to the fill line on the freezer.
Put on lid and crank until frozen.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine corn, sugar and eggs, mixing thoroughly.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Cover mixture with cracker crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pasta a la vodka
directions: Saute shallot in olive oil and butter.
Add crushed tomatoes (Red Pack is nice and chunky).
Season with salt and crushed red pepper flakes.
Add basil and simmer about 1/2 hour.
Add half and half; simmer 10 to 15 more minutes.
Add vodka and continue simmering 15 minutes longer.
Stir often.
Let stand, covered, while cooking pasta.
Enjoy!
Sauce can be frozen, if leftover.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Mix with stuffing.
Line bottom of baking dish with half of stuffing. Mix other ingredients and pour over stuffing.
Place rest of stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: perfect homemade white bread
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine 2 1/2 cups flour and yeast.

title: crock-pot pork meal
directions: Place meat in bottom of crock-pot.
Sprinkle with seasoning salt.
Make layers of onions, kraut and potatoes.
Sprinkle again with seasoning salt.
Cook on low 10 to 12 hours.

title: rhubarb marmalade
directions: Mix rhubarb, sugar and pineapple in a pan and cook 20 minutes. Stir in Jell-O.
Put in jars and seal or store in the refrigerator.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
While warm, prick all over with fork and spread with condensed milk.
Let cool.
Spread drained pineapple over cake, then spread whipped topping. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: shrimp and wild rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and bake in a greased, 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: glorious frozen salad
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese together well.
Combine all ingredients together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze at least 2 to 3 hours or overnight.

title: low sodium oatmeal wheel macaroons
directions: Combine the cinnamon and melted oil.
Add the beaten egg. Gradually add sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until delicately browned. Remove from the baking sheet while warm.
Makes 20 cookies.
One cookie equals 4 mg. sodium.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and sour cream together with a wooden spoon.
Stir in spinach, onion and Worcestershire sauce.

title: crazy cake
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, sugar and soda.
Add water, vinegar, margarine and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in loaf pan in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Cook shrimp, celery, onion and pepper in 1/3 cup butter until shrimp turns pink.
Blend the remaining ingredients (except almonds and cheese).
Mix with shrimp mixture.
Sprinkle with almonds and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pepperoni bites
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan and bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Cut in squares.

title: venison steak and gravy
directions: Sprinkle meat with tenderizer.
Add salt and pepper.
Roll meat in flour.
Fry on medium heat until brown.
Take up and put in a crock-pot until you have cooked all the meat.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done.
Let cool, peel and mash.
Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and 1/2 cup butter.
Beat at medium speed until smooth.
Spoon into lightly greased 12 x 18 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine brown sugar, pecans, flour and 2 tablespoons butter. Sprinkle mixture over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yields 8 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar; stir in 1 cup of water and cook until thickened.
Add gelatin to mixture.
Place fresh strawberries in cooked pie shell (better if the berries are cut in half).
Pour mixture over them.
Refrigerate.
Serve with Cool Whip on top.

title: whipping cream cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour and cream alternately.
Add vanilla.
Bake in greased tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: party chicken tarts
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in large skillet over medium heat. Add mushrooms, celery and onion; stir until vegetables are tender. Stir in flour, chicken and sour cream.
Reduce heat and simmer until thoroughly heated.
Stir in garlic salt and remove from heat. Cut each biscuit into quarters; press each piece into miniature muffin tins coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Brush each piece with melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 6 minutes.
Remove from oven; reduce oven temperature to 350°.

title: amy's chicken pot pie
directions: Drain Veg-All (or rinse frozen vegetables) and chicken.
Mix together.
Add onions, soup, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour into deep dish crust.
Put other crust on top.
Crimp edges together and slash top.
Put dab of margarine on top.
Bake at 400° for about 50 minutes.
Let set a few minutes before serving.

title: pie crust(for 1 pie)
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Cut in lard.
Add water slowly and gently mix with fork until particles cling together.
Make half of dough into a ball and roll out on lightly floured board to 1/8-inch thickness.
Fit into pan and trim excess.
Makes enough for 2 pie shells.

title: lemon delights
directions: Mix cake mix, Cool Whip and egg together.
Roll into balls, then roll in confectioners sugar.
Bake 8 minutes in 350° oven.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Mix all but 1 cup corn chips.
Pour into 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Spread sour cream, 1/2 cup shredded cheese and 1 cup corn chips over top; bake 5 minutes longer.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Slice stems and scoop out seeds.
Blanch in boiling salted water 5 minutes; drain well.
Combine ground beef and remaining ingredients.
Stuff peppers.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Saute onions in butter. Mix all ingredients; pour into pie shell and sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: valentine salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Bring juice to a boil.
Pour over gelatin. Cool.
Add pineapple and cottage cheese.
Fold in whipped cream and nuts.
Chill until firm.
Salad will keep for several days in the refrigerator.
Makes 18 servings.

title: company salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Cool.
Add pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Chill in large flat dish.
Heat pineapple juice in top
of double boiler.
Add flour and sugar to beaten egg.
Mix with juice and cool until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spread over Jell-O.
Shred cheese over all.
If desired, top with chopped nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken in white wine sauce
directions: Melt butter in large, deep skillet and saute the chicken pieces.

When they are nicely browned, remove and reserve them. Add the 3 chopped shallots and the 3 whole shallots to the pan. When they have begun to brown, return the chicken and any cooking juices to the pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Reduce the heat and cook for about 45 minutes.
Turn the pieces from time to time, until they are uniformly cooked through.
As soon as the liquid begins to dry up, add the wine.
Discard the whole shallots before serving.
Serves 4.

title: one hour buttermilk rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add sugar and shortening. Add remaining ingredients, beating until smooth. Let rise 10 minutes. Shape into rolls. Let rise 30 minutes. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mock candy bars
