directions: Put 4 or 5 marshmallows in paper cupcake holders.
Melt oleo, chips and peanut butter until smooth.
Pour 2 tablespoons over each cup of marshmallows.
Refrigerate.

title: pineapple cupcakes
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat well.
Pour into cupcake liners and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Bring to a boil the first 5 ingredients; while simmering, mix flour with salt.
Add 1 whole egg and mix with fork until little lumps and shreds appear.
Drop this into boiling soup, stirring all the while, and cook about 10 minutes.
Add a tablespoon of butter and enough milk to thin out so it isn't so thick.
This soup tastes better warm than hot.

title: daniel's grasshopper pie
directions: Crush cookies and add butter.
Pat into pie pan to make crust.

title: italian beef
directions: Brown meat on both sides in frying pan.
Then place meat in the crock pot.
Add all ingredients except green pepper.
Add jalapeno pepper with juice as much to your taste, plus approximately 1 cup of water.
Cover, and simmer on low 4-6 hours. Slice meat very thinly and add to juice in the crockpot if necessary.
Simmer for 1 hour or until tender.
Place green pepper in meat mixture and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: fudge walnut pie
directions: In a medium bowl, stir melted chocolate into sour cream. Beat in milk.
Add pudding mix.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in walnuts.
Spoon into pie crust.
Top with whipped topping and garnish with chocolate curls and walnuts.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours or until firm.
Serve chilled.

title: zippy beef
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and stir until brown, then drain well.
Cook, then drain macaroni.
In ungreased 2-quart casserole, mix all ingredients.
Cover; bake until bubbly, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fudge icing
directions: Mix all ingredients in pan and stir over heat until all are melted.
Stir constantly with a wooden spoon until it comes to a rolling boil.
Boil exactly one minute.
Remove from heat and let set until cool.
Beat until thick enough to ice a cake.

title: hawaiian banana bread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients, stir in nuts and set aside. Combine remaining ingredients. Add to dry ingredients, stirring until just moistened. Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes, or until done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then turn out on rack.
Freezes well.

title: old fashioned buckwheat pancakes
directions: Add yeast mixture to two cups cold water.
Stir in the flour and buckwheat flour.
Add salt.
Beat vigorously until smooth. Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
In the morning, add molasses, melted butter and soda dissolved in 1/2 cup hot water. Let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes, then bake on hot griddle.
Serve with sausage and maple syrup.
Yummy.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Cook to soft ball stage.
Beat until creamy.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Stir constantly while this is cooking in a very deep pan or it will boil over.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form ball. Serve with crackers.

title: shaggy dogs
directions: Melt milk chocolate candy bars, adding milk to make a thin syrup.
(One small candy bar plus 1 tablespoon milk makes enough syrup for 2 Shaggy Dogs.)
Toast marshmallows on a stick; dip into chocolate syrup, then roll in flaked or shredded coconut.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Put in a pie crust.
Cool before serving.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat well together the oleo, cooking oil and sugar.
Beat eggs and the vanilla, then add to other mixture.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Let set in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Then roll in SMALL balls and place on a cookie sheet and flatten with bottom of glass that has been dipped in sugar or with a fork.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Do NOT grease or spray cookie sheet.

title: spice cake
directions: Combine raisins, soda and boiling water.
Let stand until cool.
Cream shortening and sugar; add beaten egg and vanilla. Combine two mixtures.
Bake in muffin pans or layer pan at 350° until done.

title: amy's pound cake
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Mix flour in then add flavoring and mix well.
Cook at 350 degrees for 1 hour or 325 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Prepare cookie mix. Spread on ungreased pizza pan. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients together and bake in greased and floured sheet pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
While hot, spread Marshmallow Creme on top.
Mix oleo, cocoa and milk; heat until melted.
Add powdered sugar and nuts.
Spread on top of cake. Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: no-peek chicken
directions: Lightly grease casserole.
Mix first 5 ingredients and place chicken on top.
Sprinkle chicken with onion soup.
Seal with foil and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
Do not peek.

title: jenna's cookies
directions: Mix; batter will be stiff.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: minted peas
directions: Place peas and water in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook, covered, 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove cover; dot with oleo and pour in creme de menthe.
Yields 4 servings.
Contains approximately 90 calories per serving.

title: candy strawberries
directions: Mix milk, jello, coconut and nuts.
Refrigerate overnight. Mold into shape of small strawberries.
Roll in red sugar.
Make leaves with green icing.
Refrigerate until served.

title: easy crust chicken pie
directions: Remove chicken from bone.
Skin and cut up.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch
baking
dish.
Mix broth, soup, 1/2 stick margarine, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken.

title: "grilled"  marinated shrimp with mango relish
directions: Leaving shells on protects shrimp from burning during grilling.
Size is important.
The bigger shrimp, the easier they are to peel.

title: low-fat hot cocoa
directions: Blend sugar and cocoa in a small saucepan.
Gradually add hot water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Boil and stir for 2 minutes.
Add milk.
Heat thoroughly. Stir occasionally.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Serve hot.
Makes two 7 ounce servings.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat water and margarine until almost boiling.
Remove from heat.
Add flour and baking powder.
Return to heat, beat vigorously with wooden spoon until ball forms.
Remove from heat. Add eggs, one at a time, beating constantly, until eggs disappear. Drop mixture by rounded teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheet, forming 12 large or 20 small puffs.
Bake immediately at 425° for 15 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° and cook until beads of moisture disappear.

title: fish chowder 2
directions: Fry the salt pork until it is crisp and brown.
Pour off about 2 tablespoons of the pork fat into a soup kettle and saute the carrots and celery until softened.
Add the onion and potatoes; saute another 2 to 3 minutes.
Add the fish fillets, wine, some water, bay leaf and 10 to 12 peppercorns.
Salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat for about 20 minutes or until the fish, potatoes and carrots are tender.
Stir in the fried salt pork.
Add the milk and heat, but do not boil.

title: hot chicken supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients, except noodles; stir well. Spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with noodles. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: jiffy plum cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine the last 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake in preheated oven (350°) for 20 minutes.
Remove. Chill.
Top with whipped cream.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients all together in baking dish. Crumble Ritz crackers very fine.
Add margarine.
Spread over top of vegetable mixture.
Bake in preheated oven for 35 minutes at 375°.

title: purple cow
directions: Pour grape soda into a tea glass until it is half full.
Add one scoop of vanilla ice cream.
Use a straw or spoon and enjoy.

title: andrea's salmon steak
directions: Preheat broiler.
Mix all ingredients except salmon in a bowl. Place salmon on a greased broiler rack skin side down.
Brush mixture on salmon.
Place broiler rack in oven for 10 minutes or until fish flakes.
Brush with mixture again and serve.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; add butter and vanilla last.
Mix well.
Shape into little balls and cool.
Coat with melted almond bark (chocolate or white).
Put on wax paper to cool.
Makes 36.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the chicken and broccoli in bowl. Put chicken and broccoli in casserole dish.
Pour mixture on top of chicken and cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: jello pops
directions: Mix and fill ice cube trays.
Freeze.

title: applesauce turnovers
directions: Mash cold cottage cheese with fork.
Mix well with other ingredients using hands.
let stand overnight in icebox.
Next day, roll dough in circle.
Cut in wedges.
Put applesauce in center of each piece and press edges together.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes or less.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting while warm.
Makes about 20.

title: rice crispy treat
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows together, then add cereal. Spread in a pan.

title: substitute for sweetened condensed milk
directions: Mix and let stand about five minutes.
It's as good as the Eagle Brand!

title: oatmeal buttermilk pancakes
directions: Combine oats, soda and buttermilk.
Wait 5 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Fry on griddle.

title: brown stone front cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together 5 or 6 times.
Beat cream and eggs until fluffy.
Then add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients (in small amounts).
Mix well while adding small amounts of dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done (approximately 30 to 35 minutes).

title: puppy chow
directions: In a large microwaveproof dish, melt the butter.
Add chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Stir until smooth.
Add Chex and stir until all pieces are coated.
Put powdered sugar in a paper bag (you may use a large plastic container).
Add cereal and shake rigorously until all chocolate pieces are covered.

title: aunt annie's seven layer salad
directions: Layer vegetables in a flat dish.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar. Pour on top of the layers.
Add cheese and bacon bits. Refrigerate for at least an hour before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli half done, drain.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Fold in broccoli.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: a working man's choice
directions: Brown meat and seasoning to taste.
Add corn and green beans and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 11-inch casserole dish with lid, then spread mashed potatoes over the top of meat evenly, then put sliced Swiss cheese over the top of everything.
Salt and pepper. Put lid on and bake for 1 hour at 350° or until everything is hot throughout.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift 3 cups flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice together in a medium-sized bowl.
In a separate bowl, beat the egg whites or egg substitute with the sugar, oil and vanilla.
Stir zucchini and raisins into egg mixture.
By hand, stir in the flour mixture just until flour is blended.
Spray two 8 x 4-inch loaf pans with nonstick spray.
Bake until done.

title: indian dessert
directions: Whip the cream in blender, then add milk and nuts.
Mix in blender, then freeze.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Grease 9 X 13 pan; add bread & 1 cup cheese. Cover with sausage. Mix eggs and 2 cups milk & mustard. Pour over casserole & cover. Set overnight.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together except oil and reserve 1/2 of the cheese for topping.
Pour oil in iron skillet.
Heat until hot. Pour over corn meal mixture in bowl.
Pour mixture into hot iron skillet and top with rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Do not turn over.
Serve hot or cold as hors d'oeuvres or in slices with a meal.

title: potato casserole
directions: Grease 8 x 11-inch casserole dish with margarine.
Saute celery and onion.
Mix frozen potatoes, celery and onion.
Add sour cream and soup; mix well.
Add melted margarine and cheese. Mix and pour into casserole, top with topping.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be doubled.

title: cherry pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and margarine.
Add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and almond extracts.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Fold in 1/2 jar of cherries Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: summer salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate half hour before serving. Can add 1/2 cup chopped walnuts.
Can substitute mandarin oranges for orange sections.

title: four layer delight
directions: Mix together flour and pecans.
Add butter, stirring until well blended.
Press mixture into the bottom of a 9x13-inch baking dish.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Cook beef and drain.
Simmer all ingredients, except for sour cream.
Add just to heat.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: ms. fitz fudge
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients to soft ball stage, this will turn light brown, over medium-low heat.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate, vanilla and nuts.
Beat!
Pour into buttered pan. Cool, cut and eat.
Yummm; call me over.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix all the sauces and marinate the wings overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 min.

title: chow mein noodle cookies
directions: Melt semi-sweet and butterscotch pieces together in top of double boiler over hot water.
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in chow mein noodles and chopped nuts until evenly coated.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Chill.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Makes about 36 cookies.
(Flavor is enhanced by storing overnight.)

title: pork chops with rice
directions: Spread pork chops with mustard.
Coat with flour and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Brown in small amount of oil in skillet. Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with soup.
Pour 3/4 can water around chops.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: country apple dessert
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and butter.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch dish. Pour pie filling over cake mix "dough."
Mix brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans and sprinkle over pie filling.
Blend sour cream, egg and vanilla. Pour over top and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half.
Mix all ingredients together.
Stuff into peppers.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Baste with tomato sauce.

title: christmas jello mold
directions: Prepare lime jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Dissolve ice cream into lime jello.
Pour into mold and chill until firm. Dissolve strawberry jello in 1 cup boiling water and add frozen strawberries.
Pour over lime jello-ice cream mixture.
Chill overnight.
To unmold, dip in warm water just to the rim.
Run a wet knife around inside rim of mold.
Turn over and it should come out clean.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar and oil.
Add eggs and pumpkin.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Add raisins, nuts and water. Stir well.
Grease and flour 2 bread tins.
Place 1/2 mixture in each tin.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: grandma's steak and gravy
directions: Batter and fry cube steak.
Mix mushrooms and French onion soup together in "crock-pot".
Turn on high heat.
Make regular gravy with grease left from frying cube steak.
Pour this gravy into "crock-pot" along with mushrooms and French onion.
Mix well. Drop pieces of cube steak into mixture and let it simmer for about 4 hours.
Makes some of the best steak and gravy a hungry man ever tasted.
Great for Golden Agers who have a hard time chewing up steak.

title: layered bean dip
directions: On large round platter:

title: angel bavarian cake
directions: In double boiler, mix egg yolks, milk, flour, sugar and salt. Stir over boiling water until thickened.
Dissolve gelatin in water and add to cooked mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in mixture.
Add flavoring.
Break cake into small pieces and cover bottom of large casserole dish with cake, pour on layer of egg yolk mixture.
Repeat until all is used.
Chill and top with whipped cream and coconut before serving (I think 1/2 teaspoon almond flavoring is enough).

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef, onion and lemon juice.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add ketchup, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Let boil down to preferred consistency.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 300°.

title: chess cake
directions: Cut margarine into cake mix as you would for pie crust.
Add first 2 eggs, one at a time.
Mix until soft ball is formed. Press into a 9 1/2 x 13 1/2-inch pan.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together except bacon.
Pour into baking dish and bake in oven at 400° for
1 to 1 1/2 hours, then bake at 200° for 1/2 hour.
(Put strips of bacon across top before baking.)

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour and sugar together; set aside.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine baking soda and buttermilk.
In a saucepan, heat butter, Coca-Cola and cocoa to boiling.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture and mix thoroughly. Add buttermilk mixture, eggs, vanilla and marshmallows; stir well. Pour into prepared pan.
(The batter is thin and marshmallows may float to top.)
Bake 35 to 45 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted comes out clean.
Cake will be quite dark on top.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Crumble yeast into large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, salt and water.
Add well beaten egg.
Sift flour once before measuring. Add 1/2 flour and beat well.
Add melted shortening and mix in rest of flour.
Let rise to double its bulk.
Punch down, cover tightly and place in fridge.
About 1 hour before baking, remove amount of dough desired.
Shape into small rolls and place on greased pan.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Beat lemon and sugar.
Put aside.
Mix all ingredients except 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Place in greased baking dish.
Then pour 1/2 cup tomato sauce mixed with lemon juice and sugar over top of meat loaf.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Baste frequently.

title: ice cream cake
directions: * Use your choice of kind of cake mix and ice cream (Chocolate cake with chocolate marshmallow ice cream; spice cake with praline ice cream or strawberry cake with strawberry ice cream).

title: chippy cheese ball
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
Blend well with mixer.
Add Worcestershire sauce, onion, pepper, and 1/4 cup crushed chips. Shape into ball and roll in remaining chips.
Chill.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all of the ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Roll in finely chopped peanuts, wheat germ or confectioners sugar.
Needs no cooking or refrigeration; however refrigeration will extend life. Store in a tightly sealed container. Enjoy as a healthy, tasty snack.

title: herman coffee cake
directions: Can also be glazed with maple syrup, margarine, etc.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: carrots supreme
directions: Partially cook carrots.
Drain well.
Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Add soup, cheese, mushrooms and 1/2 cup crumbs and mix well.
Place in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with rest of crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated.
Allow 15 minutes more baking time.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Take about 10 to 12 potatoes (or enough to fill a casserole dish).
Peel the potatoes and slice them into 1-inch slices. Spread the potatoes into the casserole dish.
Pour 1 can of cream of mushroom soup over top of the potatoes.
Then measure 1/2 can milk, using the soup can.
Add the milk on top of the potatoes. Add some salt and pepper for flavor.
At this time, completely cover the potatoes with shredded Mozzarella cheese.

title: mom's mock ham spread
directions: Blend bologna in grinder or blender or by hand.
Mix in relish and mayonnaise to taste.
If you like more relish, add or more mayonnaise, add.
Spread on bread. Slice sandwiches in 1/2 or 1/4 for party sandwiches.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Parboil eggplant for 5 minutes in salted water.

title: ruth's bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine both types of milk in a saucepan.
Heat until scalding hot.
Add butter and stir well. Set aside and let cool until only warm.
Blend eggs, sugar, vanilla and cinnamon together.
Add the warm milk.
Blend for several minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Let stand to jell.
Add salad dressing and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and let set.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix cornbread as directed on package.
Add other ingredients in the order given.
Bake at 400° until done (light brown).

title: onion baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Do not peel potatoes.
Cut in large chunks.
Place all ingredients in plastic bowl.
Cover tightly. Shake until all potatoes are evenly coated.
Bake in single layer for 40 minutes or until brown and tender.
Enjoy!

title: milk punch
directions: Place thawed fruit juice in large mixing bowl.
Add sugar and salt.
Stir.
Gradually add milk and ice water, blending to make a smooth mixture.
Chill.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: In Dutch oven or 2 1/2-quart saucepan, combine all but baking soda and popcorn.
Bring to boil, stirring over medium-high heat. Stir constantly and bring to 260° (hard ball; after boiling, stir and cook 5 minutes if no candy thermometer is used).
Stir in baking soda quickly but thoroughly.
Pour at once over popcorn; stir.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour; stir 2 or 3 times. Spread on wax paper to cool.

title: monkey bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Add sugar, salt, eggs, shortening and 3 1/2 cups flour. Beat real well. Add the remaining flour; knead 10 minutes.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan well.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over bottom.
Sprinkle Angel Flake coconut over nuts.

title: linguine with clam sauce
directions: Saute the onion in margarine until tender.
Add the juice from the clams, the seasonings, the condensed cream of mushroom soup and the white wine.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.

title: caviar mousse
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water, then dissolve in hot water.
Let cool.
Add lemon juice, pepper sauce, mustard and mayonnaise to gelatin and water.
Fold in sour cream and stir in caviar.
Pour into 3 or 4-cup mold.
Chill until set; unmold.
Serve with Melba toast rounds.
Serves 6.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump and spread pineapple in ungreased 10 x 13-inch pan; cover with nuts, pie filling and yellow cake mix (directly from box). Cover with oleo pats.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: "mag swift's" cocoons
directions: Mix all together in a large bowl.
Knead well with hands until bowl is clean.
Take tiny bits of dough (size of a pecan); roll between your palms until an oval shape (not too pointed or they will burn).

title: best yet eggplant
directions: Combine eggplant with egg, onion, salts, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Add melted drippings.
In a casserole, layer eggplant, crumbs and 3/4 cup cheese. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes. Sprinkle top with remaining cheese.
Bake for about 10 more minutes. Very good.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a jar with a tight fitting cover.
Let stand for several hours . Remove garlic.
Shake thoroughly before using.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Add water to juice to make 1 1/3 cups. Bring to a boil.
Stir into gelatin until dissolved.
Cool until slightly thickened.

title: fourth of july jello
directions: Add 2 cups boiling water to each jello mix.
Stir to dissolve.
Add 1 cup cold water to each and stir.
Place each mixture in a separate 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate 3 hours.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat after each.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to cream mixture alternately with milk and lemon juice.
Add coconut.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 to 1 hour and 15 minutes or 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: In large bowl, combine pie filling, pineapple, condensed milk, marshmallows and pecans.
Fold in whipped topping; chill and serve in a pretty crystal bowl.
You can add a couple drops of red food coloring if you like a brighter color.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add the taco seasoning and taco salsa, jalapeno peppers and cheese to ground beef.
Let simmer; drain again.
Add salt and pepper.
Crumble some chips; put in bottom of dish.
Add small amount of beef mixture, then put sliced cheese.
Add rest of beef mixture; top with package of Velveeta Mexican, shredded.
Put in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Put chips around side of dish.
Crush some for the top.
You can also put lettuce and tomatoes on top, if you wish.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook meat, garlic and onion together until meat is done.
Add enchilada sauce, soups, milk and pepper.
Mix well and cook about 15 minutes.
Put in dish layer of Doritos, meat mixture, cheese and repeat.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
This freezes well and will keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: dutch apple-crisp pie
directions: Peel apples and slice thin.
Mix 1/2 of sugar with 2 tablespoons flour and spices.
Toss flour mixture with apples. Pour into pastry shell and sprinkle lemon juice over apples; set aside.

title: pudding cake
directions: Bake layer cake in 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Spread pineapple and juice over cake; add cheese, mixed with pudding.
(Mix cream cheese with 1/4 cup milk and pudding with 2 cups milk.)
Spread cheese mixture over cake.
Spread with Cool Whip and top with coconut.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix well the first 4 ingredients.
Keep cool.
Dip apples into mixture as you eat the apples.
Dip tastes like caramel.
Makes 1 cup of dip.

title: flip flop cake
directions: Be sure butter and cream cheese are room temperature.

title: squash souffle
directions: Slice vegetables and boil for 5 minutes.
In a casserole, place a layer of vegetables, a layer of cracker crumbs and a layer of cheese.
Repeat until all vegetables are used up, ending with cheese and crackers on top.
Combine the milk, well beaten eggs and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over vegetables; bake for 30 minutes at 350°, or until tender when pierced with a fork.

title: rolls
directions: Mix together and let rise until double in bulk.
Make out into rolls and let rise again.
Any remaining dough may be put in refrigerator.
Bake in hot oven until brown.

title: cool carrots
directions: Cook carrots, onions and bell pepper until tender.
Cook remaining ingredients for 5 minutes and pour over carrots and bell peppers.
Refrigerate.
Let stand 24 hours.

title: quick gumbo
directions: Combine ingredients into soup pan.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 15 minutes.
Add file powder just before taking off the stove.
(Improves with "aging.")
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: unfrosted seven-up pound cake
directions: Combine butter, shortening, flour, sugar, eggs, 7-Up and vanilla in mixer bowl.
Beat for 20 minutes.
Spoon into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until cake springs back when lightly pressed with finger.
Do not underbake. Remove to wire rack to cool.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: blueberry sour cream cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine butter (room temperature) and sugar. Cream together.
Add 2 eggs, one at a time.
Add baking powder, salt and baking soda to flour.
Sift into bowl alternately with sour cream.
Add almond extract.

title: pasta salad for a crowd
directions: *Colored noodles are good in this.

title: homemade chicken burritos
directions: Boil chicken until done; while boiling, add 1 tablespoon butter, 1/2 tablespoon chicken seasoning, salt and pepper.
Remove chicken from pot; refrigerate until cool, then remove all meat from bone.
Put chicken into frying pan with 1 tablespoon butter, chopped onion and remaining chicken seasoning.
Let simmer with cover, about 20 minutes on medium-low heat.
Put chicken into large mixing bowl.
Add Miracle Whip, sour cream, cheeses, lettuce and rice; mix well.
Spoon into tortilla wrap and roll end to end.

title: reuben's casserole
directions: Top with 12 slices of rye bread (cubed and tossed with a stick of melted butter).
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes. Add all other ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into greased casserole. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate covered saltines
directions: Cover cookie sheet with foil.
Spray foil with Pam.
Place about 30 saltines on foil.
Melt butter; add brown sugar to melted butter.
Bring mixture to a boil for 3 minutes.
Pour over saltines.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread chocolate chips over saltines.
They will melt; use spatula to spread evenly.
Top with nuts.
I sometimes buy chopped toffee at Weavers and spread with the nuts.

title: potato salad
directions: Make 3 days ahead.
Boil potatoes with skin on. Layer potatoes, salt and pepper, mayonnaise, onion, parsley, onion and cottage cheese.
Slice eggs and crumbled bacon on top.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice and cook carrots (not too well done).
Mix together all the other ingredients.
Add to carrots and marinate.

title: gloria price's hollandaise sauce
directions: Heat butter to	bubbling
in a small saucepan.	Put egg yolks, lemon juice,
salt	and cayenne into container of electric blender.
Cover
and
turn	on
high
speed.
Immediately remove cover and pour hot butter in a steady stream.
Yield: 1 1/4 cups. May
be
stored
in
refrigerator.	Can
reheat
by placing jar in a pan of warm water.

title: the casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions in skillet.
Add salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
Cream together sour cream and the cheeses.
Cook noodles and drain.

title: rhubarb surprise cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package. Spray 13 X 9 pan. Cover bottom of pan with miniature marshmallows. Pour cake batter over marshmallows. Bring to a boil rhubarb, water and sugar. Remove from heat and stir in jello. Spoon over cake batter. Bake at 350 degrees 35- 40 minutes or until brown. Cake will be slushy when taken from oven, but will soon set. Serve with cool whip or ice cream.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cut potatoes and cut carrot.
Add to diced onion and broccoli. Cover with cool water.
Add bacon grease and bacon bits.
Bring to a boil.
After brought to boil turn down and cook until vegetables are tender, about 20 minutes on medium-high.
Add milk when 20 minutes end (add salt and pepper if desired).

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Beat the first 6 ingredients together until smooth.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool and ice with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar and salad oil. Add the baby food and mix well.
Add flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ground beef with macaroni
directions: Cook the pasta as per package instructions.
Cut the onion and fry it with 2-3 tsp. oil.
Add all-spice and the beef.
Braise until meat turns brown.
Then add water and tomato sauce and salt. Cook meat for 10 minutes.

title: macaroni pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 10-inch pie pan.
Prepare macaroni; drain.
Brown beef with celery.
Drain.
Stir in sauce and mushrooms.
Simmer 15 minutes.
In large bowl, combine eggs, cheese and garlic salt.
Add macaroni; toss lightly.
Pour macaroni mixture into pan, forming a crust.
Pour meat mixture over crust; cover with foil.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove foil and let stand 5 minutes before cutting in pie wedges.

title: beef and barley soup(weight watchers)
directions: In a large pan, warm olive oil and brown ground meat.
Drain grease.
Add broth, tomatoes with liquid, soy sauce, hot pepper sauce and oregano.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat to low and simmer for 30 minutes.
(I also add celery and carrots so they can get tender.)
Then add the barley to the pot.
Cover and simmer until barley is tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sunset salad(makes 48 portions)
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in hot water.
Add vinegar and chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in carrots, pineapple and pecans. Pour into individual molds, shallow pans, or two three-quart molds.
Chill until firm.
Unmold or cut into squares.
Serve on crisp lettuce with a mayonnaise topping, if desired.
Be sure to chill larger molds overnight.

title: russian tea
directions: Tie all spices loosely in a bag and bring to a boiling point in water.
Add tea and let steep five minutes.
Strain; heat fruit juices and add last.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Place yeast in 2 cups warm water.
Melt butter; cream with sugar.
Add egg.
Add dissolved yeast to creamed mixture, then add flour and mix well.
Place in airtight bowl.
Store in refrigerator.
To cook, drop by spoonfuls onto well-greased muffin tins and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until browned.
This dough keeps for several days.
Is better on second day.

title: claudia morgan's syrup cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the first 4 ingredients.
(You may use 1/2 oil and 1/2 applesauce, also less sugar).
Combine the dry ingredients.
Add alternately to the first 4 ingredients with buttermilk.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: jalapeno cornbread ii
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dry ingredients first.
Add eggs, one at a time, then other wet ingredients.
Mix only until blended.
If batter seems too thick or dry, add another egg or 1/4 cup milk.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased oblong pan.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Place sugar in saucepan.
Add cocoa and mix well.
Add milk and butter.
Stir constantly.
Cook until mixture comes to a boil. Boil for three minutes.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats. Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
This recipe will serve 6 people.

title: tuna florentine
directions: Squeeze spinach to remove excess liquid.
Spread spinach evenly in a greased 2 qt casserole dish.
Sprinkle with onion, tuna and eggs.
Mix sour cream and soup. Pour mixture evenly over eggs.
Mix melted butter and crumbs and sprinkle evenly over top of casserole.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.

title: elaine hurst oatmeal cake
directions: Pour 1/2 cup boiling water over 1 cup oats and 1/2 cup margarine.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Combine the rest of the ingredients.
Add oat mixture.
Mix and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: garlic and chive potatoes
directions: Boil red new potatoes until tender.
Drain and cool.
Place potatoes in Pyrex dish.
Pour 1 cup melted butter over potatoes. Sprinkle with garlic salt and chives.
Put in oven; bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: orange chiffon cake
directions: Separate eggs, placing whites in large mixer bowl.
Let stand at room temperature, about 1 hour.
Have ready a 10 x 4-inch deep tube pan.
Grate orange rind, squeeze juice.
Set oven at 325° to preheat.
Sift together into small mixer bowl the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a hole in the middle of flour and pour in oil.
Combine yolks, orange rind and juice.
Add to small bowl; set aside.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Flatten dough on cookie sheet and bake as directed; cool.

title: minced clam sauce for spaghetti
directions: Mix all ingredients together in saucepan or large skillet. Heat for 10 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti noodles.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle an additional 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese on top and bake until melted.

title: oven-barbecued brisket
directions: Combine celery salt, onion salt, garlic powder and pepper. Sprinkle on both sides of brisket.
Place brisket in shallow dish. Combine Worcestershire and liquid smoke.
Pour over brisket. Cover and marinate in refrigerator 12 hours, turning occasionally. Cover and bake at 300° for 4 1/2 hours.
Drain, reserving 1 cup drippings.
Combine barbecue sauce and drippings; pour over brisket.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Slice brisket.

title: oatmeal crispy ice-cream sandwiches
directions: Use electric mixer at medium speed and beat shortening until fluffy.
Add sugars and beat well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Combine flour, soda and oats.
Add to shortening mixture. Mix well and then stir in pecans.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Shape dough into 38 balls and place 3-inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Dip flat-bottomed glass in flour and flatten each ball into a 2 1/2-inch circle.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes. Remove to wire rack and cool.

title: baked cubed steak with potatoes
directions: Soak cube steak in water for 15 to 20 minutes.
While cube steak is soaking, peel and cut potatoes into halves.
Place in an ovenproof dish.
Roll cube steak in the flour, salt and pepper. Place in hot grease to brown.
Do not cook thoroughly, just brown both sides.
Place cube steak in the dish with the potatoes.
Add 1/4 cup of flour to a small amount of grease, salt and pepper. Next, add two cans of golden mushroom soup with water to make a gravy to cover the cube steaks.
Gravy will not be thick.
If gravy does not cover cube steak, add additional water to cover.
Once gravy is poured over the cube steak, cover with tinfoil and place in the oven heated at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: molasses muffins
directions: Put flour in cup; add baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add bran; mix.
Add milk and molasses.
Add raisins.
Stir.
Bake in paper cup in covered skillet at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, eggs and milk; mix well.
Stir in coconut and flavorings.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: breakfast sausage muffins
directions: Brown sausage and drain grease.
Add margarine and cheese. Mix and heat until well blended.
Put mixture on muffin halves. I make these and place them in individual baggies and freeze. Defrost, then broil until brown.

title: double chocolate chip bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove wrapping from dough and press 2/3 of each roll of dough into bottom of one ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Over low heat, in saucepan, stir together condensed milk, chocolate chips and salt until melted and remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour and spread chocolate mixture over dough in pan. Cut remaining dough into chunks and randomly place on top of chocolate.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until golden. Cool; cut into bars.
These freeze well.

title: apricot jello mold
directions: Heat orange juice with a squeeze of lemon juice.
Dissolve jello in orange juice.
Add buttermilk and water.
Chill.
This makes a great mold.

title: juicy hamburger patties
directions: Mix ground chuck, sugar, soy sauce and ginger; let stand for a while.
Make into patties.
Dip in flour.
Mix eggs and green onions.
Dip patties in egg mixture.
Pan-fry in lightly oiled pan over very low heat.
Cook on each side.

title: wicked chocolate trifle
directions: Prepare cake mix and pudding according to package directions. (You may add 1 1/2 cups chocolate chips to pudding as it cooks for a richer chocolate flavor.)

When ingredients have cooled, assemble in trifle dish or large deep container laying thusly: cake, pudding, whipped topping and chocolate chips or other candy bits until at least whipped cream and garnish top.
Serve a lot!

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: Add mushrooms when you cook chicken.
You can use bacon drippings instead of oil.

title: potato casserole
directions: Precook potatoes for 5 minutes; drain.
In oblong casserole, put layer of potatoes and layer of beef.
Mix eggs and milk together, pour over layer and add salt and pepper.
Repeat layers and egg mixture as many times as you want.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until burger is done.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until desired doneness.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Select grown tomatoes that are still hard and green.
Slice lightly; salt and pepper.
Roll in flour and fry in about 1-inch hot oil.
This has to be done quickly to prevent absorbing too much oil.
When brown, turn over and brown other side and drain on paper towel.

title: green chile corn bread
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; remove.
Combine corn meal, salt, sugar, soda, milk and eggs, stirring until blended.
Add onion, corn, peppers and bacon (crumbled); mix well.
Pour 1/2 mixture into greased pan.
Cover with 1/2 cheese.
Spoon on remaining corn meal mixture.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pineapple and ice cream punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ginger ale. Beat at low speed of electric mixer until well blended. Pour mixture into punch bowl.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Makes 30 (4 ounce) servings.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Bring oleo, cocoa and milk to a boil.
Add vanilla, sugar and nuts.
Pour icing over cake while cake is warm.
Best over brownie cake mix made in a sheet cake pan.

title: flounder-shrimp bake
directions: Place fillets in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with soup.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Combine butter and seasonings and mix with cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle over fish.
Bake about 10 minutes.
Serves 12.
Serve with rice and tossed salad.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Set aside 1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese.
In a bowl with a mixer, beat the remaining Parmesan, Neufchatel cheese, sour cream and dill weed until well blended and creamy.
Stir in chopped artichoke hearts until blended.
Spoon mixture into an attractive shallow 3 to 4 cup baking dish.
Sprinkle with the reserved 1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese.
(If made ahead, cover and chill up until the next day.)

title: lemon-garlic salad dressing
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in small cup and let set out for at least 1 hour.
Pour over green salad.
Add salad oil.
Let set for about 30 minutes.
Toss well.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Combine butter, garlic and onion; cook until tender.
Add rest of ingredients, except spaghetti.
Cook on low until cheese melts. Pour over spaghetti.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: graham cracker pralines
directions: Lay graham crackers in squares on ungreased cookie sheet. Boil sugar, oleo and butter in saucepan for 2 minutes.
Pour syrup over crackers.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes. Remove and quickly triangle the crackers with a sharp knife. Remove and set on greased foil to cool.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together.
Add shortening, peanut butter and milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs; beat 2 minutes more. Pour into oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let cool.

title: byerly's orange creme chocolate cups
directions: You will also need 10 foil muffin baking cups.

title: texas chili
directions: Brown meat.
Drain.
Put back into pot and remaining ingredients and slow cook for 2 hours.
Serve with bread or over pasta.
Serves 6.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix hamburg, crumbs, onions, milk, egg, parsley, salt, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Gently shape into 1-inch balls and cook in shortening until brown.
Remove from skillet; drain fat.
Heat chili sauce and jelly in skillet, stirring constantly, until jelly is melted.
Add meatballs and stir until coated. Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: cocoa apple cake(tender and keeps well)
directions: Using a 10-inch cake pan, grease and flour the pan bottom. Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat together eggs, butter (or margarine), sugar and water.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, allspice, cocoa and cinnamon; after mixed, sift dry ingredients into egg mixture while stirring.
Mix well.
Fold in nuts, chocolate, apples and vanilla.
Pour into cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes, until top springs back if touched lightly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all of these ingredients and let stand overnight in buttered 2 1/2-quart size casserole. Sprinkle with paprika and bake 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown together ground beef, onion, butter and garlic.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Mix together and add mushrooms and soup. Stir and simmer 5 to 10 minutes, uncovered.
Add sour cream last. Heat through.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage together and drain.
Add other ingredients and heat until cheese has melted.
Serve hot.

title: cheese casserole
directions: Spread bread with margarine and make cheese sandwiches. Grease baking dish and place sandwiches in the bottom, cutting them to fit casserole.
Mix eggs and milk together, beating them well.
Add seasonings.
Pour mixture over the sandwiches.
Let stand 3 hours in fridge.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
This may be made the day before and baked when ready to use.
It may be served with some grated cheese on top or with crisp bacon strips on top.

title: green tomato pie filling
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until almost tender.
Add the mixed dry ingredients.
Boil hard for 5 minutes.
Place in glass jars and seal immediately.
Before pouring into unbaked pie crust, heat and stir in a cornstarch thickening and add 1 tablespoon butter. A few raisins may be added, if desired.
Bake 3/4 hour in moderate oven.

title: beef barbecue sandwiches
directions: Cut up meat into small pieces. Simmer catsup, brown sugar, A.1. and dry mustard until hot.
Add meat.
Serve on hamburg buns.

title: green pea cantonese
directions: Cook peas, unseasoned, then drain.
In frypan, cook onions and celery in butter until tender.
Add water chestnuts that have been drained and sliced very thin.
Add soup, flour and peas.
Mix all together and heat on the top of stove.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into casserole dish and cover with dressing mix. Bake at 350° until brown, about 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: the next best thing to robert redford
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, margarine and 1/2 cup of chopped nuts with a pastry blender until crumbly.
Spread in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1/2 of the whipped topping over cooled crust.
Mix vanilla pudding with 1 1/2 cups milk.
Spread over cream cheese layer. Mix chocolate pudding with 1 1/2 cups milk and spread over vanilla layer.
Spread remaining whipped topping over chocolate layer. Sprinkle top with shaved chocolate bar and chopped nuts.

title: ruby's coconut cake
directions: Mix melted butter and sugar.
Add eggs (saving 3 of the whites for icing).
Beat until mixed.
Add flour and milk.
Mix well. Add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 300° until toothpick stuck in center comes out clean.

title: chess pies (2)
directions: Mix all ingredients in one bowl.
Pour into 2 shallow, unbaked pie crusts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool before cutting.

title: spumoni cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Divide batter into 3 bowls.
Stir walnuts, green food coloring and almond extract to one.
Add cherries and red food coloring to another.
Stir melted chocolate into remaining portion.
Spray 8-inch fluted Bundt pan with Baker's Joy.
Layer with green batter first, then pink batter, then chocolate.
Do not swirl.
Bake in 350° oven 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool; invert cake.
Drizzle with chocolate glaze.

title: baked rice pudding
directions: Bring 1 cup water to a boil and add rice.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 14 minutes.
Do not stir.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: french breakfast rolls
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Blend in egg yolk.
Add other ingredients to creamed mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in small greased muffin tins, 20 to 25 minutes. Roll hot rolls in melted butter, then in cinnamon and sugar mixture.

title: old-fashioned gingerbread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, shortening, ginger and cinnamon together as for pie crust.
Reserve 1/2 cup for topping.
Combine remaining mixture with remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 8 x 9-inch cake pan.
Crumble reserved mixture over top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: basic vegetarian "meat ball or patties"
directions: Form into balls about the size of golf balls. Place in baking dish and cover with foil.
Bake in a 350° oven about 20 minutes until set and slightly brown.
Serve with sour cream, sauce and noodles or spaghetti sauce and pasta or savory sauce with potatoes.
Makes 30 balls, 2 or 3 per serving. Make patties as a veggie burger.

title: red beans a la maria
directions: Cover beans with water (1 cup beans to 2 cups water).
Add salt, pepper and ginger; cook approximately 2 hours, until tender. If you soak the beans in water overnight, it will reduce cooking time.
Saute beef, onion and garlic.
Add chili mix, oregano and tomato sauce or juice.
Mix well, then add to beans.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour out onto a well floured board. With rolling pin, roll out half batter at a time.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Drop one at a time into 2-quarts boiling chicken broth in a 4-quart Dutch oven or pan.
Cook 20 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and bring to a boil.
Let simmer 30 minutes.
Let stand overnight to blend flavors.
Makes 3 pints.

title: easy baked pork chops
directions: Brown chops in small amount of butter in frying pan.
Remove into a casserole with a cover.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.

title: prosciutto pizza
directions: Saut the onion and garlic in the oil over medium heat for 3 minutes.
Add the pepper, cover and cook over medium heat 10 minutes or until the onions are caramelized.
Spread mixture out over the pizza crust; add prosciutto, cheese and rosemary.
Bake in 400° oven 30 minutes if using a raw crust, 15-20 minutes if pre-baked.

title: "mom's" corned beef salad - 1976
directions: Heat consomme; add jello.
When it starts to thicken, add lemon juice, then all other ingredients, except the egg for garnish.
Serves 2.

title: white beans and roasted garlic spread
directions: Place the garlic in a custard cup.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until soft when tested with the tip of a knife.
Do not allow the garlic to brown.
Let cool slightly, then slip off the skins and trim off the hard stem ends.
Place half of the beans, plus the lemon juice, oil and garlic in a food processor.
Puree until smooth.
Transfer to a medium bowl.
Stir in the parsley, black pepper, half of the onions, half of the green peppers and the remaining beans.
Roughly mash the whole beans with fork.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Beat egg with 1 tablespoon water; dip chicken breasts into egg, then roll in bread crumbs. Brown chicken in oil, being careful not to burn. Mix soup with 1/4 cup water, along with celery, onion and garlic powder. Place chicken into a baking dish; pour soup mixture over meat. Cover. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes. Cover chicken with Mozzarella cheese; heat until cheese is melted.

title: irmadella reed's corn bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix shortening and flour together using a pastry blender.
Add ice water, one tablespoon at a time.
Mix with fork.
Use hands to make a ball, if necessary.
Roll out and bake until light brown.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Prepare Stove Top stuffing mix as package directs.
Put on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare vegetable mix as package directs.
Drain and layer over the stuffing mix.
Next, combine the soup, 1 can water and the Velveeta cheese until smooth over medium heat.
Pour over first 2 layers.
Add shredded cheese over top and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chewy date nut bars
directions: Combine cake mix and brown sugar.
Add butter and eggs.
Beat on medium speed 2 minutes.

title: christmas cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well!
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed avocado
directions: Be sure avocado is ripe (to test for ripeness, press at the rounded end, it should yield slightly).
Cut in half, remove seed and immediately sprinkle with lemon juice to prevent discoloration.
Mix shrimp, salt and pepper to fill avocado halves.
Arrange egg slices on top.
Top with a spoon of mayonnaise or sour cream.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Mix boxed cake mix, eggs, oil, margarine and oranges with mixer.
Grease 3 round pans.
Distribute mix evenly in all 3 pans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes only.
Remove and cool.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll into ball and roll in nuts.

title: simple baked beans
directions: Empty cans into greased casserole.
Mix sugar and mustard; put into beans.
Put cut up bacon and ketchup on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: sally struthers' shrimp scampi
directions: Heat butter over low heat.
Add olive oil, parsley, garlic and lemon juice.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook for about 3 minutes, then remove from heat.
Add shrimp to mixture; let stand about 30 minutes.
Remove shrimp from butter and place in shallow pan.
Broil approximately 5 minutes and turn.
Pour remaining sauce over shrimp; broil another 5 minutes.
Serve with toothpicks as a snack or appetizer.

title: chicken continental
directions: Roll chicken in flour; brown in butter.
Remove chicken.
Stir soup, seasonings, and water in drippings.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Spread Minute rice (directly from box) in a 1 3/4 qt shallow casserole.
Pour all but 1/3 cup soup over rice. Stir to moisten.
Top with chicken and remaining soup.
Bake covered at 375° for 30 minutes, or until tender.
Garnish with paprika, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: perfect rice
directions: Place rice in
iron skillet. Add 2 cups of water and a little salt.
Bring to a boil.
Place lid on tight. Turn off electric stove, or let boil
for 5 minutes on gas stove.
Turn off heat and let set.

title: lemon frosting
directions: Cook in double boiler until thick.

title: turtle bars
directions: Mix cake mix with melted butter and 1/3 cup evaporated milk. Pat half of this cake mixture into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Let cool.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and 1 cup nuts on top.
Drizzle caramel that has been melted in double boiler with 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Cool a little. Spread remaining cake mixture on top of caramel mixture; add remaining nuts.
Press in.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Let cool.
Cut into bars.

title: little cheesecakes
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature.
Into cupcake pans, put paper liners and a vanilla wafer.
Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and cream together.
Beat on low speed until light and fluffy.
Spoon into cups, 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° until set (10 to 15 minutes).
Cool out of pan on cake rack.
When cool spread cherry pie filling on top of each one.
Store in refrigerator. Makes 48.

title: mama's apple dumplings
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil for one minute. Roll out the 10 biscuits, each biscuit to about 5-inches. Dice apples, about 2 cups (Granny Smith) and place in the center of the biscuits; fold over. Place seam side down. Pour sauce over the biscuits and bake at 350° until brown.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco.
Mix vinegar, water and egg together.
Add to dry ingredients.
Makes 4 crusts.

title: succotash
directions: Cook corn and lima beans according to package.
Make rue; heat butter and add flour (do not brown).
Add milk slowly; stir until it thickens.
Add pepper and paprika to taste.
Add drained vegetables to milk mixture.
Serve.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Pour 1/2 batter into well oiled hot iron skillet or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle on cheese. Add remaining batter and spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spiced grape juice
directions: Soak orange rind, lemon, water and sugar for 15 minutes.
Add grape juice, cloves and cinnamon; simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix well and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Put in greased casserole dish with pan of water underneath.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top before you bake.

title: orange tapioca salad
directions: Cook water until it boils; add jello and puddings, stirring constantly, until dissolved.
Refrigerate until congealed.
Mix in Cool Whip, pineapple, oranges (both drained) and nuts. Refrigerate.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Place butter and egg yolks in bowl; beat until light and fluffy (about 1 minute).
Add cream, vanilla and salt.
Turn to stir speed; gradually add powdered sugar, mixing until desired consistency is reached.
Yields frosting for 2 (9-inch) layers.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar together until fine.
Add cooled margarine, eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°, turn temperature down to 325° and bake 25 minutes or until pie is set.
Cool, do not cut while hot.

title: christening punch
directions: Combine ingredients pour over ice ring or mold made with white grape juice (make a day ahead).

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream cheese and margarine.
Blend all ingredients with cheese mixture and make small balls with hands.
Press with fork.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Lay on paper towels to cool.

title: pizza dough
directions: Mix and let rise while making toppings, approximately 10 minutes.
Knead.
Press into pans.
Spread on sauce, meat, cheese, etc.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In unbaked pie shell, spread ham and cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over ham and cheese mixture.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Then 30 minutes at 350° or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm or cold.

title: fish coating
directions: Mix in bag.
Shake with fish.
Bake fish 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Use on whole fish.

title: mexican corn bread(a meal in itself.)
directions: Grease large skillet and sprinkle a little corn meal and let brown.
Pour 1/2 of the batter in skillet; sprinkle cheese over batter, then the meat, next onion and last the peppers.
Pour remaining
batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: delicious potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes, slice and layer alternately with minced onion in a greased casserole dish.
Mix mushroom soup and milk and pour over top of casserole.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 5 minutes before turning out.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when completely cooled.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Combine flour, salt, soda, baking powder and sugar in a bowl. Cut in 1/2 cup butter or margarine until it resembles cornmeal. Combine buttermilk and Sourdough Starter and blend.
Stir into flour mixture until mixture forms soft dough.
Turn dough onto floured board and knead gently, about 1/2 minute. Roll out 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick and cut with small biscuit cutter.
Place on cookie sheet and brush with butter or margarine.
Let rest in warm place about 1/2 hour.
Yields about 2 dozen biscuits.
Can be cut in half for 12 biscuits.

title: cocktail hot dogs
directions: Melt jelly in saucepan; add mustard.
When well combined, add hot dogs and simmer 1/2 hour, stirring often.
Spear with toothpicks and serve.

title: bet's broccoli salad
directions: Mix all together except tomatoes and bacon.
Set overnight. Just before you serve, mix bacon and tomatoes.

title: pie crusts
directions: Blend Crisco with flour until mixture looks like peas.
Make a "well" with spoon.
Add the cold water at one time.
Stir to form a soft ball of dough.
Roll out on floured area.
Grease pans, place dough and crimp edges.
Will make 2 pies.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Combine oil, eggs and sugar in a large bowl; mix well.
Gradually add "dry" ingredients to creamed mixture, stirring just until all ingredients are moistened.
Stir in strawberries and chopped nuts.
Spoon mixture into two greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove to wire rack and cool completely.

title: country raisin gingersnaps
directions: Beat together shortening and sugar and egg.
Mix in molasses, flour and spices.
Add raisins.
Chill dough.
Shape in small balls and roll in additional sugar.
Places on greased baking sheet at 375°
for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix above and pour into 2 pie crusts.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: shrimp and chicken jambalaya
directions: Saute chicken, onion, pepper and garlic in melted butter.
Add rice.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, their liquid, parsley, basil and pepper sauce.
Bring to a boil and add chicken broth.
Simmer 15 minutes, covered.
Add shrimp and peas.
Cook, covered, for 3 minutes or until tender.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, marshmallows and walnuts.
Let stand until slightly set.
Add pineapple and cream cheese.
Pour in mold and chill until set.

title: nut cream loaf
directions: Cook the
sugar,
cream
and
syrup to soft ball stage. Remove from heat and add butter, vanilla and nuts.
Stir until almost set.
Pour
out
on
greased cookie sheet and let cool. Cut into squares.

title: turtles
directions: Microwave caramels and milk on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir. Continue process until caramels are smooth and creamy.
Add margarine and pecans; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on buttered cookie sheets.
Chill for about 30 minutes.
Remove from fridge and mold into shapes.
Refrigerate for about 30 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin on 50% for 1 1/2 minutes.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Remove and stir.
Continue cooking until paraffin and chocolate are melted and glossy.
Dip caramels in chocolate and put back on cookie sheet to cool in fridge.

title: swiss international coffee
directions: Mix ahead and store in airtight jars.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, then add water.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Slice strawberries into pie shells.
Pour cooled mixture over berries. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Top with whipped topping. Yields 2 pies.

title: surprise kiss cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in flour and nuts. Shape 1 tablespoon dough around Hershey Kiss covering kiss completely.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until set but not browned.
Roll in 10x sugar.

title: meat loaf
directions: Stir together egg, onion, tomato sauce, oatmeal, salt and pepper.
Add ground beef, mixing well.
Place in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: italian green beans(microwave)
directions: Place garlic and oil in a 13 x 10 x 2-inch dish.
Cook, uncovered, at 100% for about 1 minute.
Remove from oven.
Stir in thyme, oregano and tomatoes.
Cook, uncovered, for 2 minutes. Remove from oven and stir in green beans and black pepper.
Cover tightly with microwave plastic wrap.
Cook for 7 minutes. Carefully prick plastic to release steam (be very careful of steam that will escape).
Uncover and stir in lemon juice.
Serves 4 (76 calories per serving).

title: divinity
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Bring to boil until forms soft ball in cold water.
Add half of mixture to beaten egg whites. Boil remaining syrup to form hard crystal.
Beat until cool enough to spoon out on wax paper.
Put in pecans when ready to spoon out.

title: biscuits
directions: Soften butter. Mix with sour cream.
Add flour.
Bake in small muffin tins at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes exactly 24. Freeze leftovers.
Fill muffin tins full.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Mix the pudding mix and milk; beat in softened cream cheese. Mix in Cool Whip.
Stir in sliced bananas and vanilla wafers. Leave in large mixing bowl.
Wonderful for fast dessert.
Great to take for church dinners or funeral gatherings.
I always get a lot of compliments on this.

title: marie's punch
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Just before serving add the ginger ale.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: In a large bowl, mix butter, sugar and milk with mashed sweet potatoes.
In a small bowl, combine melted butter, flour and brown sugar.
Add nuts and stir.
Pour sweet potato mixture in a casserole dish or oblong pan.
Spread brown sugar mixture on top and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: rice krispies sandwich
directions: Blend syrup and peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies.
Press mixture evenly in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze until firm. Cut in half.
On one half, spread with softened ice cream.
Put other half of top to make a sandwich.
Freeze, slice and enjoy.

title: potatoes au gratin deluxe
directions: Put milk, half and half, butter, salt and pepper in pan.
Let come to a boil.
Put in the softened potatoes and let it come to a boil again.
It should be thick.
Add some Parmesan cheese to taste.
Bake in a 325° oven for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: party chops
directions: Place chops in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients and pour over chops.
Bake uncovered at 300° for 2 hours.
Serves 12.

title: corn and green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in baking dish.
Cover with crushed cheese crackers.
Melt one stick margarine; pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: hot baked potato salad
directions: Rub potatoes with oil.
Bake 1 hour or until done.
Meanwhile, fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Add salad oil to bacon fat to make 2/3 cup.
Return to skillet; add onion, salt, pepper, vinegar and sugar.
Heat.
Cut thin
slice from top of each potato.
Scoop out centers; blend (do not mash) with vinegar mixture, green pepper and bacon.
Stuff back into potato shells. Can be wrapped individually in plastic wrap and frozen individually, then bagged ready for heating in microwave.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Mix cheese soup and milk.
Add lima beans, chopped celery and chopped parsley.
Stir in 1/2 can French fried onions.
Put in casserole.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes.
Border the casserole with remaining onions.
Bake 10 more minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together oleo, molasses and sugar.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Combine with molasses mixture.
Stir in oatmeal, nuts and raisins.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: bounds family favorite chocolate pie
directions: Cream together sugar, flour, egg, egg yolks.
Add milk; then add chocolate, butter, and vanilla.
Cook until bubbling boil. Stir constantly.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: fancy franks
directions: Simmer all ingredients in electric fondue pot after cooking 15 minutes (do not boil).

title: chicken puffs
directions: Bring water and butter to boil.
Add flour and salt all at once.
Beat until mixture forms a ball and leaves sides of pan clean.
Remove from heat and beat in eggs, one at a time.
Drop from small spoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Finished puffs should be the size of large walnuts. Split in half and fill with chicken salad.

title: railroad salad dressing
directions: Boil vinegar and sugar until dissolved.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to vinegar mixture.
Shake to thoroughly blend. Makes 3 1/4 cups.

title: annie's fried rice
directions: Cook cup of rice as directed on package.
Saute onion and green pepper chopped in 1/4 stick butter.
Beat 2 eggs; blend with onion and pepper.
Stir and add cooked rice.
Add salt, pepper, parsley, soy sauce and sugar.

title: layered taco dip
directions: In large skillet brown beef; pour off fat.
Add chilies and bouillon.
Cook and stir until bouillon dissolves.
Cool.
Stir in refried beans.
In small bowl combine sour cream and taco seasoning; set aside.
In large dish spread beef mixture.
Top with sour cream.
Cover and chill several hours.
Just before serving, garnish with cheese, tomatoes, green onions and olives. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Mix together margarine, sugar and flour and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: nancy sherman's pineapple punch
directions: Boil sugar, water, cinnamon sticks and cloves together for 30 minutes (gently).
Strain; chill.
Add pineapple, orange and lemon juices.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Serve over ice cubes or frozen pineapple juice cubes.
(If ginger ale is cold, you can omit the ice cubes.
You may wish to add an extra quart of ginger ale to dilute sweetness, or omit some of the sugar.)

title: rhubarb juice
directions: Cook thoroughly rhubarb and water.
Pour through sieve or large strainer.
Do not mash this mixture.
Let it drip clear with no pulp.
Heat the juice to boiling and add jello, pineapple juice and sugar.
Stir until sugar and jello are dissolved.
Pour into prepared jars and seal or freeze.
This keeps well in refrigerator as any canned juice.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: split pea soup
directions: Place split peas, water, bay leaf, salt and dry mustard in a kettle.
Bring to a boil, lower heat as much as possible and simmer partially covered for 20 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients, except pepper and leave it to simmer gently for 40 minutes with occasional stirring.
If necessary, add some water.
Before serving, add a generous amount of pepper.
This is a delicious fat free soup.

title: fudgsicles
directions: Beat
the eggs and remaining ingredients; pour into ice tubs.

title: avocado dip
directions: Peel and slice avocados.
Mash avocados to pulp.
Add lemon juice, garlic salt and Tabasco to taste.
Add onion, tomato and mayo.

title: cut out cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients. Chill about one hour. Roll out on floured surface and use your choice of cookie cutter. Frost with favorite frosting.

title: colonial beans
directions: In a quart casserole, combine beans with all ingredients, except bacon.
Cut bacon into pieces. Add to beans. Bake, covered, in a 400° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: lou's punch bowl cake
directions: Cook cake mix according to the instructions.
Layers begin with 1/2 of the cake.
Add 1/2 of preceding ingredients.
Add one ingredient at a time so that it is in layers.
Repeat until you use all the ingredients.
Makes 36 servings.

title: hamburger crunch
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Mix remaining ingredients (except onion rings).
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Put onion rings over top and bake 10 more minutes.

title: corn machue
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper, celery and garlic in oil until tender.
Drain corn and add with 1 can Ro-Tel tomatoes; cook 45 minutes, covered, on medium heat, stirring often to prevent sticking.

title: microwave rice pilaf
directions: Combine onion, celery, green pepper and butter in a 1 quart microwave-safe dish.
Microwave, uncovered, on high for 3-5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp tender.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Cook on high for 12-14 minutes or until rice is tender.
Serves 2.

title: luscious rich cheese cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients together and pack into bottom of spring-form pan.

title: kentucky chicken
directions: Mix crumbs, cheese, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper.
Dip each piece of chicken into melted butter, then into crumb mixture. Be sure each piece is well coated.
Arrange in a shallow roasting pan.
Pour remaining butter over all of chicken and bake 1 hour or until fork-tender at 350°.
Do not turn chicken, but baste frequently with pan drippings.

title: stuffed cucumber rings
directions: Cut both ends from cucumber; remove center with an apple corer.
Stuff cucumber with cream cheese.
Chill.
Slice.
Serve plain or on crackers.

title: crab newburg
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in medium saucepan and add green pepper and mushrooms; saute for five minutes.
In a small bowl, combine flour, pepper, salt and mustard.
Blend into melted margarine.
Add milk and wine, stirring constantly until mixture thickens (five or ten minutes).

title: chocolate clair dessert(lo-cal)
directions: Mix the vanilla pudding mix with 3 cups of milk, then fold in Cool Whip. Line a 13 x 9 pan with graham crackers. Spread 1/2 of the pudding mixture over the crackers. Put another layer of graham crackers and top with remaining pudding. Put a third layer of graham crackers. Mix the chocolate pudding mix with 1 1/2 cups of milk and spread entire chocolate mixture on grahams. Chill 4 to 6 hours.

title: hot dogs in a biscuit blanket(method:  foil)
directions: Mix biscuit mix with milk.
Roll out in a sheet approximately 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in 8 to 10 strips, about 1 inch shorter than the hot dogs are long.
Roll up each hot dog in one of these strips, leaving both ends exposed.
Wrap loosely in a lightly greased piece of foil, allowing plenty of room to expand.
Cook foil wrapped franks on top of the grill, 4 to 6 inches above coals, for 15 minutes, or until dough is cooked.

title: eggplant souffle
directions: Peel eggplant, dice and cook until tender in boiling water. Drain and mash well.
Melt butter in saucepan; stir in flour and mix well.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Add eggplant and cheese and stir.
Add onion, breadcrumbs, ketchup, salt and egg yolks. Remove from stove.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold egg whites into eggplant mixture.
Pour into greased souffle dish and set dish into a pan of hot water.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: date nut squares
directions: Beat eggs; mix with sugar.
Add flour, baking powder and salt. Mix well.
Add dates, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut in 1-inch squares.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: peach trifle
directions: Sprinkle dry peach gelatin over sliced peaches.
Mix and pour into a clear glass bowl or compote.
Place cubed pound cake over peaches.
Mix instant pudding mix with milk; beat and pour over cake before it thickens completely.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate until serving time.
Garnish with peach slices and mint sprigs, if desired.

title: crab soup
directions: Chop the bell pepper, celery and onions and blend in food processor.
Place all ingredients in a heavy pot.
Cover with milk and half and half.
Slowly bring to a boil.
Simmer for several hours.
You may need to add some more milk.
Does well in a crock-pot.

title: 7-up strawberry pie
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; cook until thick and clear. Cool.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with whipped cream.

title: meat balls deluxe
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients well and form into 6 balls.
Cover with the remaining ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° to 375°.

title: lalie's nameless wonder
directions: To Make Cake:
Bake cake mix in a 9 x13-inch pan as per instructions on box.
When cake is cool, cover top with Vanilla Pudding Icing.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Soak beans 6 to 8 hours; do not drain liquid.
Cut pork shank into cubes.
Add to beans with chopped onion; bring to boil. Simmer for 1 hour.
Reserve liquid.
Place drained beans and pork in crock-pot, mixing with remaining ingredients.
Pour liquid over beans, enough to cover (approximately 2 cups).
Cook on high 2 hours.
Turn to low; cook additional 5 hours.
Test to taste.

title: candy bar fudge bites
directions: Line 8 inch square pan with foil; extending over edges. Lightly butter foil and set aside.
In large microwave bowl, combine both flavored chips; microwave on medium for 1 to 2 minutes or until chips are melted.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in frosting and pieces from 2 candy bars. Spread in pan, sprinkle with rest of candy bars.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until firm. Remove fudge by lifting foil from fudge.
Cut into bite-sized pieces.

title: carrot fudge
directions: Cook the carrots, sugar, condensed milk and water to the soft-ball stage.
Remove the pan from the heat; add the lemon flavoring and cool to room temperature.
Beat until the mixture is creamy.
Pour the fudge into a shallow pan.
Pat it down to 1-inch depth and let it cool.
When it is firm, cut into squares.

title: cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites and baking powder until stiff.
Add to egg whites gradually the sugar and vanilla.
Fold in Ritz crackers and walnuts (if desired).
When cool, put on whipped cream.
Shred chocolate bar to decorate.

title: fudge pies
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa together and then mix eggs, milk and vanilla together.
Mix all together and put into 3 unbaked pie shells.
Cook 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
When shell is brown, pies should be done.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add sifted dry ingredients, flavoring and milk.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: one cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate before serving. Better if made the day before and stirred while kept in refrigerator.
Do not freeze!

title: no cook cereal cookies
directions: Cook syrup and sugar; bring to a boil. Add peanut butter and vanilla. Mix in Rice Krispies. Press into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: steak and gravy
directions: Pat hamburger into patties and roll in flour.
Slightly brown and place in a square pan.
After browning hamburger, put 2 teaspoons of flour in the same skillet; brown and add 1/2 cup milk and mushroom soup.
Stir until thick.
Add Kitchen Bouquet for color, if desired.
Pour over steak and bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken stew
directions: Cover potatoes with water and add chopped onions.
Cook until done.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Cook for another 30 to 45 minutes.

title: barbecued soybeans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put cooked soybeans with their liquid into a lightly oiled casserole.
Saute chopped onion and minced garlic in 2 tablespoons of oil until golden, but not brown.
Remove from heat and add to cooked soybeans.
Add the tomato juice, catsup, molasses, chopped green pepper, honey, dry mustard, chopped parsley and cayenne pepper.
Mix together thoroughly.
Lay strips of bacon on top of soybeans, if desired.
Place in preheated oven and bake 1 1/2 hours or until soybeans are tender.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Clean and cut broccoli in small pieces.
Cut onions in rings or dice. Add raisins and bacon.

title: bundt pound cake
directions: Place ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Mix on low to blend. Then beat 3 minutes on medium speed.
Pour batter in a fluted Bundt pan.
I grease and flour mine even if the pan is Teflon coated. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let cool 5 minutes, then turn out onto cooling rack.

title: ginataang pinoy
