directions: Add 1/2 cup coconut milk in a pan.
Add Knorr cube seasoning and gently boil.
Add ginger, sliced onions and tomatoes for 3 minutes.
Add chicken (meat), salt and boil
until half cooked. Add vegetables and cook another 5 to 10 minutes.
Add the remaining coconut milk and cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add fresh peppers on top.
Transfer to a platter and place onion rings on top.
Serve with rice and potatoes.

title: egg custard pies
directions: Mix all together.
Flour top with your favorite nutmeg or lemon cream.
I use lemon cream.
Bake at 400° until crust above the milk is browned.
Then turn the heat down on 345° and let them bake until the milk looks resin and thick like jello.
But don't overbake or they will be watery-like.

title: easy baked ham
directions: Smear onto the ham as much mustard and brown sugar as may be desired.
Place ham in a shallow baking dish, carefully add milk until it just covers ham.
Bake in a 325° oven until milk is largely consumed and a crust has formed over the ham.

title: orange pecan muffins
directions: Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add other ingredients.
Spoon into greased muffin pans, 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Spoon melted orange marmalade over tops of muffins while still warm.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Pour into a 3-quart buttered baking dish.

title: milky way icing
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in the top of a double boiler over hot water.
Heat, stirring constantly, until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar.
Beat well (by hand or mixer).
Pour over cake. Use to frost a 13 x 9-inch devil's food cake.

title: microwave chili cheese dip
directions: Press cream cheese into bottom of a 9-inch microwave dish. Pour chili on top of cream cheese.
Slice Mexican cheese and lay on top of chili until chili is covered.
Microwave, covered, for 5 minutes.

title: cherry crumb cake
directions: Mix together first four ingredients.
Add other ingredients, making crumbly mixture.
Spread 2/3 in buttered 8 x 12-inch pan.

title: scotty's cheese cakes
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy; add sugar, egg and lemon juice.
Beat again until fluffy.
Put vanilla wafers in bottom of cup cake liners.
Add 2/3 of cream mixture to cup cake liners. Bake 20 minutes (350°) or until set good.
Put filling on top. Refrigerate.

title: black-eyed pea dip
directions: In blender, smash black-eyed peas (easier to blend if you add some of the Ro-Tel and/or jalapeno juice with the peas).
Blend the onions, jalapenos and Ro-Tel until smooth as possible.
Chunk the Velveeta and add to mixture.
Microwave until cheese is melted.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: crumbs for fruit pies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Will be crumbly.
Put on top of pies.

title: devil dogs
directions: Mix shortening and sugar; add egg and blend well.
Add cocoa and dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla.
Place heaping teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 9 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain.
Mix with other ingredients.
Top with cheese, then stuffing mix and pat top with butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in 9 x 12-inch pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: charlie browns
directions: Bring butter, cocoa, sugar and milk to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from stove and add 1/2 cup peanut butter and 3 cups of oatmeal.
Mix well.
Spoon out on wax paper.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash in covered saucepan until soft.
Drain and save liquid, then mash squash.
Dissolve bouillon in 1/2 cup of squash liquid.
Saute onion in butter until clear.
Add onion, bouillon and 2 ounces of cheese to squash.
Cool.
Beat eggs and fold into squash mixture.
Pour into buttered casserole and top with remaining cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with crumbs and return to oven for 15 minutes.

title: clam dip
directions: Drain clams.
Mix all ingredients.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain off excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve with grated cheese on top and a dollop of sour cream.
Crumble tortilla chips into soup or serve on the side.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread crumbs in scalded milk until soft.
Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar, salt, nutmeg, vanilla and raisins.
Mix thoroughly with bread mixture.
Pour into greased baking dish and set in pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
(Can be topped while hot with vanilla pudding, either instant or cooked.)

title: beer batter fried shrimp
directions: To make batter:
Combine beer, water and vegetable oil.
Sift in the flour and salt; stir only until blended.
Fold in stiff egg white.
If necessary, add a bit more water to make a thin batter. Peel and devein shrimp, leaving on tails.
Dip shrimp in batter. Deep fry shrimp at 375° for 2 to 3 minutes, just until pink. Serve hot with French fries and cole slaw.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Bring 1 1/2 cups water to a boil; stir in both packs of jello. Drain juice from pineapple and oranges (should make 1 1/2 cups); mix juice with jello.
Add pineapple and oranges; chill 1 hour. Add marshmallows.
Mix pudding according to directions; put on top of marshmallows.
Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese; add on top of pudding.
Grate block cheese for last topping.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in oil; season with salt and pepper.
Place in casserole dish.
Cover with rice.
Mix soup and milk together and pour over rice, being careful to cover rice with liquid. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Chicken soup will be absorbed by rice and pork chops.

title: johnny cake
directions: Combine ingredients; pour into 8 x 10-inch baking pan.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: "kaylee's poor man's frosting"
directions: In saucepan, combine flour and milk.
Heat on medium. Stir constantly until thick.
Cool completely.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crust ingredients in a 9 x13 pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Let cool.

title: chicken on sunday
directions: Mix together rice, cream of celery soup, cream of mushroom soup and milk.
Place in greased 9 x 12-inch dish.
Place chicken on top.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Seal tightly with foil. Bake at 325° for 2 hours and 15 minutes.
Do not peek!

title: apricot salad
directions: Combine and stir until completely dissolved, Jell-O and boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch dish and refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Top with 1/2 package white miniature marshmallows.
Chill until firm.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop cranberries in blender.
Add sugar, pineapple and marshmallows.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Mix cheese and Cool Whip.
Add to berry mixture and stir in nuts.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: hot and sweet chinese chicken
directions: Combine chicken, egg white, salt and cornstarch; set aside. Heat peanut oil in skillet or wok and stir-fry chili peppers until brown and pungent.
Add chicken mixture and stir-fry 30 seconds. Add vegetables and continue stir-frying another 30 seconds.
Blend in remaining ingredients and cook and stir-fry for 2 minutes. Serves 4.

title: peach preserves
directions: Drain any liquid from peaches before cooking.
Cook until thick (2 to 3 hours).
Ladle into jelly jars and seal with wax. This is so easy to do.

title: no crust pizza
directions: Combine 1/3 cup liquid, bread crumbs, egg, salt and pepper. Let stand 5 minutes.
Add ground beef, oregano and half the mushrooms.
Mix lightly.
Form mixture into a 9-inch round pan. Slice cheese into 8 triangles.
Place 4 on pie.
Top with sauce, onion, green pepper, remaining mushrooms and dash of oregano. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake additional 5 minutes.
Let sit 10 minutes before cutting.

title: banana "slush" punch
directions: Boil water and sugar.
Cool and add remaining ingredients, except ginger ale.
Freeze mixture in freezer bags for approximately 2 to 3 hours before serving. Remove from freezer and add ginger ale.

title: parmesan corn chowder
directions: Cook potatoes, celery and carrots in boiling water with salt and pepper for 10 minutes.
Make white sauce of flour, margarine and milk.
Melt cheese in sauce.
Add corn to sauce and then stir into vegetables.
Heat before serving.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; salt and pepper to taste. Add taco seasoning and remove from heat. Mix well. Cool. Toss together with lettuce, beans, onion, peppers, cheese and tomatoes. Just before serving, mix salsa and dressing. Add to salad along with crushed Doritos. Toss well.

title: cream of corn soup
directions: Melt the butter; simmer onion in it until soft.
Stir in the flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in corn and milk.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: braised pork chops with fruit
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Sear pork chops in a hot lightly greased skillet.
Season lightly.
Place apples, apricots, prunes or pineapple slices on the chops skin side down.
Fill the center of the fruit with brown sugar.
Cover the bottom of the skillet to 1/2-inch with chicken stock or fruit juice. Cover the pan closely.
Bake for 50 minutes.
Remove the chops from the pan carefully, so as not to disturb the fruit.
Keep warm.
Remove some of the fat from the juices and add sweet or cultured sour cream to the pan juices.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients well.

title: smothered cabbage wedges
directions: Cut cabbage into 8 wedges.
Cooked in small amount boiling salted water about 10 minutes, drain.
Saute vegetables in butter. Combine flour, salt, and pepper.
Stir into sauteed vegetables. Stir in milk.
Stir until bubbly and thick.
Arrange cabbage in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour vegetable sauce over cabbage.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 375°.
Combine mayonnaise, cheese and chili sauce.
Spoon over cabbage.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: chunky guacamole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Serve with plain tortilla chips.
Yield 1 1/2- 2 cups.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut round steak in pieces.
Flour and brown.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Top with sliced onion and green pepper.
Pour tomato sauce over everything.
Bake at 250° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Put in baking pan after browning, then top with onion and pepper.

title: stir-fried asparagus
directions: In skillet, melt butter. Add bouillon, celery salt, dill, salt and pepper; mix. Add asparagus; coat and cover.
Cook for 2 minutes. Add soy sauce. Serve.

title: italian beef
directions: Place roast, fat side up, on a rack in a shallow roasting pan. Roast, uncovered, in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or to 145°. Transfer roast to a platter.
Skim fat from the pan juices. Transfer juices to a covered container; chill.
Cool roast for 30 minutes.
Cover and chill.
Using a sharp knife, thinly slice the chilled roast across the grain.

title: jello pinwheels
directions: Lightly spray 8 or 9-inch square pan with
nonstick cooking spray.
Use a paper towel to spread on bottom and sides.

title: apple crisp
directions: In 2-quart (8 x 8-inch) baking dish, arrange apples.
Combine flour, rolled oats, brown sugar and cinnamon; cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over top of apples.
Cook, uncovered, 12 minutes or until apples are tender.
If you prefer a more crunchy, brown topping, place under the broiler a few minutes.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: dough art
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Knead until it forms a medium stiff smooth dough.
Add more flour or water, if needed.
For color; work in dabs of paste food coloring.
For white dough:
Mix in white acrylic paint.
Store in refrigerator until ready.
Place flour on a waxed paper covered surface.
Roll out dough to 1/2-inch thick.
Dip cookie cutters in flour and cut out shapes.
Dry in 325° oven for 1 to 2 hours or until shapes are hard to the touch. Melt paraffin in double boiler.
Using slotted spoon dip each shape in wax.
Transfer to wire racks over newspaper.

title: spaghetti primavera
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain. Meanwhile, in large skillet, heat oil and saute zucchini, red and bell peppers and garlic until vegetables are just tender.
Stir in cream, then 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and seasonings until evenly blended.
Heat through until slightly thickened, being careful not to boil. Toss hot cooked spaghetti with sauteed vegetable mixture. Serve sprinkled with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: poor boy cobbler
directions: Melt oleo and put in bottom of cake pan (9 x 13-inch).
Put in fruit.
Mix flour, sugar and egg.
Put on top of fruit.
Bake at 325° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: a perfect pie crust
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in a large bowl and mix well with a fork.
Add shortening and mix well with fork until crumbly.
In a small bowl, beat 1/2 cup water, vinegar and egg with a fork. Combine the two mixtures, stirring until all ingredients are moist.
Divide dough in 5 portions and shape each portion in a flat round patty ready for rolling.

title: jelly roll
directions: Sift
flour
once.
Beat
eggs, adding sugar gradually, until mixture becomes thick and light colored.
Gradually fold in
flour and
vanilla.
Pour onto cookie sheet that has been greased. Bake in hot oven at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: hanky panky's
directions: Brown beef and sausage; drain. Cut cheese into cubes and melt into meat. Add garlic, onion and oregano. Spread mixture on bread. Broil slightly. Can be made ahead of time. Freezes well.

title: cranberry salad(new england treasure)
directions: Grind cranberries and orange, rind and all.
Add sugar. Dissolve lemon Jell-O in hot water.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Take 1 pound ground meat and cook it for about 10 minutes. Take 2 cans corn and put over ground meat.
Cook until warm.
Take corn bread mix and mix it with a little water and 1 egg; stir. Take half of corn bread mix and spread it in the pan.
Take corn and meat and put it on top of corn bread mix.
Spread it around and take the other half of corn bread mix and spread on top of meat and corn.
Cook for about 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: pan-fried chicken(4 servings)
directions: Preheat a nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken breasts and brown 10 minutes on each side.
Reduce heat.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes, turning occasionally.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: no-crust norwegian apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix in walnuts and diced apple.
Beat in (whisk or spoon) egg and vanilla.
This will be very thick.
Put into 8 or 9-inch greased pie plate.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Add ice cream or other topping.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and butter and boil for 1 minute. Combine milk, peanut butter and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Pour sugar mixture over this and beat well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
Cool and serve.

title: cornbread stuffing
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cornbread, onion, celery and seasonings in a large bowl. Mix well. Blend in broth and milk. Mixture should be very soft to allow for loss of moisture during baking. Add more broth if necessary. Cover and chill 8 hours. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or golden brown.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until thick.
Pour into 8-inch baked pie shell.
Meringue, if desired.

title: microwave vegetables
directions: Mix onion soup mix, tarragon and melted butter.
Separate cauliflower and broccoli into flowerets and coat with soup. Microwave for 6 to 8 minutes.
Next, add cherry tomatoes.
Cook 1 more minute and keep covered until ready to serve.

title: spoonburgers
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain.
Add soup and bring to a boil.
Add cheese, meat and add flour.
Stir and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: cheerio bars
directions: Melt the oleo in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over melted oleo.
Do not stir.
Sprinkle marshmallows and Cheerios over cake mix.
Dribble condensed milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix honey and butter in saucepan.
Blend over low heat.
Mix in popped corn and peanuts in large bowl.
Mix well to coat each kernel.
Spread in single layer on cookie sheet. Bake for 10 to 15 minutes until crisp.
Cool.

title: hooper fishing and hunter recipe
directions: Wrap eggs in foil before boiling.
They will not crack.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Scald the milk.
Mix flour, sugar, salt and cocoa in separate bowl.
Add a little hot milk to flour mixture to make consistency like gravy. Mix. Then add to rest of hot milk. Add egg yolks, butter and vanilla. Cook over low heat until thick.
Pour into pie crust and refrigerate.

title: dump cake
directions: Sprinkle brown sugar over bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Dot with 1/2 stick butter.
Dump in and spread with juices, pineapple and cherries.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over mixture.
Dot with rest of butter.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon. Mix with first 5 ingredients and stir until well blended.
Add walnuts.
Pour into an ungreased large loaf pan. Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place each breast in freezer Baggie.
Pound lightly with mallet to make 1/4-inch thick cutlets, working from center out.
Place cheese slice and ham slice on each piece of chicken.
Tuck in sides and roll up, pressing to seal well.
May use toothpicks.
Coat with bread crumbs.
Heat butter or canola oil in skillet.
Brown chicken.
Remove to 11 x 7-inch casserole dish.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Beat egg yolks and sugar until light.
Add flour, baking powder and juice.
Fold in egg whites.
Melt 1/2 stick butter and 1 cup brown sugar in skillet.
Arrange sliced pineapple, cherries and pecans in bottom.
Add batter and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mom's awesome lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in salted water, as per directions.
Drain and set aside.
Heat oil in a skillet.
Cook garlic and onion until soft. Add beef and seasonings, cooking until crumbly.
Add tomato paste and hot water to meat mixture and simmer for approximately 5 minutes, then set aside.
Blend eggs with cottage cheese and ricotta cheese, then set aside.
In a 9 x 13 baking dish, spoon a thin layer of meat sauce and a layer of noodles.
Next add 1/2 of the cottage cheese and egg mixture, topped with some Swiss and mozzarella cheese.
Spoon on an additional layer of meat sauce, another layer of noodles, the remaining egg mixture and cover again with Swiss and mozzarella cheese.
Top with remaining meat sauce and top with grated parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Allow Lasagna to cool for 10 minutes before serving.

title: raspberry punch
directions: Add water for 3 gallons.
Can be placed in freezer and stirred occasionally until slushy.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream sugars, oleo and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla. Add nuts and chips.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip, pineapple and marshmallows. Add pudding mix. Top with cherries, if desired. Refrigerate for several hours or overnight. This will stay good for several days.

title: chicken with peas and bacon
directions: Salt and pepper the chicken; brown in the olive oil and remove it from pan.
Combine peppers, onion, bacon, parsley and garlic and saute in the oil and juice in the browning pan.
Add the chicken; cover and cook over slow heat for 30 minutes or until chicken is done.
Add peas and cook 5 minutes more.
If using fresh or frozen peas, precook partially.

title: joan quay's sour cream cookies
directions: In a large bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In another bowl, combine softened butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Mix one cup of sour cream with "fluffy" ingredients.
Add flour mixture a little at a time.
Set until cold.
Roll out for Christmas cookies.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together in order shown and bake 45 minutes at 350° in muffins or iron skillet.

title: easy cherry cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except can of cherries, and pour into baked and cooled graham cracker crust.
Pour the can of cherries on top.
Chill.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Mix margarine and cocoa.
Beat eggs slightly and add sugar and salt.
Stir in cocoa. Blend well.
Add flour and vanilla, then nuts.
Spoon batter in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows on top of warm cake.
Cover with your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread coconut and pecans on bottom of pan.
Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Mix cream cheese, butter and 10x sugar. Drop by spoonfuls over cake.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes exactly. Cake will be shaky when taken out of oven, but will set up as cools.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch heat resistant glass pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Cut tortillas into 8 pieces.
Spread half of tortillas in pan.
Add half the chicken, broken into bite size pieces.
Repeat layers.
Dissolve cornstarch in broth.
Cook over medium heat.
Add onion, tomatoes and chilies; add mushrooms (drained).
Add milk.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Pour sauce over chicken and top with cheese and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: hot spinach dip
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine cheese, milk, butter, bouillon and nutmeg.
Cook and stir over low heat until thickened.
Stir in spinach; heat.
Remove from heat and add lemon juice.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Spray nonstick skillet with vegetable cooking spray.
Heat 1 minute.
Stir-fry chicken in 2 batches until browned.
Remove.

title: white wine sangria
directions: Cut one of each fruit in half and slice for garnish.
Squeeze juice from rest.
Combine juice with wine, brandy, honey, cinnamon stick and grapes in large glass container.
Cover. Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and fruit slices.
Serve over ice.
Makes 12 (3/4 cup) servings.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Melt butter in water.
Remove from heat; stir in stuffing, then egg and sausage.
Blend thoroughly.
Chill for 1 hour. Shape into small balls.
Cut bacon strips into thirds, crosswise. Wrap bacon around dressing mixture and fasten with toothpick. Place on rack in shallow pan and bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until brown and crisp.
Drain on paper towel and serve hot.
May be made ahead of time and frozen before baking.
Yields 36 appetizers.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and rolled oats.
Stir to mix well and drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: the "anything goes" pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Place macaroni in a large bowl.
Add the olive oil, salt and pepper. Add artichoke hearts, roasted pepper, capers, tomatoes, cheese and parsley; stir gently to combine.
Set aside.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Dredge meat in blended flour, garlic salt, salt and pepper. Reserve extra flour mixture.
Brown meat in butter, then add onions and mushrooms.
Cook until tender and browned.
Stir in 2 tablespoons reserved flour.
Gradually add broth, Worcestershire and catsup, stirring until boiling.
Add sour cream, heat well. Serve over noodles.

title: toll house pie
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add flour, brown sugar, sugar and margarine, then stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into one 8-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve warm or cooled.
Great.
Just like a chocolate chip cookie.

title: party punch
directions: Chill all ingredients.
In punch bowl combine punch, grapefruit juice and grenadine.
Add strawberries.
Just before serving, add 7-Up.
Float orange slices on top.

title: pineapple blueberry cream
directions: Crush corn flakes fine and bake 10 minutes.
Add sugar and butter and press in pan.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well by hand and form into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Use over poultry or meat.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and vanilla well.
Mix in half and half. Pour into freezer can.
Put motor in place.
Start freezer.
In freezer
bucket, alternate a layer of crushed ice with a layer of kosher or rock salt.
When ice bucket is half full, pour a cup or two of water on ice to speed melting.
Continue alternating ice and salt.
It takes from 40 minutes to one hour to freeze. Freezer will stop when it's done.
Remove motor and take off top of can, being careful not to get salty ice in ice cream.
Remove the beater from the can.
Put cork in hole and pack with ice.
Let set a few hours.

title: quick casserole
directions: Salt and pepper ground beef to taste.
Add onion and green pepper.
Press down in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with mushroom soup.
Spread grated cheese over top.
Place potato nuggets over cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
(This may be divided into 2 smaller pans.)
Freezes well.

title: turtle candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch together, then put in the peanuts. Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.

title: chocolate shake
directions: Place all ingredients in blender. Blend until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Yields 3 servings.
Has 130 calories, less than 1 g fat.

title: monkey balls or caramel coffee cake ring
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray Pam generously in a Bundt pan. Sprinkle 3/4 tablespoon nuts in bottom of pan.
Separate biscuits. Gently pull each in half and form into balls (20 balls per can). Melt together butter, sugar and water.
Mix in nuts.
Place 1/2 dough balls in pan, pour 1/2 of melted mixture over them, finish with the rest of the balls and top with remaining mixture.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Let cool and invert onto plate.

title: salad dressing(christmas red)
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding salad oil last.
Do in blender. Very good.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and place in 9 x 9-inch pan. Combine brown sugar, flour, oats and oleo.
Press on top of rhubarb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Chill thoroughly if desired.
Cut into bars. Cool at least one hour before cutting.
Store loosely covered at room temperature. Makes about 36 bars.

title: broken glass salad
directions: Mold jello
in
separate
flat
pans, using 1 1/2 cups water for each.
Chill
until
firm, then cut into small squares.
Heat pineapple juice.
Dissolve
Knox gelatine in 1/4 cup cold water and add pineapple juice.
Chill
until
it
starts
to set.
Add to 2 cups whipped cream; sugar and
vanilla.
Fold in jello cubes. Make crumbs of graham crackers, sugar
and butter.
Line dish with crumbs.
Add filling and sprinkle remainder of crumbs on top.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Fold in Cool Whip. Then add fruit and nuts.
(Peach is my favorite.)

title: velvet banana bread
directions: Combine bananas and eggs.
Cream shortening and sugar and add banana-egg mixture.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir well and add nuts.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 large or 4 small bread pans.
(I prefer to spray with Pam.)
Mix berries, eggs and oil together with mixer on low speed.
Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, soda and salt in large bowl.
Add to strawberry mixture. Blend with mixer until all dry ingredients are mixed in well. Stir in nuts, if desired.
Pour evenly into prepared bread pans. Bake 1 hour or until toothpick in center comes out clean.

title: 2 x 4 soup
directions: Mix and heat in crockpot.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening well.
Add eggs, vanilla and then dry ingredients.
Drop on greased baking sheet.
Bake in moderate oven until lightly browned.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake until brown at 400°. For quickie grating, chopping and mixing, put all ingredients (except cornbread mix) into blender; chop well.
Add to dry mixture and stir well.
Pour into well Pamed pan and bake.

title: jam filled muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. In small bowl, lightly beat eggs; add milk, butter and lemon peel.
Pour into dry ingredients; stir just until moistened. Spoon half of batter into 12 greased or lined muffin cups.
Make well in center of each; add jam.
Spoon remaining batter over jam. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: my mom's pear salad
directions: Line bowls with lettuce.
Place 2 pear halves in each bowl. Put small "dollop" of mayo in center of each pear.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Serve cold.

title: chicken-fried steak
directions: First prepare steak by trimming it well and tenderizing.
Then pat it with paper towels.
Dip in egg and milk mixture and coat with bread crumbs.
Fry in olive oil at 375°.
Season to taste on both sides, but remember that a little red pepper goes a long way. Enjoy!

title: "good pickles"
directions: Combine ingredients.
Boil, then drop pickles in until they turn jar hot and seal.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, add sugar gradually.
Cream until fluffy, add unbeaten egg
and
vanilla,
beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients, blend into
cream mixture, chill dough.
Roll out on well floured board 1/8-inch thick.	Cut out.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen, depending on size.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Melt mayonnaise and cheese over low heat or microwave 5 minutes.
Fry bacon until very crispy.
Crumble bacon into cheese sauce.
Mix frozen or thawed potatoes with cheese mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Makes 2 (13 x 9-inch) pans.
Recipe may be cut in half.
